INSERT INTO `features` VALUES (1,'feature','Add feature voting','Add some user voting system for features so that users can have some sway on what gets developed next.\r\n[[para]]\r\nInitial thoughts are that a user will get 3 votes. These can be spread over different features or piled onto one that they really think is important.',1,'closed','2009-03-15 17:17:05','2009-03-21 05:56:30','implemented'),(2,'feature','Altitude profile charts','Display an altitude profile chart for each track.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe chart should be in the \'Altitude\' section of the track description and could be in addition to the existing up/down/start/end altitude summary.',23,'open','2009-03-15 20:32:01','2009-03-18 06:22:03','accepted'),(3,'problem','Label misalignment ','On some tracks the \'Grade\' label is misaligned.  As in this example:[[br]]\r\n[[image:http://i443.photobucket.com/albums/qq159/ian314159_pics/GradeLabelProblem.png:Ridgeline example:321:204]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis problem seems to be only for tracks that haven\'t been updated for a while.',23,'closed','2009-03-16 12:54:51','2009-03-21 05:58:10','implemented'),(4,'problem','Comment count not displaying for Problems','As per title. This is minor and an easy fix.',1,'closed','2009-03-17 08:55:36','2009-03-21 05:55:31','implemented'),(5,'problem','Track summary formatting is untidy','The display of summary information for each Area and State is untidy.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt could be improved by:[[br]]\r\n- sorting the list[[br]]\r\n- always displaying the distances to 2 decimal places[[br]]\r\n- right aligning the numbers[[br]]\r\n- putting a dividing line above the total distance, and[[br]]\r\n- adding \"of\" into the track count.\r\n[[para]]\r\nPerhaps something like the following:[[br]]\r\n[[image:http://i443.photobucket.com/albums/qq159/ian314159_pics/TrackSummary.png:Track summary:465:151]]',23,'closed','2009-03-17 20:58:20','2009-03-22 05:37:43','implemented'),(6,'problem','Track Report font','The user name and date under each track report has a font that looks too large.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:01:34','2009-03-21 05:59:13','implemented'),(7,'problem','kml file is lost when a track\'s area is changed','If a track is changed to be in a different area then the kml file no longer works.  This seems to occur because the kml file name includes both the region and the area numbers.  Presumably the kml file becomes orphaned, being no longer associated with a track.  \r\n[[para]]\r\nA suggested solution is to change the kml file naming convention to reflect only unique and unchanging attributes of the track â€“ such as the track number.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:02:37','2009-03-22 05:38:28','implemented'),(8,'problem','Allow apostrophes in the \'Also known as\' field','Currently an error message is displayed if the user attempts to include an apostrophe in the \'Also known as\' field.  For example, Possum Bait Line (in the Makara area) is also known as Grant\'s Track.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:04:16','2009-06-03 11:59:55','implemented'),(9,'problem','Controls for editing connecting tracks','To be consistent with the \'Add report\' link for track reports, the \'Edit\' link for connecting tracks should be above the list.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSimilarly, when editing the connecting tracks list for a track, the track lists and the \'Done\' link move whenever a connecting track is added or deleted â€“ which is somewhat awkward.  It would be better if they didn\'t move â€“ which could be achieved by repositioning them to be above the list of connecting tracks.  \r\n[[para]]\r\nThis would also mean that the Edit and Done links would be in the same position, which would be good from a usability perspective.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:06:51','2009-03-21 06:00:37','implemented'),(10,'feature','Add Street View in an InfoWindow','Google Street View provides a perspective that may be useful for finding some tracks.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSee [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/streetview/ this example]] and click on each icon to see an InfoWindow that contains a Street View of that location.  The view is interactive, so the user can look around, zoom in/out, and even move the viewing position along the street.',23,'open','2009-03-17 21:09:19','2009-03-18 06:01:46','accepted'),(11,'feature','Display multiple tracks on a map','Currently each track is presented in isolation.  This makes it difficult to see how each track relates to those around it.  A consequence of this isolation is that it is difficult to plan a ride that includes several tracks.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt would be good to show how nearby tracks relate to each other. One possibility would be to display the \'Connecting Tracks\' on the map in addition to the track being described.  \r\n[[para]]\r\nPerhaps the \'Connecting Tracks\' list could be redefined to be a list of \'Adjacent Tracks\' that it is helpful to display on the same map, even if they don\'t actually connect to the track being described.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe additional tracks could be displayed in a different colour, to distinguish them from the main track of interest. Displaying a track in a colour that differs from the kml style is possible, though it requires some JavaScript to parse the file and set the colour manually, rather than using the defined style.\r\n[[para]]\r\nA key problem with this idea is that the Google Maps API doesn\'t cope well with multiple kml files or many track points. That is, the map displays very slowly or not at all if there is too much data. It would take some investigation to find a solution that has satisfactory performance.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:13:16','2009-06-03 12:06:54','implemented'),(12,'feature','Enable embedded YouTube videos','Allow the user to specify a YouTube video to embed in the track description.  This could involve a new tag such as \'\\[\\[youtube:â€¦\\]\\]\'.  Given that the description text area is 492 pixels wide, the YouTube video size option of 480x385 pixels would be essentially ideal.\r\n[[para]]\r\nNote that YouTube videos can currently be added to an InfoWindow on the map via the kml description field (see [[track:78]] for an example), though it would be more obvious to the user if the video is directly embedded in the track description.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:16:01','2009-08-10 04:20:56','implemented'),(13,'problem','Track tags don\'t work in feature requests','It seems that track reference tags within a feature request are not parsed.  External Link and image tags are parsed though.\r\n[[para]]\r\nFor example, see the \'Enable embedded YouTube videos\' feature request.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:18:31','2009-03-21 05:58:26','implemented'),(14,'feature','Add a tag to format as a bullet point list','Several track descriptions, along with the \'About\' page, include bullet point lists.  Currently these lists are created manually.  It would be better to include a tag to create a nicely formatted bullet point list, with some type of bullet point that matches the design of the site, has appropriate spacing and included a hanging indent.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSee the external link in the Street View feature request for an example list.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:21:53','2009-06-14 05:01:33','implemented'),(15,'feature','Hosting of embedded images','Provide an upload and hosting facility for images that are embedded in the track descriptions.\r\n[[para]]\r\nCurrently images are hosted externally, which is awkward and leaves open the possibility of missing images at a later time if the external hosting arrangement changes.',23,'open','2009-03-17 21:25:27','2009-03-18 05:57:32','accepted'),(16,'feature','Formatting of embedded images','Provide some additional formatting options for embedded images, such as: left, right, or centre alignment; wrapping text around the image (float left/right); and borders.',23,'open','2009-03-17 21:29:49','2009-03-18 05:59:27','accepted'),(17,'feature','Tidier ellipsis display for track reports','The Track Report list on the Home page and each region page has a couple of issues:[[br]]\r\n1. the right-hand side of the list is ragged, and[[br]]\r\n2. links to internal or external pages fail to display properly if they are truncated by the ellipsis.\r\n[[para]]\r\nA suggested alternative treatment for the ellipsis display is shown in [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/truncate this example]].',23,'open','2009-03-17 21:31:55','2009-03-18 05:41:22','accepted'),(18,'problem','\'Delete comment\' link needs a line break','After adding a comment to a Feature, the \'Delete comment\' link needs a line break before it, as it currently continues on the same line as the end of the comment.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:40:16','2009-03-21 05:55:58','implemented'),(19,'feature','Swap between Feature and Problem','Sometimes the distinction between a Feature suggestion and a Problem report isn\'t obvious.  That is, a Problem report might evolve into a Feature request.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt would be good to be able to change the type from one to the other.',23,'closed','2009-03-17 21:42:50','2009-03-22 05:35:04','implemented'),(20,'problem','Apply special formatting for feature/problem comments','The special formatting does not get replaced for feature/problem comments.',1,'closed','2009-03-18 05:55:36','2009-03-21 05:55:04','implemented'),(21,'feature','Add email sending','Tracks currently does not send any email. This would be useful on occasion. E.g signup verification, feature comment added.',1,'open','2009-03-18 06:26:10','2009-03-18 06:26:28','accepted'),(22,'problem','Comments are being truncated','This is bad. Wrong database type methinks',1,'closed','2009-03-18 07:32:21','2009-03-18 07:42:11','implemented'),(23,'feature','WYSIWYG editing of content','Creating and editing track descriptions would be much more user friendly if they included some form of WYSIWYG facility.\r\n[[para]]\r\nOne obvious candidate for adding this functionality is [[link:http://tinymce.moxiecode.com/index.php Tiny MCE]].  There are many ways in which Tiny MCE can be used for adding WYSIWYG editing to content - the most similar to the tags that Tracks uses is the [[link:http://tinymce.moxiecode.com/examples/example_09.php BBCode]] mode (click the \'Toggle WYSIWYG\' button to see what it is doing).',23,'open','2009-03-18 10:56:10','2009-03-24 05:08:38','accepted'),(24,'feature','Unique identifier for each Suggested Feature or Reported Problem','It might sometimes be useful to reference a Suggested Feature or a Reported Problem. For example, to indicate that a new Suggested Feature is related to an existing Suggested Feature or Reported Problem in some way (though sufficiently different that it warrants a new item rather than being a comment or edit of an existing item).\r\n[[para]]\r\nTo do so, each item would need some type of unique identifier to be displayed.  Usage could be in the form of either a link or a drop-down list (like the connecting tracks).',23,'closed','2009-03-18 11:04:28','2009-03-21 05:56:52','implemented'),(25,'feature','Gallery of images','Have a gallery of images for each track and perhaps each area.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThere are many tools available for displaying a gallery or a slide show.  [[link:http://highslide.com HighSlide]] is one particularly good tool, with many presentation variations.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSee [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/gallery/gallery.html this mockup]] for an example of a gallery that would fit within the Track content area.\r\n[[para]]\r\nUsage of Highslide is fairly straightforward, requiring minimal coding. I suspect most of the work to implement this type of feature would be in the management of the images - with each one requiring an image, a thumbnail of appropriate size, a title, and a caption.',23,'open','2009-03-18 21:09:34','2009-05-17 05:38:48','accepted'),(26,'feature','Test environment','Recently we\'ve been testing various features using the live website - such as YouTube Videos in a map InfoWindow, Street View, elevation charts, putting altitude data in kml files, etc.  Using the live site for this testing isn\'t ideal - it would be better to have a playpen where these things could be tested without potentially messing up live pages.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSo, I wonder if a simple test environment could be created by having a Region that is hidden except when a user is logged in to the site.  We could then create areas and tracks within that test region to try various things, without messing up the publically visible site.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSuch a play pen would also provide new content creators with an opportunity to practice with creating/editing content without fear of breaking a live page.',23,'closed','2009-03-19 11:25:15','2009-06-03 11:25:53','implemented'),(27,'feature','Allow Features/Problems to be re-opened','It might sometimes be useful to re-open a Feature Request or a Problem Report, to add additional information - for example, if the problem recurs.\r\n[[para]]\r\nNote that I don\'t currently have anything I want to re-open, so this feature is on the \'nice to have\' list.',23,'open','2009-03-21 08:34:31','2009-03-22 05:33:53','developing'),(28,'feature','Show closed date for Feature/Problem','Currently a Feature/Problem shows the Suggested/Reported date and the Updated date. For completeness, it would be helpful to also show the Closed date.',23,'closed','2009-03-21 08:36:16','2009-03-22 05:37:15','implemented'),(29,'feature','Timestamp comments on Feature/Problem','Currently the Feature/Problem list shows the number of comments and the name of the last person to comment - for example, \"(2, Jonny)\".  It would be helpful to also show a timestamp for the last comment - for example \"(2, Jonny, 6:22am 18 Mar 09)\" - as there is no indication in the Features/Problems list of when a comment has been added.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSince adding a timestamp would make the bracketed bit quite long, perhaps it should always be on the next line?\r\n[[para]]\r\nAnd maybe make the font size/colour consistent with that used for the Track Reports?',23,'closed','2009-03-21 08:43:02','2009-03-22 05:36:25','implemented'),(30,'feature','Rating system for tracks','It\'d be great to be able to rate tracks, with a star system like in the Kennett Brothers book or similar. I guess we could start adding rating info into track reports... The ideal situation would be a voting system, where logged in users could vote tracks up or down. ',59,'open','2009-03-21 21:27:28','2009-03-22 05:40:01','accepted'),(31,'feature','Create \"classic rides\" section','In a previous version of Tracks there was a \"Classic Routes\" section that combined collections of existing tracks into a good loop/ride. It would be nice to have this feature back.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt would replace some of the existing tracks that are really collections of tracks, such as [[link:tracks.org.nz/tracks/show/268 GrandLoop]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis will be dependent on  [[link:tracks.org.nz/features/11 #0011]] (Display multiple tracks on a map)',1,'open','2009-03-22 04:39:59','2009-04-28 01:07:18','accepted'),(32,'problem','Can\'t delete own posts','Hi \r\n\r\nMistakenly posted several posts today using google chrome browser (update button didn\'t refresh screen).  Tried to delete extra posts but couldn\'t. Delete feature for own posts would be cool.\r\n\r\nCheers',92,'closed','2009-03-24 18:16:51','2009-08-07 07:25:17','implemented'),(33,'feature','Allow edit of last feature/problem comment','Next to the \"Delete comment\" add a \"Edit\" option. This will only apply to the last comment and you can only edit|delete your own.',1,'closed','2009-03-25 04:03:44','2009-06-03 12:00:56','implemented'),(34,'problem','Search result links open in new window','This annoys me! Investigate if this can be changed.',1,'closed','2009-03-25 05:07:26','2009-10-15 02:35:19','implemented'),(35,'problem','Rain gauge has disappeared','Where did the rain gauge go?',23,'open','2009-03-26 07:21:36','2009-04-05 07:39:12','accepted'),(36,'feature','Format for printing','Printing pages from Tracks doesn\'t work well - the content is mangled to the point of being almost unusable. This occurs across a variety of browsers.\r\n[[para]]\r\nI wonder if having a CSS media type for print would help?\r\n[[para]]\r\nAlternatively, or perhaps in addition, being able to print a mini track guide to take on a ride would be a useful feature?',23,'closed','2009-03-26 07:26:36','2009-10-15 02:34:59','implemented'),(37,'problem','Overview map','The overview map on each Google Map (in the bottom right corner) is now displayed by default, even though the code says it should be hidden.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis is probably a bug in the Maps API - or has something changed on Tracks?',23,'open','2009-03-26 07:30:09','2009-06-04 00:14:34','developing'),(38,'feature','News section','I wonder if it would be useful to have a News section, in which announcements could be made when there are significant new features, bug fixes, areas added, track updates that we want to highlight, etc.\r\n[[para]]\r\nPerhaps have the News created at the Region level, and automatically aggregated to be shown on the home page?  Under the Navigator would seem like a good location.',23,'open','2009-03-29 08:57:23','2009-06-04 10:07:39','developing'),(39,'feature','More searching and exploring of data','Add some different ways to search and explore Tracks data. eg by all beginner tracks.[[para]]\r\nMaybe an \"advanced search\" page?[[para]]\r\nFrom an email request/question from Sam.\r\n',1,'open','2009-04-18 12:29:34','2009-09-27 05:07:34','accepted'),(40,'feature','View the tracks and descriptions live in Google Earth','I use this pair of KML files all the time: [[br]]\r\n[[link:http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/globallists.cfm?listpage=googleearth http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/globallists.cfm?listpage=googleearth]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe second link is the cool one - it updates at a prescribed frequency from the site.\r\n[[para]]\r\nMight be something worth considering here. It\'s nice to see a map of everything when you\'re deciding on the day\'s ride.\r\n[[para]]\r\nI\'d be happy to work on how to code it. What are you folks using as the back end - Java and PHP?',102,'open','2009-04-20 09:12:06','2009-04-20 09:21:01','new'),(41,'feature','Track AKAs are clunky','The tracks Also Known As editing is really clunky. This should be made nicer...',1,'open','2009-04-26 16:02:18','2009-04-26 16:02:18','new'),(42,'feature','Links section','It would be good to add a list of relevant links.  The list could include things like: [[link:http://www.wellington.govt.nz/ WCC]], [[link:http://gw.govt.nz/ GWRC]], [[link:http://feelinggreat.co.nz/facilities-and-venues/mountain-bike-tracks/ Feeling Great]], [[link:http://makarapeak.org/ Makara Peak]], [[link:http://doc.govt.nz/ DOC]], [[link:http://www.vorb.org.nz VORB]], and blogs such as [[link:http://www.bushloveracing.com/ Bush Love Racing]] and [[link:http://oli-roadworks.blogspot.com/ Oli]], etc.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe links would need to be organized in some way â€“ perhaps by region (though some are national), and/or by category (Councils, Blogs, Forums, Mountain Bike Parks, etc).',23,'open','2009-05-20 16:55:43','2009-05-20 16:56:23','new'),(43,'feature','Extend Tracks tweets','It would be helpful if the Tracks tweets included more types of changes to the site. That is, updates to Features/Problems, comments on Features/Problems, editing of tracks, and maybe other site changes too.',23,'open','2009-05-21 20:05:50','2009-06-03 12:40:32','accepted'),(44,'problem','KML Overlays Don\'t display in IE7','I hate to bring up an IE bug. But the kml overlay track lines are not showing up in IE7. Probably due to this issue...http://code.google.com/apis/maps/documentation/#XHTML_and_VML\r\n\r\nHopefully its an easy fix',59,'closed','2009-06-01 20:19:25','2009-08-07 07:26:36','implemented'),(45,'feature','Improve multiple tracks per map view','This is a continuation of adding multiple tracks per map, see [[link:tracks.org.nz/features/11 here]] for full detail.',1,'open','2009-06-03 12:02:42','2009-06-03 12:37:43','accepted'),(46,'feature','Password reset','Password reset functionality is missing!',1,'closed','2009-06-03 15:21:45','2009-06-11 06:55:45','implemented'),(47,'problem','Can\'t edit track maps','When editing a track the map is broken...',1,'closed','2009-06-04 13:24:55','2009-06-06 01:36:43','implemented'),(48,'problem','Track infoWindows are too wide','When a user clicks on a track on the map, an infoWindow pops up to display a brief overview of the selected track.  If the overview text is more than a few words long, then the infoWindow is too wide.  For example: [[track:25]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nA potential solution is to assign a width to the infoDescription DIV, as was done in the [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/multitracks4/css/style.css CSS for the multi-track examples]].',23,'closed','2009-06-10 13:16:00','2009-06-14 05:02:00','implemented'),(49,'problem','Bullet points don\'t work in description fields','Using the new bullet point tag breaks the indentation of the track description text.  That is, description text that is tagged as a bullet point is left-aligned with the section labels, rather than being indented like the rest of the description text.',23,'closed','2009-06-14 20:30:27','2009-08-06 14:47:59','implemented'),(50,'problem','Nested tags don\'t work','Nested formatting tags tend to get confused and don\'t work as expected.\r\n[[para]]\r\nFor example, try adding bullet point tags around the links in the Access section of the [[link:http://tracks.org.nz/area/show/15 Akatarawa Forest]] overview.  Similarly, the Stage 4 heading in the description of [[track:228]] looks OK, but actually requires multiple tags to achieve the desired affect, rather than simply nesting the bold and track tags.',23,'closed','2009-06-14 20:36:32','2009-08-07 07:35:24','implemented'),(51,'problem','Track modified timestamp doesn\'t capture some events','There are some track change events that are not captured by the \"Last modified\" timestamp.  For example: adding an \"Also known as\", and changing the list of \"Adjacent Tracks\".',23,'closed','2009-06-23 08:25:53','2009-08-07 07:28:10','implemented'),(52,'feature','Regional map on the Home page.','With the expansion of Tracks to cover multiple regions, it might be helpful to put a regional map on the Home page.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe straightforward version of this map could have a map of NZ with a marker at the centre of each region.  That is, much like the current region maps, which have a marker for each area within that region.\r\n[[para]]\r\nA more sophisticated map could have the country divided into regions using something like the [[link:http://koordinates.com/layer/197-nz-regional-councils-2008/ Regional Council boundary data]].  However, the Regional Councils might be a bit big, so perhaps some custom regional definition would be more appropriate?\r\n[[para]]\r\nTaking this idea a step further, it should be possible to make the map interactive, doing things like highlighting a region on mouseover event and popping up an information window with a description of, and link to, that region when it is clicked.\r\n[[para]]\r\nMore broadly, this raises the question of how to define regions?  For example, instead of Christchurch being a region, should it be an area within the Canterbury region; similarly, should Queenstown be an area within the Otago region?  Or would some other categorization be more appropriate?',23,'closed','2009-06-29 21:09:17','2009-09-06 03:43:05','implemented'),(53,'problem','Javascript error if Overview field contains a linefeed','If the \"Overview\" field of a track contains a linefeed, then the browser raises a Javascript error and fails to draw the track on the map.  Firefox reports the error message: \"unterminated string literal\".\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis error affects that track and all others that list it as an adjacent track.  Presumably this is because the \"Overview\" field is used to populate the infowindow for all tracks shown on a map, whether it is the current track or an adjacent track.',23,'closed','2009-07-02 20:29:32','2009-08-07 07:27:44','implemented'),(54,'feature','Calculate track length automatically','It would be very helpful for Tracks to calculate the track length automatically, rather than it being entered manually by the user.\r\n[[para]]\r\nCalculating the track length automatically would also help to ensure consistency between the displayed length and the distance shown on altitude charts.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe following snippet of Javascript is the basis for a track length function - it calculates the distance between two pairs of coordinates. The calculation should be done on the server side rather than by the client, so this code needs to be translated into some other language.\r\n[[para]]\r\n// Calculate length, in km, along Great Circle between two points[[br]]\r\n//  on the Earth\'s surface, using the \'Spherical law of cosines\'.[[br]]\r\n// Derived from http://www.movable-type.co.uk/scripts/latlong.html[[br]]\r\nvar EarthRadius = 6369; // Earth\'s radius (at NZ), in km[[br]]\r\nvar lat1R = lat1.toRad();  // Convert degree coordinates to radians[[br]]\r\nvar lon1R = lon1.toRad();[[br]]\r\nvar lat2R = lat2.toRad();[[br]]\r\nvar lon2R = lon2.toRad();[[br]]\r\nvar Distance = Math.acos(Math.sin(lat1) * Math.sin(lat2)[[br]]\r\n+ Math.cos(lat1) * Math.cos(lat2)[[br]]\r\n* Math.cos(lon2 - lon1)) * EarthRadius;[[br]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe kml is already parsed in the map data encoding process, including dealing with multiple track sections, so it should be fairly straightforward to iterate over all the coordinates and then update the length field in the database.\r\n[[para]]\r\nGiven that a path consisting of line segments is always shorter than the real track, it would also be good to include a field for adjusting the calculated length.  A typical adjustment would be in the range 1% to 5%, depending on how convoluted the real track is, how hilly it is (which could add 1% to the length), and how much detail is included in the kml data.',23,'closed','2009-07-07 12:26:02','2009-08-08 04:49:22','implemented'),(55,'feature','Print format: 1-2 pages','Hi guys\r\n\r\nI often use the description and map to help navigate to riding spots in the Welly region that I haven\'t been to.\r\n\r\nI think it would be a valuable feature if you were able to print out the track description textbox and the map.\r\n\r\nAt the moment the print command will print out about 5-7 pages per track. It starts out with the navigator bar, then the updates then the track description. The map doesn\'t print at all.\r\n\r\nI think a simple 1-2 page print set up would be awesome.\r\n\r\nHey thanks for this site. It is brilliant!',92,'closed','2009-07-11 15:15:50','2009-09-13 08:19:56','new'),(56,'feature','Routes','Allow routes to be specified (a set of tracks with a given riding order), and viewable in the GIS.\r\n\r\nThis would be useful for specifying race courses (e.g PNP), or itineraries (e.g. \'beginners day out\'), or favourite rides.\r\n\r\nAlso, would be neat to then embed them in other web sites.\r\n\r\nDunno if this is already covered?',129,'open','2009-07-22 14:14:04','2009-08-06 16:29:15','accepted'),(57,'problem','Some RSS feeds are broken','Some of the RSS feed links just go to an error page â€“ for example, the [[link:http://tracks.org.nz/region/rss/1 Wellington RSS feed]].',23,'closed','2009-07-23 12:10:19','2009-08-07 07:28:29','implemented'),(58,'feature','Allow a hand-drawn track path','It would be useful in the absence of real gps data to allow a hand drawn path to be added.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis could be useful in some situations, especially as a starter for new tracks. Maybe it could be identified as \"not from gps data\", or something.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIn the bad old days before the file upload option I had a simple google map line drawing script, will see if I can find it...',1,'open','2009-08-06 13:00:37','2009-08-06 13:03:36','accepted'),(59,'problem','Scrolling over map grabs scroll event','When you scroll the page down with mouse wheel (or track pad) and the map scrolls under the pointer, the scroll events are captured by the map and it shrinks or grows. This is surprisingly annoying! Investigate whether this can be turned off for the map.',1,'closed','2009-08-06 17:47:16','2009-08-07 07:27:30','implemented'),(60,'problem','Broken maps on some edit pages','Caused by recent map stream-lining, fix coming soon.',1,'closed','2009-08-07 03:14:58','2009-08-07 07:26:18','implemented'),(61,'problem','Map sliders?','I have lost the map sliders from my map views. I am unable to zoom into where I wish to mark my trails.',126,'open','2009-08-11 08:08:44','2009-08-11 08:08:44','new'),(62,'problem','Images no longer fit in the description fields','The formatting of the content column appears to have changed, so images that used to fit nicely within the description fields are now forced to the right and go outside the column\'s border. This seems to be at least partially due to additional white space to the left of the content labels.\r\nFor example: [[track:32]].',23,'closed','2009-08-13 14:03:19','2009-08-18 09:34:17','implemented'),(63,'problem','Last modified by fails in some circumstances','A couple of cases where \'last modified by\' fails:[[br]]\r\n1. I updated the list of Adjacent Tracks for [[track:75]], but the updated date didn\'t change.[[br]]\r\n2. I uploaded a new kml to [[track:247]] and the updated date changed correctly, but the username didn\'t change.',23,'closed','2009-08-13 14:07:30','2009-08-20 04:56:59','implemented'),(64,'feature','Revert to automatic track length calculation','Having selected the option to manually enter a track\'s length, there doesn\'t seem to be a facility to revert to having the track length calculated automatically.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIn going back to automatic track length calculation, it would be helpful if the database stored the manually entered length so that it isn\'t lost.',23,'open','2009-08-26 19:59:51','2009-09-08 13:01:46','accepted'),(65,'problem','\'Reset map view\' for regions is broken','Clicking a region\'s \'Reset map view\' doesn\'t reset the map view.',23,'closed','2009-09-05 10:10:48','2009-09-07 06:27:12','implemented'),(66,'feature','Add tooltips to region polygons','It would be really nice to have tooltips when hovering over the main page region polygons.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis is a left-over item from [[feature:52]].',1,'open','2009-09-06 03:38:05','2009-09-06 03:38:16','accepted'),(67,'feature','Add snap-to for creating/editing region shapes','It would be nice if the region polygons would (optionally) snap-to adjacent regions.\r\n[[para]]\r\nRefer to [[feature:52]] for some notes on this.\r\n',1,'open','2009-09-06 03:40:19','2009-09-06 03:40:37','accepted'),(68,'feature','Filter Regions by Activity','Would be good to be able to toggle on/off a filter to view only MTB tracks (e.g. exclude foot only tracks).',92,'open','2009-09-06 16:07:04','2009-09-07 11:29:47','accepted'),(69,'feature','Make embedded videos larger','Currently the embedded videos are quite small, at 320x240 pixels.  Could the videos be a bit bigger?\r\n[[para]]\r\nFor example, the standard YouTube size of 480x385 pixels should fit.',23,'closed','2009-09-08 20:22:28','2009-09-27 06:38:36','implemented'),(70,'feature','Extend video embedding to include other formats','Currently the video embedding allows for YouTube and Vorb videos.  It would be very useful to extend the feaure to include other media formats.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIn particular, the Vimeo service is commonly used and includes an embedding facility.  For example: I\'d like to add this [[link:http://www.vimeo.com/6691202 Koru]] video, along with others that the author will add shortly.',23,'closed','2009-09-24 17:52:40','2009-09-27 06:38:20','implemented'),(71,'problem','Track report submission doesn\'t appear to work','When making a track report, clicking the \'Save report\' button doesn\'t appear to work - ie. it seems to do nothing. The track report is actually saved, but the text box doesn\'t close and the submitted report isn\'t shown until the page is refreshed.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe \'Update report\' button works fine, after editing a track report.',23,'closed','2009-09-27 19:19:12','2009-10-01 06:19:36','implemented'),(72,'feature','Use (Official?)Track Gradings','Currently the tracks are graded from Beginner, Easy, Intermediate and all the way to extreme.\r\n\r\nIs there some description about what these gradings mean? \r\n\r\nFor example Mountain Bike New Zealand uses a 1-6 grading scheme to describe tracks.... and the CMBC MTB club has a 1-5 rating system (which is has fairly similiar descriptions...)\r\n\r\nCMBC Ride Grading:        \r\n \r\nGrade One:\r\nFairly flat, wide and smooth track and gravel roads. Suitable for all first time riders e.g. Hagley Park.\r\n\r\nGrade Two:\r\nGentle climbs and easily avoidable obstacles such as rocks and potholes. You couldn\'t ride it in your sleep but beginners will still enjoy these rides e.g. The Traverse Track, Victoria Park\r\n\r\nGrade Three:\r\nChallenging riding with steep slopes and/or tricky obstacles possible on a narrow track with poor traction. Requires riding experience and some fitness e.g. Worsleys Track or VIctoria Park in the Eucalyptus trees\r\n\r\n\r\nGrade Four:\r\nKiller climbs, dangerous drop-offs, sharp corners. Some sections are easier and safer to walk.\r\n\r\n\r\nGrade Five:\r\nTrials skills essential to clear huge obstacles and/or frictionless surfaces. Only a handful of riders will enjoy these rides. E.g. Pylon Track â€“ Hanmer Springs. \r\n \r\n \r\n',162,'open','2009-09-28 22:28:53','2009-09-28 22:38:49','new'),(73,'problem','AKA failed','I attempted to add an AKA for [[track:97]]. However, clicking the \"New\" link resulted in the process crashing spectacularly.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe error message page was headed by \"NameError in Track_aka#new\".  The error message continued with \"Showing app/views/shared/_nav_current.html.erb where line #1 raised:  undefined local variable or method \'nav_level\' for #<ActionView::Base:0xb7ce03d0>\", etc.',23,'open','2009-10-17 13:32:40','2009-10-17 13:32:40','new'),(74,'feature','Automatically populate Adjacent Tracks list','Currently the Adjacent Tracks list needs to be manually populated. It would be helpful if the list was populated automatically when a track is created or a map\'s view is updated.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt should still be possible to add Adjacent Tracks manually. For example, adding a track that is just outside the map view, but which is a natural extension of the current track. Manually removing automatically added tracks should also be possible (though perhaps hidden rather than removed â€“ see Status comment below).\r\n[[para]]\r\nThere\'s a limit to the number of tracks that can be displayed on the map, so there would need to be a mechanism for limiting the number of automatically added adjacent tracks â€“ maybe based on the adjacent track\'s distance from the current track?  This distance parameter should be a user input. An additional rule to limit the number of tracks would be to restrict automatically added tracks to only those within the current\'s tracks area (perhaps as a user-selectable option).\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt would be a computationally intensive task determining whether any part of any track is visible within the map view of the current track.  However, shortcuts are possible â€“ for example, for each track store its north, south, east, and west bounds (recalculated whenever a track\'s kml file changes) then determine if the rectangle defined by those bounds overlaps the rectangle defined by the bounds of the current track (extended by a margin to allow for nearby tracks that may fall just inside or outside the map view). There are standard procedures for determining if rectangles overlap. \r\n[[para]]\r\nPerhaps mark each adjacent track in the list to indicate its status (visible when editing the list): ie. automatically added and displayed; automatically added but manually hidden; and manually added.',23,'open','2009-12-08 07:29:23','2010-01-15 10:26:15','accepted'),(75,'feature','Automatically show adjacent tracks as the map view changes','An extension of [[feature:0074]] would be to automatically update the tracks displayed on the map when the user changes the map view (scrolls or zooms).  \r\n[[para]]\r\nThis feature would be especially useful for planning an excursion that starts on one track and then progresses to others.[[para]]\r\nThis feature is subject to the same limitations as [[feature:0074]] with regard to the number of tracks that the map can display before it becomes too sluggish. Similar rules could be applied for limiting the number of tracks displayed.',23,'open','2009-12-08 07:34:28','2009-12-08 07:34:28','new'),(76,'feature','Filter by access','As tracks grows there are more \'foot access only\' tracks. It\'d be great for riders if we could filter by access. ie filtering out \'foot only\'. Equally walkers might want to filter out \'bike only\'. Ideally the filter could be set in a users profile.',59,'closed','2010-01-12 15:18:14','2010-01-14 14:57:45','new'),(77,'problem','Use https for sensitive information','Use https protocol when submitting any sensitive data, this is currently only passwords I think.',1,'open','2010-01-15 10:28:13','2010-01-15 10:28:24','accepted'),(78,'feature','Auto-fit map view to uploaded kml','Currently when a track is created the Google Map inherits the view of the track\'s area. This view is usually too broad for a specific track.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt would be better if, when the track\'s kml is uploaded, the map view were to automatically zoom to, and centre on, the track. Such functionality would be much like the \"Auto-fit region\" button that is available when editing a region\'s shape. Perhaps it would be useful to have an \"Auto-fit track\" button, in addition to automatically fitting the view to the kml when it is uploaded?\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt should still be possible to manually adjust the map\'s view, as per the current functionality. If a new kml is uploaded, the view should stay unchanged if it had been manually set, otherwise the view should be automatically updated to fit the new kml.',23,'open','2010-01-18 12:21:01','2010-01-18 12:21:01','new'),(79,'feature','Enable gpx file download','In addition to being able to download a track\'s kml file, it would be useful to provide a gpx file to download. The gpx could then be uploaded directly to a GPS unit, whereas the kml file needs to be converted first.',23,'open','2010-01-18 12:50:44','2010-01-18 12:50:44','new'),(80,'feature','Puke Ariki Track','This track runs from Dry Creek to Cornish and is made up of a number of different shorter tacks. Is it possible to show these all together to make it easier to plan',193,'closed','2010-01-19 21:11:06','2010-01-24 20:28:53','new'),(81,'feature','Display milestones on a track','Sites like [[link:http://www.mapmyride.com/ride/new-zealand/wellington/395897558304 mapmyride]] show milestones when plotting a track on the map. It would be useful for Tracks to display milestones.\r\n[[para]]\r\nI\'ve prepared a couple of examples, to see how this might work.  The first example, [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/milestones/milestones-koru.html Koru]], is a fairly short track. The second example, [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/milestones/milestones-skyline.html Skyline]], uses the same code to display milestones on a longer track.',23,'open','2010-01-21 19:13:03','2010-01-21 19:14:46','new'),(82,'feature','Full screen map','Sometimes it would be useful to have a larger map. One way to achieve this is to have the map toggle between normal size and full screen, as in this [[link:http://iod.freehostia.com/tracks/fullscreen/fullscreen.html full screen map example]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe function doesn\'t always play nice with the \"Earth 3D\" map type, but otherwise it is simple to set up.',23,'open','2010-01-24 12:41:25','2010-01-24 12:41:51','new'),(83,'problem','Search ','If I search for \"coppermine\" in the site search. No results are returned. Yet if I use google to do \"site:tracks.org.nz coppermine\" I get the \"Coppermine Loop\" track as the first result,\r\n\r\nSimilarly if I search for boobies (haha) in the site I don\'t get the track boobies as the top result. Yet the track boobies is the top result if I google \"site:tracks.org.nz boobies\".\r\n\r\nAre track titles not being indexed?\r\n\r\nI tried a few other searches and get similar results.',59,'open','2010-02-02 22:42:31','2010-02-02 22:42:31','new'),(84,'feature','Credit where it is due','How about a new field to credit the efforts of the track builders?\r\n\r\nCould just encourage people to put credits in the \'other notes\' section.\r\n\r\nThere are lots of deserving people deserving public recognition for their efforts.\r\n\r\nCheers\r\n\r\nJay',92,'open','2010-03-21 21:11:56','2010-03-21 21:11:56','new'),(85,'feature','New track: add note re upload path','When you are adding a new track there is no \"upload path\" link. This appears once you have saved it. Maybe add a note to explain this?',1,'open','2010-03-23 09:38:47','2010-03-23 09:38:47','new'),(86,'feature','Adopt a track','Add a couple of fields (or something) so that each track can have a \"go to\" person or group that can be contacted/notified about a particular track.',1,'open','2010-04-13 05:59:56','2010-04-13 05:59:56','new'),(87,'problem','reports','Hi\r\n\r\nHow do I delete a report that was created if no longer relevant?\r\n\r\nRegards\r\n\r\nFrank ',165,'open','2010-04-18 19:58:05','2010-05-06 13:44:34','accepted'),(88,'feature','Aggregate KML files by area','Love this site thx. I can search for the linked kml files in Google Maps on my GPS enabled Blackberry mobile device & use this to guide me to new tracks. I just wish there were single kml files to show all the tracks in a single area, e.g. Makara Peak, Wrights Hill, etc.\r\n\r\nAs these areas already have their own page & a list of corresponding tracks, I\'m hoping it\'s possible to automate the creation of a combined kml file for the relevant tracks & link to this from the area page.\r\n',257,'open','2010-05-10 15:03:51','2010-05-10 15:03:51','new');
