INSERT INTO `specials` VALUES (1,'Index','[[h2:Welcome to Tracks!]]\r\n[[bold:[[italic:Note:]]]] [[italic:we have just changed our hosting company so hopefully the site will be more stable now.]]\r\n[[para]]\r\n[[bold:Tracks]] is an exploration into a track guide/status based primarily around mountain biking and trail running in New Zealand. It was initially focused on the tracks around [[region:1]]\'s many hills and green belts. We have recently expanded to look into all corners of New Zealand, stay tuned.\r\n[[map]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nAnyone can use the info on [[bold:Tracks]]. [[link:www.tracks.org.nz/account/signup Sign up]] to contribute. Everything here is [[link:tracks.org.nz/policy#license free]] and created/edited by users for users. [[link:www.tracks.org.nz/account/login Sign in]] to make changes to your favourite tracks. Got a track, area or region that\'s not listed here, [[link:tracks.org.nz/contact contact us]] to become a content creator.\r\n[[para]]\r\nSee the [[link:tracks.org.nz/about About]] for the latest site innovations and updates.\r\n'),(2,'About','[[bold:Tracks]] started out in mid 2005 as an exploration into creating an online resource around mountain biking in [[region:1]]. The scope was changed to include walking tracks when we started running, doing family walks etc. [[region:1]] is a great city for doing this with a large and varied track network.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThere are various existing track resources but they mostly try to cover all of New Zealand which means only detail on a few choice tracks or they are erratic with their coverage. So far none attempt to maintain data on current track status etc. We also wanted to have a really fine-grained guide to be able to cover lots of tracks in a small area, even if they may only be short connectors.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIn Feb 2009 [[bold:Tracks]] was extended to potentially cover all of New Zealand. Track info will be slowly added by interested locals we hope.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt is very likely that progress will be slow and erratic as life is always busy. You are welcome to [[link:tracks.org.nz/account/login contribute]].\r\n\r\n[[h1:Latest back-end updates]]\r\n\r\nThe intent of this section is to provide info on recent updates, prove that there is progress, and maybe to keep us focused on making things better!\r\n\r\n[[h2:Release 51, 13 October 2009]]\r\n[[bullet:[[feature:36]] New simple printer-friendly track pages]]\r\n[[bullet:[[feature:34]] Search result links now open in same window]]\r\n\r\n[[h2:Release 50 7 October 2009]]\r\n[[bullet:Fixed tricky bug that caused home page maps and all region view/edit maps to break.]]\r\n\r\n[[h2:Release 49, 29 Sept 2009]]\r\n[[bullet:[[feature:71]] Rolled-back the user settable video size as it was causing problems, videos are still larger though.]]\r\n\r\n[[h2:Release 48, 26 Sept 2009]]\r\n[[bullet:[[feature:69]] Made the default video size larger. Also added user default setting.]]\r\n[[bullet:[[feature:70]] Add Vimeo media option, \\[\\[media:vimeo:ref\\]\\] ]]\r\n[[bullet:Sorted out proper deploy using Capistrano]]\r\n\r\n(full change history can be found [[link:http://tracks.org.nz/history.txt here]])'),(3,'Contact','This website is hopefully a collaborative effort. However if you have a problem or want to do something that is not obviously available then send email to [[bold:info@tracks.org.nz]]'),(5,'Policy','At this stage there are really very few terms and conditions. You get what you see, you edit what you want, and hopefully it may be useful to you or someone else.\r\n[[para]]\r\nAbout the only thing we will promise is that any personal data you may submit on sign-up (e.g. email) will not be used for nefarious purposes. A-la Google\'s \"don\'t be evil\" sentiment.\r\n[[h1:License]]\r\n[[bold:Tracks]] is covered under a [[italic:Creative Commons Attribution Share Alike]] license.  Unless otherwise noted all content may be reused as per the terms of this license. A summary of this license is reproduced here:\r\n[[para]]\r\n[[image:http://tracks.org.nz/images/misc/88x31.png:::]] [[italic:[[bold:Attribution Share Alike]]]]\r\n[[para]]\r\n\"[[italic:This license lets others remix, tweak, and build upon your work even for commercial reasons, as long as they credit you and license their new creations under the identical terms. This license is often compared to open source software licenses. All new works based on yours will carry the same license, so any derivatives will also allow commercial use.]]\"\r\n[[para]]\r\nPlease refer to [[link:http://creativecommons.org/about/licenses Creative Commons]] for full detail.\r\n[[para]]\r\nAll other parts of [[bold:Tracks]] unless specifically noted otherwise remain the property of [[link:http://www.cheekymonkey.co.nz Cheeky Monkey]]. Please [[link:tracks.org.nz/contact contact]] us if you require further info on this.');
