INSERT INTO `track_reports` VALUES (1,23,1,'Clean and dry. Recent rain had not made much impact.','2004-11-01 00:00:00','2004-11-01 00:00:00'),(2,24,1,'There is a tree down at the first corner.','2004-11-01 00:00:00','2004-11-01 00:00:00'),(3,23,1,'Foo.','2005-10-09 00:00:00','2005-10-09 00:00:00'),(4,33,1,'Fancy new signs and styles have been installed at every intersection and gate.','2005-10-15 00:00:00','2005-10-15 00:00:00'),(5,16,1,'A few puddles still to dry out, could do with some draining.','2005-10-15 00:00:00','2005-10-15 00:00:00'),(6,8,1,'On the difficult section there is water running off the hill and then following the track which is creating quite a bog.','2005-10-15 00:00:00','2005-10-15 00:00:00'),(7,29,1,'A few bad bogs in the middle still.','2005-10-15 00:00:00','2005-10-15 00:00:00'),(8,25,1,'Dry. The big bogs near the glade have nearly gone.','2005-11-01 12:30:00','2005-11-01 12:30:00'),(9,24,1,'Primo! Some trail pixies have been filling the small bogs with rocks and a few lumps have been shaved. Nice lines.','2005-11-01 12:30:00','2005-11-01 12:30:00'),(10,27,1,'Track is getting slightly overgrown in parts. Also some ruts starting to form. Very dry though.','2005-11-01 12:30:00','2005-11-01 12:30:00'),(11,11,1,'Some corners and lumpy sections have been smoothed.','2005-11-02 12:30:00','2005-11-02 12:30:00'),(12,5,1,'The jump just before the picnic table has been tickled up and a nana line has been added.','2005-11-02 12:30:00','2005-11-02 12:30:00'),(13,7,1,'New boardwalk section seems like overkill right now, but I think it will prove it\'s worth come winter. The last 2 metres do not have mesh on and will get slippery with rain. Also watch your speed exiting as the sharp left hander comes up much faster now.','2005-11-02 12:30:00','2005-11-02 12:30:00'),(14,7,1,'Mesh covers entire boardwalk now.','2005-11-05 10:00:00','2005-11-05 10:00:00'),(15,10,1,'Nice and dry, ruts are present but are not getting worse.','2005-11-05 10:00:00','2005-11-05 10:00:00'),(16,3,1,'Several loose dry patches of deep gravel from recent work parties.','2005-11-05 10:00:00','2005-11-05 10:00:00'),(17,14,1,'Very dry. Cleaned without a dab. The only dodgy bits are some of the upper sections with loose gravel.','2005-11-20 10:30:00','2005-11-20 10:30:00'),(18,30,1,'Very dry which is making the steeper parts more technical than when it\'s a little damp, Parade Drop particularly.','2006-01-07 11:00:00','2006-01-07 11:00:00'),(19,29,1,'Starting to get overgrown with grass.','2006-01-07 11:00:00','2006-01-07 11:00:00'),(20,28,1,'A few more jumps have appeared, they are all on open track and have alternate easy lines. Also a pine tree has blown over at the bottom, but there is just enough room to ride on the left.','2006-01-07 11:00:00','2006-01-07 11:00:00'),(21,24,1,'Pulled a few weeds and cleared some over-hanging branches. Track is still narrow with the recent spring growth.','2006-01-08 10:30:00','2006-01-08 10:30:00'),(22,28,1,'Made the track around the fallen tree obvious by digging a ramp and removing most of the dead branches in the way.','2006-01-08 10:30:00','2006-01-08 10:30:00'),(23,35,1,'A large tree is down near the top just on the edge of the thick bush. You can climb over it but it\'s a bit of a hassle, definitely a chainsaw job to remove.','2006-01-10 12:30:00','2006-01-10 12:30:00'),(24,35,1,'The fallen tree has been removed, in fact I heard is was removed the day after the previous note.','2006-01-21 11:00:00','2006-01-21 11:00:00'),(25,16,1,'Did this from [[track:1]] end, what\'s with the \"wrong way\" sign? It\'s better this way, more down. Anyway the gorse is closing in and rather sharp!','2006-02-04 11:00:00','2006-02-04 11:00:00'),(26,29,1,'Foliage is closing in a bit.','2006-02-04 11:00:00','2006-02-04 11:00:00'),(27,25,1,'Supposedly there is a months worth of tree work starting on the 7th.','2006-02-04 11:00:00','2006-02-04 11:00:00'),(28,24,1,'A little greasy after overnight rain, should dry off quickly with forecast Southerlies.','2006-02-04 11:00:00','2006-02-04 11:00:00'),(29,35,1,'Bottom exit is blocked by the park renovations. You can go up the bulldozer track and back down to the regular exit Eastern exit by the child care centre.','2006-02-05 11:00:00','2006-02-05 11:00:00'),(30,24,1,'Sweet! Track is groomed and flowing, particularly the bottom half.','2006-02-20 12:30:00','2006-02-20 12:30:00'),(31,28,1,'No sign of the tree felling yet.','2006-02-20 12:30:00','2006-02-20 12:30:00'),(32,32,1,'The huge mob of sheep have been moved from the top paddock and most of the sheep shit has gone, nice.','2006-02-24 12:30:00','2006-02-24 12:30:00'),(33,35,1,'Still tricky to exit the lower end with all the digging going on. When you exit the single track carry on straight across the track up the short rise, and follow your nose to the steep downhill back to the original track across the top of the park.','2006-02-24 12:30:00','2006-02-24 12:30:00'),(34,34,1,'The bottom tighest section is a bit rutted and skidded. I guess the skid-kids and shuttle bunnies have discovered this track.','2006-02-25 11:30:00','2006-02-25 11:30:00'),(35,30,1,'Sweet! A little narrow with re-growth but the surface is in good nick.','2006-02-25 11:30:00','2006-02-25 11:30:00'),(36,29,1,'Bottom quarter seems to be pruned back. Still a bit leafy further up. Super dry though.','2006-03-15 16:45:00','2006-03-15 16:45:00'),(37,25,1,'No sign of the supposed tree work yet...','2006-03-15 16:45:00','2006-03-15 16:45:00'),(38,24,1,'Very dry. Some loose gravelly sections and a few brakey bumps where steep.','2006-03-15 16:45:00','2006-03-15 16:45:00'),(39,32,1,'Sheep are back in the top paddock, though not nearly as many as a few weeks ago.','2006-03-18 10:45:00','2006-03-18 10:45:00'),(40,5,1,'The new esses near the top are holding out ok. I still think they will be terrible in the wet.','2006-03-18 10:45:00','2006-03-18 10:45:00'),(41,7,1,'The hole at the end of the curvy boardwalk has got so bad that someone has put a hefty plank in it. This is a dodgy obstacle which will make people ride beside it, maybe that was the intention.','2006-03-18 10:45:00','2006-03-18 10:45:00'),(42,44,1,'Off piste! Still a pine needle scramble. Tunnelling required at the top and just before tower 9. I plan to get in there soon and open up some of it, that gorse is wicked.','2006-03-19 10:30:00','2006-03-19 10:30:00'),(43,45,1,'Plenty of knee-high gorse growing centre of track and from the sides.','2006-03-19 10:30:00','2006-03-19 10:30:00'),(44,13,1,'Loose. The last 2 weeks without rain have seen this track cut up pretty bad. Still all ridable but ball-bearing loose in places.','2006-03-19 10:30:00','2006-03-19 10:30:00'),(45,44,1,'The bottom 25 metre section has had the gorse and nasties cleared. The final drop to the transmission tower still needs to be walked though and it may stay this way for a while as it hides the exit to the track nicely.','2006-03-20 12:00:00','2006-03-20 12:00:00'),(46,44,1,'Started marking out the main downhill section under the pines. Kicked a path through the pine needles and trimmed low branches that might skewer a rider. Track goes most of the way to the top and needs plenty of riding to smooth things out. Some corners are quite tight.','2006-03-25 10:30:00','2006-03-25 10:30:00'),(47,45,1,'I followed this 4wd track right through to the end at tower 8. Nice track, fair gradient with think layer of pine needles. Lots of opportunies for deviations through the pines and at one point the track touches farmland with views across to the tracks up British Peak and the trail along the creek at the bottom.','2006-03-26 10:30:00','2006-03-26 10:30:00'),(48,44,1,'Walked the final bit to the top, it\'s almost through! Still 25 metres of gorse to trim and there is a fence that probably shouldn\'t be chopped. Added some really fun curvy bits and bedded down some other lines. There are a couple of corners that are still too sharp. Also some slight uphill bits are too technical, I\'m sure these can re re-routed to flow downhill or at least level.','2006-03-26 10:30:00','2006-03-26 10:30:00'),(49,32,1,'Lots of goats on the track near the top of [[track:33]], very smelly!','2006-04-01 10:00:00','2006-04-01 10:00:00'),(50,44,1,'Track is quite passible now. Still have to hike through the gorse at the top. A few lines and corners mid-way down need some loving but it\'s getting some good flow.','2006-04-01 10:00:00','2006-04-01 10:00:00'),(51,44,1,'Other people are using the track! The top barbed wire on the fence has been removed which makes it much easier to climb over.','2006-04-12 13:30:00','2006-04-12 13:30:00'),(52,3,1,'Puddles are starting to form in the usual winter places.','2006-04-12 13:30:00','2006-04-12 13:30:00'),(53,5,1,'Lots of wet greasy bits.','2006-04-12 13:30:00','2006-04-12 13:30:00'),(54,22,1,'Lots of wet greasy bits and puddles.','2006-04-12 13:30:00','2006-04-12 13:30:00'),(55,29,1,'Lots of wet greasy bits. The winter puddles are starting to form. Foliage is also getting pretty close.','2006-04-12 13:30:00','2006-04-12 13:30:00'),(56,32,1,'Busy busy! This track is getting really popular with the walkers.','2006-04-14 11:20:00','2006-04-14 11:20:00'),(57,11,1,'Nice and dry. A couple of rocky steps are getting tricky to clear.','2006-04-14 11:20:00','2006-04-14 11:20:00'),(58,5,1,'Sweet! Just the right amount of dampness to make it sticky but not wet (or muddy). It\'s that time of year though that this could change quickly with a good dump of rain.','2006-04-14 11:20:00','2006-04-14 11:20:00'),(59,22,1,'Slippery on the rocky sections, watch those big corners.','2006-04-14 11:20:00','2006-04-14 11:20:00'),(60,1,1,'Sticky but not wet.','2006-04-15 10:00:00','2006-04-15 10:00:00'),(61,9,1,'Grass has been cut to reveal the old line which is much easier to ride, the rut is not so severe.','2006-04-15 10:00:00','2006-04-15 10:00:00'),(62,32,1,'Lots of dogs (and their owners), this track is getting really popular with the general public.','2006-07-09 10:30:00','2006-07-09 10:30:00'),(63,23,1,'Excellent condition. Even with all the recent rain there are no bad ruts. A few slippery bits and wet patches, but no puddles or bogs that can\'t be avoided.','2006-06-25 10:30:00','2006-06-25 10:30:00'),(64,28,1,'Just a few wet patches. No ruts or bogs that can\'t be avoided, similar to the [[track:23]]. A couple of the larger puddles have had some trail-pixie work, new gravel and small drainage ditches mostly.','2006-06-25 10:30:00','2006-06-25 10:30:00'),(65,28,1,'More little jumps are appearing along the sides of the track.','2006-07-24 11:00:00','2006-07-24 11:00:00'),(66,25,1,'The usual winter wet patches appearing on the descent down from [[area:4]] to the glade. The clay channels can be a bit dodgy on the front wheel.','2006-07-24 11:00:00','2006-07-24 11:00:00'),(67,44,1,'Quite a lot of small windfall on the track, needs a tidy.','2006-07-17 13:15:00','2006-07-17 13:15:00'),(68,45,1,'lots of water in all shady bits but no mud.','2006-07-17 13:15:00','2006-07-17 13:15:00'),(69,24,1,'I drained lots of the bog puddles. Really needs some grubber work though to remove the little dams that form on the outside of the puddles. This track is always wet in winter and I would recommend not riding it at present.','2006-07-15 10:45:00','2006-07-15 10:45:00'),(70,35,1,'Mucky surface and some wet sections. Also a moderate sized makaracarpa tree down on the steepest section. It can be wriggled under but be careful coming down.','2006-07-17 13:15:00','2006-07-17 13:15:00'),(71,29,1,'Great job by the council or PD gang to trim the entire track. Some trimmings lying on the track but they have tidied up nicely. There are several big bos and sloppy bits that will need some attention soon. I drained a few by channeling the out, but long term cambers and proper drainage need to be added.','2006-07-09 10:30:00','2006-07-09 10:30:00'),(72,12,1,'A few boggy bits.','2006-07-09 10:30:00','2006-07-09 10:30:00'),(73,48,1,'Condition is good, probably because this is one of the least-used tracks in the park.','2006-07-09 10:30:00','2006-07-09 10:30:00'),(74,22,1,'After warnings on [[internet:2]] to stay off the south-facing and bushy tracks I was surprised how good the track was. Certainly slippery but not too muddy.','2006-07-09 10:30:00','2006-07-09 10:30:00'),(75,33,1,'Cattle are loose on the top part so look out for those \'land-mines\'.','2006-07-01 12:00:00','2006-07-01 12:00:00'),(76,29,1,'Some big bogs appearing. Council workers are currently trimming the growth. The top third has been trimmed and swept aside.','2006-07-01 12:00:00','2006-07-01 12:00:00'),(77,45,1,'Lots of water on all foliage make for a rather wet time. But there is no mud anywhere so this is a good winter option right now.','2006-07-01 12:00:00','2006-07-01 12:00:00'),(78,16,1,'Quite wet and slippery in the shady bits.','2006-07-01 12:00:00','2006-07-01 12:00:00'),(79,8,1,'Plenty of wet patches and a few boggy bits lower down. Overall not too bad considering the general condition of other tracks right now. There has been some water-bar fixing about half way down which will be good when the general wetness passes. The rampy sections have had the wire mesh repaired and the transition from the ramp to soil has been fixed for now - this is always going to be a problem (like [[track:7]]) as you come off the boards with brakes applied and they lock as you hit the dirt.','2006-07-01 12:00:00','2006-07-01 12:00:00'),(80,44,1,'Condition is good, probably because very few people use this track.','2006-07-01 12:00:00','2006-07-01 12:00:00'),(81,23,1,'Track condition is excellent. All wet bits are gone. Heinous, there is human feces, paper and general rubbish right at the top. I suspect from the guys building the new bomb-shelter thing just there.','2006-07-02 11:00:00','2006-07-02 11:00:00'),(82,25,1,'Quite a few big old pines have been removed from just inside the fence. This is part of the [[internet:4]] 500 year plan I guess, also helps secure the fence itself.','2006-07-02 11:00:00','2006-07-02 11:00:00'),(83,28,1,'The skid-kids have been installing new jumps. Nothing too dangerous although it\'s easy to carry a lot of speed, be careful. It can all be ridden around.','2006-07-02 11:00:00','2006-07-02 11:00:00'),(84,23,1,'Some wet patches in the central traverse section that will dry out quickly.','2006-07-24 11:00:00','2006-07-24 11:00:00'),(85,29,1,'Lots of very wet boggy bits, needs some serious draining. The pruned foliage is all cleared up and will not need attention until next year at least.','2006-07-24 11:00:00','2006-07-24 11:00:00'),(86,24,1,'A dry track for the first time this winter. A track-pixie has been working near the top. A few bogs worked over, but the main effort is the re-alligned entry at the top. There has been some chatter about getting gravel from the Council, will find out more.','2006-07-27 16:00:00','2006-07-27 16:00:00'),(87,9,1,'Grass is still very short and some gravel has been placed in the wheel ruts.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(88,10,1,'Freshly trimmed for the race in a couple of weeks time. The upper clay sections are quite slippery.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(89,4,1,'Quite wet. Towards the lower end there are some sketchy ruts forming.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(90,49,1,'Track is only partially complete. The lower end is sort of rideable for about 250 metres. Quite a bit of soft soil on top makes it rather greasy at present.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(91,12,1,'Very dry. Several little drains are working a treat.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(92,14,1,'Track is pretty good. Some greasy sections towards the top are a bit tricky as you can\'t slow down and have to commit yourself. The drop into the creek is pretty good now, the wheel-eating hole halfway has gone - I don\'t think it\'s the toughest section any more.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(93,1,1,'Very nice. All the gravel spread last week has had a bit of time to settle. There\'s still a few sections near the top that didn\'t get gravel but it\'s generally looking really good. Little water bars have been installed too. These look pretty solid so should hold up for quite a few years.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(94,7,1,'Surprisingly dry.','2006-07-30 11:00:00','2006-07-30 11:00:00'),(95,4,1,'Even wetter today, water running along the top quarter. Some work will be required soon towards the bottom to remove the ruts before summer.','2006-07-30 11:00:00','2006-07-30 11:00:00'),(96,2,1,'Quite wet and greasy in parts. The short straight steep section is marginal to ride with clay ruts digging out badly.','2006-07-30 11:00:00','2006-07-30 11:00:00'),(97,50,1,'Quite a bit of work has been done, mostly re-forming the bermed corners to provide better lines and remove ruts. It\'s still quite sticky.','2006-07-29 12:00:00','2006-07-29 12:00:00'),(98,22,1,'Quite dry. Clay sections still quite slippery but no big puddles like recently.','2006-07-30 11:00:00','2006-07-30 11:00:00'),(99,24,1,'3 metres of gravel has been delivered. A new top entry has been carved and will be filled with gravel soon. Further down the track is messy after just a small amount of rain last night, I guess it\'s still winter...','2006-07-31 12:15:00','2006-07-31 12:15:00'),(100,36,1,'Council workers have trimmed the over-hanging foliage to 2 bus-widths wide! It\'s clearer than I have seen it in the last 20 years. Not sure why they have done this.','2006-07-31 12:15:00','2006-07-31 12:15:00'),(101,42,1,'Greasy slippy slide.','2006-07-31 12:15:00','2006-07-31 12:15:00'),(102,25,1,'Lots of surface water.','2006-08-09 20:30:00','2006-08-09 20:30:00'),(103,31,1,'A few large bogs in the middle.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(104,29,1,'Boggy.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(105,4,1,'Quite wet. The ruts lower down are getting deeper and quite slippery.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(106,50,1,'Sticky but the new work is holding.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(107,5,1,'Ugly. The rutty sections are getting worse. I\'m not sure if this can be fixed easily, maybe some sort of rock armouring would work.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(108,22,1,'The rocky corners are very slippery right now.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(109,1,1,'The new gravel is just coping. I think it will hold out until the dry comes.','2006-08-05 11:30:00','2006-08-05 11:30:00'),(110,40,1,'Rode in the pouring rain and it was not too bad. Apart from the plentiful water, the folks painting the transmission towers seem to have driven enough to reveal a well-built track under the mud. The mud has washed away and it\'s pretty solid underneath.','2006-08-06 15:00:00','2006-08-06 15:00:00'),(111,32,1,'Extreme axle-deep bogs and cow shit. Yeah, that pretty much sums it up! The track is mostly ok heading south until you reach the gate just beyond the high-point where the cattle are doing unbelievable things to the track. It gets much better after the intersection with [[track:33]]. The track was already struggling in this cattle-section after vehicles ripped it up when they recently replaced a few fences, but add winter and cattle and you have a whole different experience. It\'s not even fun to walk. That said, see the entry [[blog:Wellington,0608061500]].','2006-08-06 15:00:00','2006-08-06 15:00:00'),(112,22,1,'The big smoothed-rock corners are quite slippery. Rear braking only!','2006-08-13 11:00:00','2006-08-13 11:00:00'),(113,1,1,'Gravel is really bedding down nicely.','2006-08-13 11:00:00','2006-08-13 11:00:00'),(114,4,1,'Dry which makes the ruts at the lower end seem quite tame.','2006-08-13 11:00:00','2006-08-13 11:00:00'),(115,9,1,'Grass is still short - it\'s not growing season. A lot of the rutty lines have been filled with gravel.','2006-08-13 11:00:00','2006-08-13 11:00:00'),(116,10,1,'The upper clay sections are still tricky.','2006-08-13 11:00:00','2006-08-13 11:00:00'),(117,23,1,'Lots of spray paint on the track marking out what looks like future water bars. Good idea.','2006-08-17 13:00:00','2006-08-17 13:00:00'),(118,24,1,'The new top sections of gravel still needs to bed in. The rest of the track is very soft.','2006-08-17 13:00:00','2006-08-17 13:00:00'),(119,35,1,'The big tree has been removed.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(120,44,1,'Quite a lot of windfall.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(121,11,1,'Track has been thoroughly trimmed. I suspect by the PD/Council guys as the tunnel-like sections have been fully opened up beyond what is really necessary.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(122,13,1,'Slippery but ok. Not much traffic during winter I guess.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(123,7,1,'The wire is coming off the boardwalk.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(124,22,1,'Trimmed but still very slippery.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(125,29,1,'Mucky. Some minor bog-draining is happening but it needs serious attention.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(126,34,1,'Sweet. The track has held up really well over winter.','2006-08-19 11:30:00','2006-08-19 11:30:00'),(127,23,1,'Lots of surface water running along the track, particularly in the middle traverse section. The spray paint is fading away...','2006-08-27 11:30:00','2006-08-27 11:30:00'),(128,35,1,'Someone has walked the track with a chainsaw and rounded off all the large stumps and logs that used to poke out onto the track. This means that the lines are straighter and will be faster. Be careful of other users.','2006-08-28 12:45:00','2006-08-28 12:45:00'),(129,30,1,'The normal entry is quite technical right now. The recent heavy rains have left lots of large loose boulders through the upper stream section. Once you meet the intersection of PD and Evil the rest of the track is pretty similar to usual.','2006-09-02 11:00:00','2006-09-02 11:00:00'),(130,29,1,'Much drier today. There are a few wet and soft patches. Shifted some gravel into a couple of bog holes.','2006-09-02 11:00:00','2006-09-02 11:00:00'),(131,44,1,'Re-cleared the line under the pines. Mostly pine needles and small windfall. Noticed some potential extensions...','2006-09-09 11:00:00','2006-09-09 11:00:00'),(132,45,1,'The gorse in the centre is starting to grow and a couple of sections are closing up. Still all ridable though.','2006-09-09 11:00:00','2006-09-09 11:00:00'),(133,13,1,'A bit greasy today. Also a sizable rut forming down the centre of the track. Quite a lot of stinging nettle along the bottom half at present.','2006-09-09 11:00:00','2006-09-09 11:00:00'),(134,22,1,'Plenty of lumpy sections still. The winter has left quite a bit of damage. I think it will get even wilder when [[track:53]] is completed.','2006-09-09 11:00:00','2006-09-09 11:00:00'),(135,53,1,'Wow, great progress from one work party. A solid 100m and a couple of bridges already. These are rather skinny though so I suspect they may be upgraded later as this is supposed to be an \'easy\' track.','2006-09-09 11:00:00','2006-09-09 11:00:00'),(136,31,1,'Quite a bit of water damage at the bottom. Still mostly ridable up though.','2006-09-06 12:30:00','2006-09-06 12:30:00'),(137,25,1,'Beware the greasy ruts when heading down to the glade.','2006-09-06 12:30:00','2006-09-06 12:30:00'),(138,24,1,'New gravel is setting nicely. About the top third is gravelled now.','2006-09-06 12:30:00','2006-09-06 12:30:00'),(139,36,1,'Still lots of loose plant bits on the track left from the recent clear-felling of the scrub.','2006-09-06 12:30:00','2006-09-06 12:30:00'),(140,27,1,'A few greasy patches. A modest sized tree is lying across the track just past the lower intersection with [[track:42]].','2006-09-06 12:30:00','2006-09-06 12:30:00'),(141,32,1,'There is a council sign warning about track conditions between top of [[track:33]] and [[track:40]]. Serious mud is still an issue.','2006-09-10 11:00:00','2006-09-10 11:00:00'),(142,16,1,'Scrub cleared to car width and lots of well made drainage ditches.','2006-09-10 11:00:00','2006-09-10 11:00:00'),(143,1,1,'Condition is excellent. The gravel has settled really well.','2006-09-10 11:00:00','2006-09-10 11:00:00'),(144,9,1,'Fantastic. Short grass, gravel in the old rut, and dry makes for good fun!','2006-09-10 11:00:00','2006-09-10 11:00:00'),(145,5,1,'Nicely dried out for the first time since winter. Don (The Don) was chipping away at some of the bad lines with a grubber.','2006-09-15 14:00:00','2006-09-15 14:00:00'),(146,5,1,'Don\'s handy work is good. He has attempted to re-route some of the bad rutty sections near the top. More work is required...','2006-09-16 11:00:00','2006-09-16 11:00:00'),(147,46,1,'Foliage is getting close, and the bear-pit temporary bridge is almost gone.','2006-09-17 14:00:00','2006-09-17 14:00:00'),(148,17,1,'Very dry. Windfall mostly cleared but still very heavy with pine needles. Also a modest tree down about halfway, can be easily ridden over - even though there are chainring marks, probably from the big suspension crowd.','2006-09-17 14:00:00','2006-09-17 14:00:00'),(149,41,1,'Nice and dry but a little overgrown. Some gorse in the middle 3rd. Also winter has left a nasty rut through the middle 3rd.','2006-09-17 14:00:00','2006-09-17 14:00:00'),(150,9,1,'Quite a big rut forming just before the entrance to [[track:10]].','2006-09-23 11:00:00','2006-09-23 11:00:00'),(151,57,1,'A bit lumpy from the winter and cattle combo.','2006-09-23 11:00:00','2006-09-23 11:00:00'),(152,24,1,'Dry. New gravel is getting a bit chewed.','2006-09-24 11:00:00','2006-09-24 11:00:00'),(153,23,1,'The spray paint for the possible water bars is all but gone, too bad.','2006-09-24 11:00:00','2006-09-24 11:00:00'),(154,39,1,'Dry, rocky and windswept - perfect!','2006-09-24 11:00:00','2006-09-24 11:00:00'),(155,23,1,'Track is currently being bulldozed. Bottom half has already had some rain and is sticky and setting fast. The top half is still under \'destruction\' and is very soft and loose. It will probably settle/set very quickly. However there does not appear to be any provision made for water run-off so it may cut up really fast.','2006-10-04 12:30:00','2006-10-04 12:30:00'),(156,40,1,'Surprising amount of water damage. Nothing that will stop you riding but it could catch you out coming down.','2006-10-07 11:00:00','2006-10-07 11:00:00'),(157,32,1,'Nearly dry enough to enjoy. The fence-fixing crew are busy at various points along the track making it messy.','2006-10-07 11:00:00','2006-10-07 11:00:00'),(158,49,1,'Currently about 25% ridable. Do not persevere with your bike beyond the tools, it\'s a real struggle!','2006-10-07 11:00:00','2006-10-07 11:00:00'),(159,1,1,'Fresh digging and trimming on the upper-most part.','2006-10-08 11:00:00','2006-10-08 11:00:00'),(160,2,1,'Lots of trimming and some patches of gravel laid on the end nearest to [[track:1]].','2006-10-08 11:00:00','2006-10-08 11:00:00'),(161,47,1,'Nicely trimmed, no gorse leaners.','2006-09-24 11:00:00','2006-09-24 11:00:00'),(162,27,1,'Last puddle now dry!','2006-09-24 11:00:00','2006-09-24 11:00:00'),(163,42,1,'Nice and dry. Spring growth is making the track narrow though.','2006-09-24 11:00:00','2006-09-24 11:00:00'),(164,23,1,'After all that rain the bottom section has cut up really badly. The recent bull-dozer work has made a hash of the track as the existing drainage ditches were obliterated.','2006-11-22 12:30:00','2006-11-22 12:30:00'),(165,24,1,'After all the recent rain the newly graveled parts are good but non-graveled sections are soft and boggy.','2006-11-22 12:30:00','2006-11-22 12:30:00'),(166,27,1,'General condition is good. The top is getting a little overgrown (which bodes badly for [[track:42]]), and there is a new tree down right at the bottom which can be easily negotiated. Some fool has tried to get a quad bike up the middle section which has helped keep the foliage at bay - minimal track damage though.','2006-11-22 12:30:00','2006-11-22 12:30:00'),(167,35,1,'Major macaracarpa tree down completely blocking the track. There is a just-walkable track forming to go down past it. Probably best avoided as a climb at present.','2006-11-25 11:00:00','2006-11-25 11:00:00'),(168,7,1,'Major rework of the big left-hand rocky corner. This should please the punters until [[track:53]] is completed.','2006-11-25 11:00:00','2006-11-25 11:00:00'),(169,50,1,'The only rocky dodgy section has been smoothed off, the track is definitely average now.','2006-11-25 11:00:00','2006-11-25 11:00:00'),(170,5,1,'Flash new corner to avoid rutty mess is good.','2006-11-25 11:00:00','2006-11-25 11:00:00'),(171,14,1,'Good condition. Top 10 metres is currently the most difficult section.','2006-11-25 11:00:00','2006-11-25 11:00:00'),(172,50,1,'Freshly trimmed, for the Makara Peak Rally.','2006-11-26 11:00:00','2006-11-26 11:00:00'),(173,7,1,'Freshly trimmed, for the Makara Peak Rally.','2006-11-26 11:00:00','2006-11-26 11:00:00'),(174,22,1,'The next big corner down from the one recently fixed was in the process of getting the same treatment. Also the last big right-hander has been bermed and de-rutted.','2006-11-26 11:00:00','2006-11-26 11:00:00'),(175,29,1,'Foliage is getting close!','2006-11-26 11:00:00','2006-11-26 11:00:00'),(176,31,1,'The last section just before the actual scout hall has rutted out quite badly with recent rain.','2006-11-26 11:00:00','2006-11-26 11:00:00'),(177,34,1,'The big dead tree at the very bottom by the mine has finally lowered itself so that you have to stop to get under it.','2006-11-26 11:00:00','2006-11-26 11:00:00'),(178,9,1,'All grass mown from start to end to a height of about 6 inches.','2006-12-03 13:00:00','2006-12-03 13:00:00'),(179,1,1,'The big tree has been removed that used to hang low-ish over a big left-hander (going up) just beneath the [[track:54]].','2007-01-13 16:00:00','2007-01-13 16:00:00'),(180,35,1,'Tree is gone, track is all clear.','2007-01-13 16:00:00','2007-01-13 16:00:00'),(181,29,1,'Becoming narrower as the spring growth finally kicks in. Some blackberry and gorse will be nasty later in Summer, watch out if travelling fast.','2007-01-16 19:00:00','2007-01-16 19:00:00'),(182,25,1,'Shiny new signs have been installed at the intersection with [[track:24]] and the entrace at George Denton Park.','2007-01-16 19:00:00','2007-01-16 19:00:00'),(183,24,1,'A little narrow in places due to plant growth. Also a wheel rut forming about halfway down due to cornering not braking.','2007-01-16 19:00:00','2007-01-16 19:00:00'),(184,24,1,'The aforementioned rut is almost invisible when riding up. Must be a speed/approach angle thing.','2007-01-18 07:00:00','2007-01-18 07:00:00'),(185,25,1,'Watch out for contractors on the upper western edge near where a transmission tower is just inside the fence. It looks like the old fence has corroded due to cyclists splashing through the puddle next to the fence.','2007-01-18 07:00:00','2007-01-18 07:00:00'),(186,55,1,'Still slippery under foot. Bikes have chewed it up a bit.','2007-01-18 07:00:00','2007-01-18 07:00:00'),(187,41,1,'Nice and narrow with new growth. Also the playground at the top is being replaced, beware contractors.','2007-01-18 07:00:00','2007-01-18 07:00:00'),(188,29,1,'Very narrow and overgrown in places. Blackberry plants are a bit nasty.','2007-02-05 11:30:00','2007-02-05 11:30:00'),(189,31,1,'Very narrow and overgrown, fun like a tunnel though.','2007-02-05 11:30:00','2007-02-05 11:30:00'),(190,34,1,'Getting narrow and overgrown.','2007-02-05 11:30:00','2007-02-05 11:30:00'),(191,5,1,'Recent work has widened a few sections. Also defined the track better in the wide messy sections. The short new grassy section of track with the fun hump at the start has a terrible right-hand exit that will rut out soon.','2007-02-06 10:30:00','2007-02-06 10:30:00'),(192,50,1,'Some older parts are starting to rough up. The lower half has been worked on and is flowing nicely.','2007-02-06 10:30:00','2007-02-06 10:30:00'),(193,40,1,'Freshly bladed. Still loose and dusty.','2007-02-07 12:00:00','2007-02-07 12:00:00'),(194,53,1,'Only one short unrideable section near the bottom. Recent work at the top is very nice, but dry and loose. There are lots of pointy sawn-off stumps around still so be very careful riding. ','2007-03-03 10:00:00','2007-03-03 10:00:00'),(195,23,1,'Smooth and fast. A couple of outside-corner berms are appearing. Feels very exposed and loose on the top half when riding down... beware!','2007-04-12 12:30:00','2007-04-12 12:30:00'),(196,39,1,'Beware the new ruts from recent rain. Large rocks on upper section seem to be absent...','2007-05-04 12:15:00','2007-05-04 12:15:00'),(197,32,1,'Ground is softening slightly. The new sections of pilot track between Mt Kaukau and Crowsnest seem to be surviving the recent rains. The northern-most sections are very exposed to the northerly winds.','2007-05-05 10:30:00','2007-05-05 10:30:00'),(198,33,1,'The cattle appears to have been moved elsewhere, land mines are slowly dissolving.','2007-05-05 10:30:00','2007-05-05 10:30:00'),(199,32,1,'Gorse is pretty bad in a couple of the switchbacks beneath the houses in Karori.','2007-05-06 10:30:00','2007-05-06 10:30:00'),(200,49,1,'Newly finished skink is very cool. Some more diggings happening in odd places, overall about 1/3 ridable.','2007-05-06 10:30:00','2007-05-06 10:30:00'),(201,48,1,'Freshly pruned!','2007-05-06 10:30:00','2007-05-06 10:30:00'),(202,9,1,'Grass and track-hangers pruned, very tidy.','2007-05-06 10:30:00','2007-05-06 10:30:00'),(203,3,1,'Drainage ditches cleared, bridge ramps filled and a new wider bridge installed.','2007-05-06 10:30:00','2007-05-06 10:30:00'),(204,5,1,'Lower curly rocky sections have had some work.','2007-05-06 10:30:00','2007-05-06 10:30:00'),(205,52,1,'Lightly trimmed all along. Watch those pesky clippings, derailler magnets...','2007-05-17 12:30:00','2007-05-17 12:30:00'),(206,11,1,'Fully trimmed with new drainage ditches along full length.','2007-05-17 12:30:00','2007-05-17 12:30:00'),(207,13,1,'Foliage completely trimmed - brazilian! The top section is wide enough to allow riding on the newly exposed grass, so you don\'t need to follow the rut. A bit of water diversion performed too.','2007-05-17 12:30:00','2007-05-17 12:30:00'),(208,4,1,'Serious rut forming in the clay on the lower half. Very greasy where there is some soil.','2007-07-07 11:00:00','2007-07-07 11:00:00'),(209,5,1,'The usual winter muck, actually pretty good given the recent amount of rain.','2007-07-07 11:00:00','2007-07-07 11:00:00'),(210,24,1,'Top two thirds is good. Lower third is a bit soft but the track is holding.','2007-07-26 12:20:00','2007-07-26 12:20:00'),(211,27,1,'Some very slippery ruts in places. Top half in the bush has been beautifully trimmed.','2007-07-26 12:20:00','2007-07-26 12:20:00'),(212,23,1,'Dry and fast. Minimal loose soft sections for going up, and just enough random rocks to keep it interesting coming down. Primo!','2007-07-29 10:30:00','2007-07-29 10:30:00'),(213,35,1,'The dodgy buggers who lay the logs across the track are active again. They were easily removed though and the track is clear.','2007-08-23 12:00:00','2007-08-23 12:00:00'),(214,40,1,'Super smooth and dry. The electricity contractors have packed down the gravel.','2007-08-23 12:00:00','2007-08-23 12:00:00'),(215,32,1,'Nearly dry. The cattle are making a mess still though, particularly on the single track section near the start of [[track:44]], and near the old house site on the 4wd section.','2007-08-23 12:00:00','2007-08-23 12:00:00'),(216,12,1,'New berms have been added that look like fun to ride down, will report back...','2007-08-24 12:15:00','2007-08-24 12:15:00'),(217,5,1,'Finally drying up after the winter.','2007-08-24 12:15:00','2007-08-24 12:15:00'),(218,6,1,'A little bit of loving has been applied in the form of gravel in some of the potential problem spots. Condition is good.','2007-08-24 12:15:00','2007-08-24 12:15:00'),(219,7,1,'The new realignment is getting close to finished. It is all ridable but narrow in a couple of spots.','2007-08-24 12:15:00','2007-08-24 12:15:00'),(220,67,1,'Current progress is about 600 metres of just walkable track. Beware the short sawn-off stumps, they eat your shins!','2007-12-18 15:43:25','2007-12-18 15:43:25'),(221,53,1,'Open! Beware of all the soft gravel. Not much rain lately to settle it.','2007-12-19 10:36:47','2007-12-19 10:36:47'),(222,67,1,'Blazing is now at 850 metres.','2007-12-23 17:59:05','2007-12-23 17:59:05'),(223,23,1,'Very dry and quite loose at the top when descending.','2007-12-22 16:03:17','2007-12-22 16:03:17'),(224,24,1,'Plenty of loose gravel in the top 200 metres. Take care. Also some track pixie work at the big S section, looks like it will go direct rather than the S.','2007-12-22 16:06:40','2007-12-22 16:06:40'),(225,67,1,'Spent most of an hour blazing, added maybe 50 metres more. A nice beech tree right beside the trail. Just rounding another spur with lots of manuka. Once around it\'s 80-100 metres of largish bush, should be good progress. I left my trusty hand saw at the trail head, please don\'t steal it!','2007-12-24 01:10:24','2007-12-24 01:10:24'),(226,67,1,'Xmas day blazing session, progress is now 920 metres or so all up. There\'s a nice beech tree beside the track. Also saw a pair of saddlebacks.','2007-12-25 12:47:35','2007-12-25 12:47:35'),(227,24,1,'A new curve has been added at the top of the big S, but it sucks. Doesn\'t flow and is very narrow. Not sure what it\'s all about.','2007-12-25 00:14:46','2007-12-25 00:14:46'),(229,67,1,'Reached the 1km mark, yay! There is a new access now. Head south on the seal past Suri\'s Slip to the dip just before where the cattle stop was. Keep hard left and you should see the yellow mark just before a large manuka. Only problem is there is not good cover for stashing bikes.','2007-12-28 15:03:01','2007-12-28 15:03:01'),(230,67,1,'A little more progress. Got around the barberry/gorse section and now into a good section of tall manuka. Approx 1050 metres now.','2007-12-28 15:05:18','2007-12-28 15:05:18'),(231,67,1,'Track is now 1140 metres long. Easy progress ahead through large manuka. Passed the fence that comes down from just south of the concreted-in cattle stop. Might need a new access soon.','2007-12-29 13:38:53','2007-12-29 13:38:53'),(232,27,1,'New veg was cleared about 4 weeks ago. Nice and wide but the blackberry is already lunging across the track, waiting to grab your arms/legs.','2007-12-30 20:38:38','2007-12-30 20:38:38'),(233,36,1,'Top five metres still very bushy.','2007-12-30 20:44:26','2007-12-30 20:44:26'),(234,39,1,'Bottom section doesn\'t seem so bad.','2007-12-30 20:46:05','2007-12-30 20:46:05'),(235,24,1,'The person or people digging the track have been sculpting some of the existing track. This looks good right now but it is not allowing for drainage, could be trouble when it\'s wet.','2008-01-01 13:39:50','2008-01-01 13:39:50'),(236,67,1,'New entrance. Just past (south of) the concreted-in cattle-stop on the big corner keep eyes peeled for the usual marker. It\'s a good 30 or so metres down to the trail-head, currently 3 tags on a manuka.','2008-01-01 13:42:00','2008-01-01 13:42:00'),(237,67,1,'Length is now 1250 metres. Hacked through a huge stand of stinging nettle, nasty stuff at 3 metres high!','2008-01-02 16:52:23','2008-01-02 16:52:23'),(238,7,1,'New entrance is fully operational. Still some soft edges.','2008-01-02 19:37:53','2008-01-02 19:37:53'),(239,23,1,'Still very sketchy at the top when descending.','2008-01-05 15:26:13','2008-01-05 15:26:13'),(240,67,1,'Added another 100 metres. Did some quick checks via my garmin and we are right on target altitude-wise to hit the saddle by the ostriches. I estimate about another 450 metres of blazing to the saddle. Looks like a bit of steeper terrain coming up.','2008-01-06 13:26:46','2008-01-06 13:26:46'),(241,29,2,'There is some nasty stinging nettle in a few places. It is very stingy right now!','2008-01-06 14:46:13','2008-01-06 14:46:13'),(242,47,2,'Wide. Nicely pruned and all gorse poisoned and dead track side.','2008-01-06 16:35:30','2008-01-06 16:35:30'),(243,46,2,'Quite overgrown, with non-spiky plants though. The planks over the hole are wobbly and dodgy.','2008-01-06 16:36:50','2008-01-06 16:36:50'),(244,31,2,'Track had major make-over about 6 weeks ago. Surface is very good and foliage trimmed well back. No ruts as yet.','2008-01-07 08:13:15','2008-01-07 08:13:15'),(245,23,1,'All good after recent rain. Less dusty loose stuff.','2008-01-10 14:11:39','2008-01-10 14:11:39'),(246,24,1,'Sweet. Smooth and firm. Someone has been trimming in places and it\'s all good.','2008-01-10 14:13:44','2008-01-10 14:13:44'),(247,67,1,'Another 50 meters have been added. That puts full length at about 1.4km now. A new entrance is needed...','2008-01-14 14:36:14','2008-01-14 14:36:14'),(248,31,2,'A modest sized tree is down at the bottom where there is a new split in the track. You can ride the old steep way.','2008-01-14 18:41:38','2008-01-14 18:41:38'),(249,29,1,'The top quarter has been cleared. Great job, very wide, looks like the council/pd lads. It is getting very close towards the bottom.','2008-01-16 14:31:13','2008-01-16 14:31:13'),(250,30,1,'Very nice. Quite dry and minimal loose stuff.','2008-01-16 14:32:00','2008-01-16 14:32:00'),(251,29,2,'Nettles have been pulled out. There are still lots of grabby blackberry and bush lawyer hangers that grab your arms though.','2008-01-20 05:58:57','2008-01-20 05:58:57'),(252,31,1,'Cleared the fallen tree mess near the bottom. You can now go via either track.','2008-01-20 07:59:36','2008-01-20 07:59:36'),(253,5,2,'Getting pretty loose at the bottom','2008-01-20 10:35:42','2008-01-20 10:35:42'),(254,67,1,'70 more metres today. Just coming up to a nice little clearing on a saddle. Perfect place to make a new access. Probably time to start from the ostrich saddle and head back to this point.','2008-01-20 21:34:47','2008-01-20 21:34:47'),(255,67,1,'Cleared the 40 metres to the clearing. A total of about 1.55km, nice. Also added a new access track - to find the top go south on the sealed road just past the post exit/entrance to [[track:25]], it\'s marked in the usual way. Tools are back down the track proper about 10 metres, again marked in the usual way. Next work is probably to put a marker at the clearing - like a supermarket bag tied up high and then start from the ostrich saddle and work back.','2008-01-21 13:38:45','2008-01-21 13:38:45'),(256,67,5,'Outstanding work Jonny.  Just got back from holiday and checked out the whole length of the blazed trail at lunchtime.  Took 35 min to walk.  I\'ll go back tomorrow and put something up the tree to see if we can see it from further south.  The elevation and route choice look spot on!','2008-01-22 17:22:31','2008-01-22 17:22:31'),(257,67,5,'Put yellow bag up tree.  It can be seen (with difficulty) from the last corner heading south down to the turnoff but not from corner south of turnoff.  Looks like the track will come out in the middle of the \'fern\'/low growth/slip area.  It might be an idea to blaze to this area as its easy to see.  Have started the blazing from the turnoff heading north (one saw hanging in a tree - rest of tools in same place).  It seems as if we\'ll need to gain a bit of height to meet the existing track but it\'ll be easier to figure that out when we get to the final ridge separating the two track ends.','2008-01-24 16:58:39','2008-01-24 16:58:39'),(258,34,1,'Near the top by the turn off to Birdwood steps there has been some track maintenance. About 50 metres is extremely soft and loose due to the extreme dry track conditions right now.[[br]]Otherwise good.','2008-02-01 00:22:03','2008-02-01 00:22:03'),(259,23,1,'There\'s a sign at the top (only) saying some tracks in the area are closed for maintenance until 14 Feb, except for the [[track:23]]. Which is strange as the only place I could see \"maintenance\" was at the cattle yards on the [[track:23]]! Large yellow dozer/mower thing, beware.','2008-02-06 06:45:45','2008-02-06 06:45:45'),(260,39,1,'Spring gorse is beginning to lean over the track and with recent dry weather it is hardening up and getting nasty.','2008-02-06 06:47:20','2008-02-06 06:47:20'),(261,65,1,'Getting over-grown in places.','2008-02-06 14:59:44','2008-02-06 14:59:44'),(262,5,1,'Kind of looks like some work has been done on the loose lower section. Either that or it is just breaking up. Either way it is very dry and loose.','2008-02-06 15:02:27','2008-02-06 15:02:27'),(263,46,1,'Still quite overgrown. Ok for walking though.','2008-02-10 14:12:44','2008-02-10 14:12:44'),(264,67,1,'Checked out current progress and added a few more metres, excellent! All up at 200 metres from ostrich saddle heading north. Maybe only another 200 metres to connect at the clearing. There is a seriously stinky rubbish dump site along the new bit of track, TVs, fridges, microwaves, and general bags of bad. No sign of the dude(s) who were camping at the clearing...','2008-02-10 14:23:29','2008-02-10 14:23:29'),(265,56,5,'The WCC has a big digger with the mower attachment on it clearing all the veg.  Looks like its almost done - approching the south end','2008-02-13 14:02:42','2008-02-13 14:02:42'),(266,67,5,'The track heading south now meets the track heading north!!  Yippee the first cut of blazing stage 1 of the track extension is complete.  Be warned - it still needs a bit more work down the south end - track isn\'t that well marked in places and has a steep side slope.  We now need WCC signoff before the earthworks commence.  Hopefully Jonny will walk the track with his GPS and load it up on this page.  Yell out how long it takes to walk!','2008-02-15 15:03:56','2008-02-15 15:03:56'),(267,67,1,'Walked the full length of stage 1, about 1.9km! Took me about 30 minutes at a trot/scramble. Overall loss of altitude of about 30 metres. Will post the track path and profile as soon as I sort out a tech issue...','2008-02-17 12:16:25','2008-02-17 12:16:25'),(268,29,1,'Foliage now trimmed for the entire track. Some small bits on track still but should not cause problems.','2008-02-27 16:12:22','2008-02-27 16:12:22'),(269,34,1,'Previous diggings are settling down. The lower section from road to the creek has been trimmed too.','2008-02-27 16:13:43','2008-02-27 16:13:43'),(270,67,5,'WCC has granted consent (thanks Dave) to bench the track from the windmill to Long Gully turnoff - all the red line shown on the Google map.  Will go buy tools (thanks Ground Effect - in advance) and start digging!!!!','2008-02-28 13:55:30','2008-02-28 13:55:30'),(271,68,1,'Track seems to be open. Condition is good with only a few soft edges. Some close trees if traveling too fast.','2008-03-07 10:39:31','2008-03-07 10:39:31'),(272,7,1,'New section still has some soft edges. And looks like a crime scene with tape running through the trees!','2008-03-07 10:40:50','2008-03-07 10:40:50'),(273,46,1,'A decent trim has been done. Easily passable now. The main part that parallels the fence has had a really good prune. Some major digging too, maybe part of the new bird sanctuary building?','2008-03-08 16:53:24','2008-03-08 16:53:24'),(274,1,1,'Giant rodents have been digging little drainage ditches, all good stuff.','2008-03-08 16:55:42','2008-03-08 16:55:42'),(275,9,1,'Removed a large tree from across the top jumpy/rutty section, all clear.','2008-03-08 16:57:01','2008-03-08 16:57:01'),(276,10,1,'Grass and foliage making the track quite narrow.','2008-03-08 16:57:37','2008-03-08 16:57:37'),(277,68,1,'About 100 metres from the top there is an obvious old 4wd track heading up. It would connect really easily with [[track:50]] and would help make the park more maze-like and less \'loopy\', if you know what I mean. Worth considering as a future project.','2008-03-08 17:02:46','2008-03-08 17:02:46'),(278,58,5,'The western vertical side of the shaft has suffered a few bouts of gravity sickness ie piles of rubble all over the place.  Its still passable but more of a scramble than a ride (not that it was ever ridable for mortals anyway).','2008-03-10 11:29:49','2008-03-10 11:29:49'),(279,59,5,'The western end has been weed eaten from the red rocks track, past the spooky gully track to the next high point.  It gets a bit prickly close to the old quarry.  Worth a look if you\'ve never been there (include the scramble down Elevator Shaft) but probably not a regular ride route.','2008-03-10 11:35:30','2008-03-10 11:35:30'),(280,41,5,'The track is in the process of being rebenched - top to bottom.  The two ends have been done with some extra hairpins put in to reduce the gradient.  Its fairly loose at pres but should firm up great.  The benching looks like the work of G P-T but could be wrong.','2008-03-13 09:09:38','2008-03-13 09:09:38'),(281,4,1,'Overall condition is very good. Giant rodent diggings as seen on [[track:1]] are so fresh it is almost as if Zac was just digging them this morning!','2008-03-15 13:22:46','2008-03-15 13:22:46'),(282,7,1,'Lower half has been trimmed nicely.','2008-03-15 13:23:59','2008-03-15 13:23:59'),(283,25,1,'The steep section heading down to the glade (southern end low-point) when going clockwise has a serious rut forming.','2008-03-15 13:27:33','2008-03-15 13:27:33'),(284,67,1,'About 70 metres is nicely benched now. However it looks like pigs may be doing their best to turn over the freshly dug soil.','2008-03-15 13:29:49','2008-03-15 13:29:49'),(285,41,2,'New track work is good. Very dry though so will be loose until some wet/dry cycles.','2008-03-25 19:29:20','2008-03-25 19:29:20'),(286,27,1,'The fallen pine across the track near the bottom has been cut and moved aside.','2008-03-26 11:03:01','2008-03-26 11:03:01'),(287,31,1,'Entire track is in excellent condition. Surface is solid.','2008-03-28 18:50:34','2008-03-28 18:50:34'),(288,52,1,'Extremely sketchy near the top. Very dry and loose.','2008-03-28 18:51:57','2008-03-28 18:51:57'),(289,30,1,'Foliage getting very close but track is solid.','2008-03-28 18:52:45','2008-03-28 18:52:45'),(290,67,1,'Digging is on... Ride-able from the top corner of [[track:24]] for maybe 90 metres. Top zigzag access is very soft so probably down only at present.','2008-03-29 17:11:56','2008-03-29 17:11:56'),(291,67,5,'Installed info signs at the main entry points to the track.  Paced out the new track (north end) and entry at 170 metres (Jonny must have a very long stride!).  The track around the old windmill lookout knob has had a bit of benching work done by \'the others\'.  Also added a few metres to it.    Yesterday I started benching at the south end of the track (next to the Long Gully turnoff).  Did about 10 metres.  Hopefully this rain will help stabilise the new bench work.','2008-03-31 12:08:58','2008-03-31 12:08:58'),(292,32,1,'The first week of the wet season (kinda) and the cattle have been moved back into the middle section of the track, above Otari/Wilotn. They are making a big mess, both chopping the track and leaving \"land mines\". Also a new person/bike width mini-cattle stop near to of British Peak turn off. Very nifty, yes I said nifty!','2008-04-06 13:46:16','2008-04-06 13:46:16'),(293,29,1,'Track in good condition given the recent rain and yesterday\'s downhill event.','2008-04-06 13:54:51','2008-04-06 13:54:51'),(294,30,1,'Slippery after recent rain but yesterday\'s downhill event did little or no extra damage. The bottom quarter/fifth has been trimmed nicely.','2008-04-06 13:57:05','2008-04-06 13:57:05'),(295,67,5,'Benched 200m at the north end and 70m at the south end.','2008-04-08 09:02:11','2008-04-08 09:02:11'),(296,49,1,'Officially open. Condition is pretty good, however there is no gravel and the wet is coming so ride gentle. Probably more ridable in the [[track:14]] to [[track:13]] direction.','2008-04-08 13:44:37','2008-04-08 13:44:37'),(297,11,1,'Foliage trimmed, ruts removed, surface solid. Solid, nuff said.','2008-04-08 13:53:18','2008-04-08 13:53:18'),(298,11,1,'More track work has left some loose stuff but it should settle down really quickly, be gentle when riding down for a bit.','2008-04-12 20:56:19','2008-04-12 20:56:19'),(299,7,1,'Track closed until about 24 April due to work being done on the coms gear at the junction of [[track:7]]/[[track:22]].','2008-04-16 14:43:16','2008-04-16 14:43:16'),(300,22,1,'Track closed until about 24 April due to work being done on the coms gear at the junction of [[track:7]]/[[track:22]].','2008-04-16 14:43:44','2008-04-16 14:43:44'),(301,48,1,'Track has been extended at the top. It now traverses via single track to the top of the old [[track:4]] exit (known by some as P-Spot).','2008-04-21 14:30:47','2008-04-21 14:30:47'),(302,11,1,'Condition is excellent. Recent diggings have settled nicely.','2008-04-27 17:33:39','2008-04-27 17:33:39'),(303,12,1,'Excellent. Haven\'t been here for a while and it\'s all good. Lots of recent track work should see the winter through.','2008-04-27 17:35:50','2008-04-27 17:35:50'),(304,4,1,'Generally pretty good. New drains working. Still plenty of bare clay bits that will get slippery and chewed during the coming winter.','2008-04-27 17:37:22','2008-04-27 17:37:22'),(305,50,1,'Condition is good. Lots of recent digging has sured up most potential winter bogs.','2008-04-27 17:38:58','2008-04-27 17:38:58'),(306,7,1,'Track is open again. Contractor work is continuing on the coms tower so be careful during weekdays for the next week or so. Also there has been plenty of track loving on the upper parts, including some modest jumps that can be rolled easily if that\'s not your thing.','2008-04-27 17:42:08','2008-04-27 17:42:08'),(307,29,1,'Condition is ok for now. It will get mucky as usual during the winter.','2008-04-27 17:43:07','2008-04-27 17:43:07'),(308,30,1,'Fun! Classic \"deliverance\".','2008-04-27 17:43:41','2008-04-27 17:43:41'),(309,69,1,'A wild ride for sure! My first time down and it looks like not many others use this track. After [[track:70]] goes off to the left it is very steep with soft old clay. The last 5 metres are completely overgrown and if you shut your eyes and hold straight you will pass through!','2008-04-27 18:01:52','2008-04-27 18:01:52'),(310,71,1,'Vegetation is very close, but track is easily passable.','2008-04-27 18:08:16','2008-04-27 18:08:16'),(311,24,1,'Filthy f**kers, someone has laid a huge dump right alongside the track. Probably about 50 metres down from the top, look for the white paper! Disgusting...','2008-04-27 18:15:38','2008-04-27 18:15:38'),(312,67,1,'Chipped away another 5 metres or so at the south end, through stumps etc. Just about to round a corner to a new valley so that feels like progress. It\'s going to be a cool track.','2008-04-27 18:56:22','2008-04-27 18:56:22'),(313,41,1,'The little sign (walkers left, bikers right) near the intersection with [[track:62]] has gone, maybe a disgruntled walker?','2008-04-28 21:11:23','2008-04-28 21:11:23'),(314,30,1,'Wild ride! The recent rain has made the top rocky section very challenging. It\'s probably as technical as I have ever seen it, especially while it\'s wet.','2008-05-04 19:07:44','2008-05-04 19:07:44'),(315,14,1,'There was a big make-over yesterday by the Makara Peak supporters. Condition is excellent with no recent rain. Top left-hander is much more negotiable without the awkward \"crashing in the bushes\"! A new left-hand line about halfway down has a technical drop at the end with a really short run-out, beware. Otherwise it\'s all good with the old rut removed. Nice work!','2008-05-19 15:50:54','2008-05-19 15:50:54'),(316,67,5,'Track now benched and rideable for 330m at the north end and 130m at the south end.  Its about 25% done for benching!','2008-05-20 17:42:23','2008-05-20 17:42:23'),(317,49,5,'Up T3 and down the cleaned up Trickle Falls is a great combo!','2008-05-20 17:45:48','2008-05-20 17:45:48'),(318,39,1,'A few loose trimmings at the top. Also some piles of soft gravel in places and a few growing ruts about halfway. Still really good though.','2008-05-23 20:10:53','2008-05-23 20:10:53'),(319,4,1,'Lots of fresh gravel action at on the newest top section, good timing. Still soft and still plenty of muddy sections. Good work.','2008-06-10 16:22:23','2008-06-10 16:22:23'),(320,10,1,'Quite slippery on the upper sections, particularly just after [[track:65]] comes in.','2008-06-10 19:18:54','2008-06-10 19:18:54'),(321,65,1,'Track is solid considering the recent wet. New bridge looks solid.','2008-06-10 19:19:39','2008-06-10 19:19:39'),(322,30,1,'The track seems to be permanently wet now, winter and all that. The roots and rocks are quite slippery. Still 100% rideable and lots of fun though.','2008-06-14 14:51:36','2008-06-14 14:51:36'),(323,29,1,'Lots of soft mud but not messy.','2008-06-14 14:52:16','2008-06-14 14:52:16'),(324,51,1,'Super messy mud. The contractors vehicles have made the surface very messy. There is a good solid gravel base though.','2008-06-14 14:56:32','2008-06-14 14:56:32'),(325,22,1,'Usual greasy bits. Some new drains at odd angles on some corners.','2008-06-14 20:20:23','2008-06-14 20:20:23'),(326,14,1,'Recent track work holding up well. There is a series of sloping rocks about 1/4 way down that are extremely slippery when wet, i.e now.','2008-06-14 21:24:13','2008-06-14 21:24:13'),(327,34,1,'Track condition is still very good.','2008-06-15 20:34:50','2008-06-15 20:34:50'),(328,73,1,'New gravel seems to have set pretty well in spite of the renegade actions of a certain cyclist!','2008-06-21 15:14:03','2008-06-21 15:14:03'),(329,1,1,'A few minor puddles but really pretty good. Although I still think winter is still just teasing, not proper wet yet.','2008-06-27 18:48:03','2008-06-27 18:48:03'),(331,2,1,'A few rutty clay sections but nothing serious.','2008-06-27 18:50:38','2008-06-27 18:50:38'),(332,4,1,'Lots of gravel laid and general maintenance. All good as it was getting pretty mucky in places, particularly the top 3rd. Good work Don and co.','2008-06-27 18:52:44','2008-06-27 18:52:44'),(333,5,1,'A few new drains and gravel applied to the top section where you first start properly heading down. A good thing as this is usually the wettest place in the park.','2008-06-27 18:54:37','2008-06-27 18:54:37'),(334,67,1,'Checked out the south end. Like what you\'ve done with the \"lounge\" section Mr S! One pig dig session has made a hole in the middle of the track, easy to fix. Removed a few windfalls from the recent wild wind.','2008-06-30 11:18:37','2008-06-30 11:18:37'),(335,29,2,'The big tree that was down near the Woodhouse intersection has been cleared.','2008-07-05 18:27:23','2008-07-05 18:27:23'),(336,32,1,'The grassy section from the watertank south to the exit at Makara Hill road was getting a major trimming. Lots of little stuff on the ground.','2008-07-05 18:31:37','2008-07-05 18:31:37'),(337,12,1,'Snow on the sides of the track near the top! Most unusual for Wellington.','2008-07-05 21:40:52','2008-07-05 21:40:52'),(338,5,1,'Messy but fun.','2008-07-05 21:41:12','2008-07-05 21:41:12'),(339,50,1,'Sloppy stuff on top, solid underneath.','2008-07-05 21:41:51','2008-07-05 21:41:51'),(340,7,1,'A few newish drains have left the track surprisingly dry. One big loose patch of gravel to beware of, just as you drop in to the big right-hander just before the wooden section before the coms tower - got that!','2008-07-05 21:46:47','2008-07-05 21:46:47'),(341,29,1,'Mucky in places.','2008-07-05 21:47:20','2008-07-05 21:47:20'),(342,32,1,'Big tree segment down right at the south-end track user counter. Easily negotiated though. Possibly the workers that were up there today will fix it.','2008-07-05 21:48:50','2008-07-05 21:48:50'),(343,41,17,'Some bigger ruts appearing near the Holloway Rd (bottom) end of the track. Worst ruts are on the tighter corners. Heavy rain has made the edges a bit loose too.','2008-07-06 17:06:47','2008-07-06 17:06:47'),(344,29,17,'Boggy in patches. Ok down, but some loss of traction at points heading up.','2008-07-06 17:51:03','2008-07-06 17:51:03'),(345,67,1,'Did some digging at the north end. Added about 15 metres of ridable track in the previous \"photo dig\" section. A pair of saddlebacks joined me and did their squawking thing. Neither of them had bands so they must be next-generation from the bird sanctuary nearby.','2008-07-09 14:06:19','2008-07-09 14:06:19'),(346,27,1,'Some graveling action and smoothing on the steepish rutted section near [[track:42]]. Also someone has chopped out some roots on the upper bushy traverse bit. The annual bogs are back, small but deep!','2008-07-09 15:18:03','2008-07-09 15:18:03'),(347,27,1,'Looked up from the bottom to view small digger making mess. Not sure how far up it goes, will investigate soon, maybe when it stops raining...','2008-07-29 17:01:31','2008-07-29 17:01:31'),(348,30,1,'So much water there is no mud! Stream crossings were axle deep but this should subside a bit soon.','2008-08-05 07:17:06','2008-08-05 07:17:06'),(349,23,1,'All good. Some surface water in the saddle section but lower half is surprisingly dry. Quite a few large rocks and small slips require extra concentration when descending quickly.','2008-08-05 18:32:36','2008-08-05 18:32:36'),(350,67,1,'Some more lunchtime dig sessions have moved the north trail end to a large grassy access from the sealed road above, so it\'s not just an out-and-back anymore.','2008-08-05 18:36:21','2008-08-05 18:36:21'),(351,5,1,'Super messy. Best avoided at present as riding will cause significant damage.','2008-08-05 18:38:30','2008-08-05 18:38:30'),(352,35,23,'The lower part of the track is blocked in two places by a large tree that has fallen in a slip.  It is passable, but requires a bit of a scramble.','2008-08-05 21:49:23','2008-08-05 21:49:23'),(353,12,23,'Encountered a family of goats, including a small kid.  Hopefully they won\'t eat the newly planted seedlings.','2008-08-05 22:04:13','2008-08-05 22:04:13'),(354,63,1,'(2nd hand info) there are reports of a decent rockfall blocking the road for vehicles but is still passable (just) for bikers and walkers.','2008-08-07 13:56:24','2008-08-07 13:56:24'),(355,25,23,'A sprinkling of snow near the wind turbine and Wrights Hill added to the already very wet track conditions.  Also, watch out for the ruts near the glade - they are approaching canyon proportions.','2008-08-09 22:01:03','2008-08-09 22:01:03'),(356,7,1,'The loose patch of gravel has mostly settled down. The corners immediately after this have had some work and are still soft.','2008-08-10 08:26:27','2008-08-10 08:26:27'),(357,25,23,'The section of track between Waiapu Road and George Denton Park is closed by earthworks.  A large hole has been dug where the track first meets the fence, about 200m from the Waiapu Road entrance.','2008-08-10 08:59:50','2008-08-10 08:59:50'),(358,36,23,'Gorse is closing in on the top 30m of the track.  Time for a trim.','2008-08-10 19:18:15','2008-08-10 19:18:15'),(359,24,23,'A bit muddy in places, but generally in good condition considering the rain we\'ve had recently.','2008-08-10 19:20:47','2008-08-10 19:20:47'),(360,39,23,'Surprisingly dry and fast, given recent weather conditions.  The very last section, a 300m long rut-infested gravel slide that descends 90m to the beach, is as dicey as ever (ie. great fun).','2008-08-10 19:37:08','2008-08-10 19:37:08'),(361,63,23,'In addition to the rock fall, there is a deep washout near the first group of baches closest to the Owhiro Bay Parade car park.  OK for bikers and walkers.','2008-08-10 19:43:28','2008-08-10 19:43:28'),(362,10,1,'A little feral. Lots of punga fronds, muddy sections and close foliage. One really mean rut on an upper clay section, only about 4 metres long but narrow and deep.','2008-08-16 21:42:38','2008-08-16 21:42:38'),(363,4,1,'Fantastic. A few puddles but all that gravel has set nice and firm.','2008-08-16 21:44:00','2008-08-16 21:44:00'),(364,8,1,'A bit messy but not too bad. The chicken wire on the ramps is coming off and the final ramp to track exit is getting a bit sketchy.','2008-08-16 21:45:25','2008-08-16 21:45:25'),(365,35,23,'A bypass is emerging over the slip, but it isnâ€™t bike friendly. The large tree no longer blocks the track.','2008-08-17 19:03:57','2008-08-17 19:03:57'),(366,14,23,'Looks to have had little traffic recently, which is probably a good thing for preserving the track during winter (I was walking).','2008-08-17 19:04:54','2008-08-17 19:04:54'),(367,49,23,'Parts of the track are a bit soft.  The Twister obstacle is almost buried in rubble washed down the hill.','2008-08-17 19:05:22','2008-08-17 19:05:22'),(368,13,23,'Bottom half is quite wet, but in reasonable condition.','2008-08-17 19:05:53','2008-08-17 19:05:53'),(369,11,23,'All good.  The track surface is surviving the winter in good condition.','2008-08-17 19:07:11','2008-08-17 19:07:11'),(370,11,17,'Yup - she\'s all good.','2008-08-17 21:29:26','2008-08-17 21:29:26'),(371,12,17,'Minor rutting appearing on a couple of the switchbacks.  Fantastic condition considering the rainfall this year.','2008-08-17 21:35:06','2008-08-17 21:35:06'),(372,4,17,'Cool up and down. Full credit to the shovel crew.','2008-08-17 21:36:18','2008-08-17 21:36:18'),(373,8,1,'Track was getting some love today, in progress when I went through. Some drainage ditches etc, new mesh on the ramp section, and the old switchbacks were being reworked so that you can\'t straight-line it. Meh to that last one, I don\'t think it\'s work the effort.','2008-08-17 23:13:17','2008-08-17 23:13:17'),(374,53,22,'Gravel is bedding down nicely, still a few off-camber corners to catch beginners. Nice','2008-08-18 13:00:15','2008-08-18 13:00:15'),(375,27,5,'WCC contractors have gravelled and compacted the last 20 m of the track  before you hit Aro St.  They\'ve put in about 4 serious rain ditchs to stop gravel washing onto Aro St.  Checked it out today and it seems to work fine.  I\'ve rebenched a fair amount of the upper track up to the turnoff to the pylon/first big puddle on single track. ','2008-08-18 16:11:12','2008-08-18 16:11:12'),(376,74,23,'The track surface is mostly firm and in good condition. Watch out for a small tree that has fallen across the track about 150m from the top.','2008-08-23 20:22:58','2008-08-23 20:22:58'),(377,75,23,'Firm and fast.  Gravel added to the extension has settled well, making for a solid track surface.','2008-08-23 20:26:56','2008-08-23 20:26:56'),(378,76,23,'Dry and firm.  A few sections are deeply rutted, but not too bad.','2008-08-23 22:45:26','2008-08-23 22:45:26'),(379,80,23,'Very slushy clay, especially around the dirt race track.','2008-08-24 11:40:06','2008-08-24 11:40:06'),(380,81,23,'Freshly trimmed and graded, so in fine condition.','2008-08-25 12:16:12','2008-08-25 12:16:12'),(381,8,1,'New mesh on structures is good, but made of some plasticky stuff that was extremely slippery under bike shoes, tyres ok. New switchback about midway to stop you straight-lining a section is good, slows riders a bit.','2008-08-25 12:53:30','2008-08-25 12:53:30'),(382,10,1,'Still messy. Punga fronds off the track but clay is soft and the ruts and rocks are tricky.','2008-08-25 12:55:56','2008-08-25 12:55:56'),(383,35,17,'Big tree is still obstructing the lower track. There is a bypass but boggy on the uphill side so riding over could offer a reality check for over confident riders - quick dismount recommended. The track has got a bit sloppy with all the rain. Still a good ride up and down.','2008-08-28 18:37:20','2008-08-28 18:37:20'),(384,11,17,'This track is bullet proof.  Itâ€™s soaked up litres of rain and still sweet. Love those switchbacks.','2008-08-28 18:41:23','2008-08-28 18:41:23'),(385,12,17,'As with Varley\'s - Zac\'s is surviving the wet winter in style.','2008-08-28 18:42:49','2008-08-28 18:42:49'),(386,28,17,'Few deep boggy patches that can\'t be avoided. Not a huge issue it\'s firm underneath.','2008-08-30 09:32:38','2008-08-30 09:32:38'),(387,27,17,'Really hard to get bite on clay and dirt climbs - a number of slippery sections. ','2008-08-30 09:29:00','2008-08-30 09:29:00'),(388,16,17,'New corners with good berms added on the \'difficult\' exit. Probably been there for ages but haven\'t ridden it for a while.','2008-08-31 13:55:11','2008-08-31 13:55:11'),(389,27,2,'Just before the bottom where the new digging stops a large pine tree has fallen over away from the track and taken huge chunk of the track with it, beware!','2008-08-31 17:27:16','2008-08-31 17:27:16'),(390,67,5,'Done about 230m at the south end.  Have paced out and put in distance markers at 100m rests on trees (sorry Jonny its not GPS techo).  Have gone south to north and we have 700m to go to join the two track ends up.  We also have the track around the back of the knob to do as well - about 350m.  In all, we\'ve done about 0.85 kms of the 1.9 km overall length.  Thats averaging 140m per month, so 5 more months could see the track ends connected (excluding back of knob).','2008-09-01 16:34:25','2008-09-01 16:34:25'),(391,84,23,'A little muddy under the gum trees, but generally good.','2008-09-01 21:56:19','2008-09-01 21:56:19'),(392,85,23,'Recent storm damage has been mostly cleared away, except for one large fallen tree at the side of the track.','2008-09-01 21:57:55','2008-09-01 21:57:55'),(393,86,23,'Recently trimmed - but watch out for some drainage ruts on the descent.','2008-09-01 21:59:02','2008-09-01 21:59:02'),(394,87,23,'The upper section has been recently trimmed, so all clear.','2008-09-01 22:00:48','2008-09-01 22:00:48'),(395,83,23,'When it is wet, that clay and bare rock surface requires either full commitment or dismount to carefully climb down - there\'s no inbetween.  Beware.','2008-09-01 22:04:35','2008-09-01 22:04:35'),(396,88,23,'In almost pristine condition - clearly gets little use, probably because of the trees blocking the track.','2008-09-03 07:15:41','2008-09-03 07:15:41'),(397,89,23,'Fresh gravel in places, which is quite deep and soft so watch out for that.','2008-09-06 08:24:00','2008-09-06 08:24:00'),(398,12,23,'Saw those goats again, about 200m from where Zac\'s meets Snake Charmer.','2008-09-06 21:51:22','2008-09-06 21:51:22'),(399,93,23,'There\'s a small slip across the track on the eastern hill just before the wetland boardwalk.','2008-09-06 22:03:12','2008-09-06 22:03:12'),(400,30,1,'Extreme amounts of water, will only be temporary. Stream crossings were unrideable with water over knee height. Fun though!','2008-09-07 07:28:53','2008-09-07 07:28:53'),(401,29,1,'Very wet. The huge low branch on the macrocarpa tree near the bottom that you wriggle around has split and is threatening to get lower.','2008-09-07 07:31:13','2008-09-07 07:31:13'),(402,32,17,'Just a deep bog in many places. Hard to keep rolling momentum. Mud over the wheel rims. Likely to be a bike and hike especially on uphill sections (unless you have a big enough engine to counter wheel spinning).','2008-09-07 14:01:12','2008-09-07 14:01:12'),(403,40,23,'Some small ruts just above the pylon that the track passes under, but otherwise good.','2008-09-07 18:33:23','2008-09-07 18:33:23'),(404,32,23,'Absolutely gorgeous - a beautiful fine Wellington day with barely a breath of wind.  Oh, and the track was OK (at least north of Emedee).','2008-09-07 18:42:38','2008-09-07 18:42:38'),(405,29,1,'Gone from just wet to filthy mucky, I guess plenty of use over the weekend has \"slopped it up\". The marcocarpa branch is lower...','2008-09-08 10:26:17','2008-09-08 10:26:17'),(406,25,1,'Some major puddles on the section above [[track:34]] and above [[track:31]].','2008-09-08 11:01:37','2008-09-08 11:01:37'),(407,29,17,'Tree has been cleared by WCC contractors. Track is wet but ok. ','2008-09-12 08:37:44','2008-09-12 08:37:44'),(408,49,1,'Checked out the new swing bridge structure. I like it. Not too difficult but feels weird to ride. Most of the track is soft and slippery so I walked a fair bit in the uphill direction.','2008-09-13 17:59:30','2008-09-13 17:59:30'),(409,9,23,'The upper section is firm and fast. The lower section is getting a bit rugged, with a rough and loose rocky surface.  There are also a couple of rock falls partially across the track.','2008-09-14 20:57:10','2008-09-14 20:57:10'),(410,48,23,'Extension\'s surface is still quite raw, but in reasonable condition.','2008-09-14 21:07:55','2008-09-14 21:07:55'),(411,35,23,'Soft track conditions offer little traction, making for a difficult climb.','2008-09-14 21:05:59','2008-09-14 21:05:59'),(412,27,17,'Some sketchy bogs on 2 corners. Most of track is fantastic with the exception of those two wet patches. The hole left by the uprooted tree could create a couple of new pairs of beige undies or some bent bones.','2008-09-16 06:55:26','2008-09-16 06:55:26'),(413,24,1,'Gorse is getting tight on the top sections and I\'m sure that pooh is still lurking... stay on track!','2008-09-17 10:08:22','2008-09-17 10:08:22'),(414,36,1,'Well trimmed and widened at the top by the style/fence. All clear.','2008-09-17 10:09:13','2008-09-17 10:09:13'),(415,30,1,'All good.','2008-09-20 15:11:04','2008-09-20 15:11:04'),(416,13,1,'A bit slippery but in good condition. Looks like not much usage lately.','2008-09-20 15:12:12','2008-09-20 15:12:12'),(417,14,1,'Condition is good. A little slippery but not much use, that\'s winter I suppose.','2008-09-20 15:13:19','2008-09-20 15:13:19'),(418,2,1,'Good cleanup by the Makara Peak Supporters last weekend. Foliage trimmed and some boggy clay sections graveled. Good work.','2008-09-20 15:20:31','2008-09-20 15:20:31'),(419,5,1,'Drying up. Some sections have had some work, drainage, gravel and realignment. Rides well at present.','2008-09-20 15:21:49','2008-09-20 15:21:49'),(420,22,1,'Very last section has had some trimming which makes the visibility lines much better, track feels wider.','2008-09-20 15:23:08','2008-09-20 15:23:08'),(421,29,17,'Spring has sprung! Dried right out. Firm and fast surface.  ','2008-09-23 08:37:22','2008-09-23 08:37:22'),(422,32,17,'Few minor soft spots but mostly firm and dry.  ','2008-09-29 09:07:35','2008-09-29 09:07:35'),(423,67,5,'Have got to the 300m distance marker at the south end and the 900m marker at the north end ie 600m to go to connect up the track (excludes the bit around the back of the knob - about 350m).','2008-09-29 09:09:08','2008-09-29 09:09:08'),(424,24,5,'Have de-gorsed (pulled out rather than cut) most of the top part of the track (up to Maori Gully ridge).  Hope to finish it off this week.','2008-09-29 09:11:56','2008-09-29 09:11:56'),(425,79,35,'Relatively dry, tacky in some places. No large puddles or wet areas. \r\nTrail packed in nicely now, with problematic areas rock armored.','2008-09-29 22:33:07','2008-09-29 22:33:07'),(426,75,35,'Gravel is well settled now after recent increase in traffic. No wet areas.','2008-09-29 22:34:39','2008-09-29 22:34:39'),(427,2,23,'New signage indicating that the track is one-way, from [[track:1]] to [[track:3]].','2008-10-04 11:51:01','2008-10-04 11:51:01'),(428,1,23,'Recently trimmed, with some additional armouring along the Karori Stream section.','2008-10-04 11:54:48','2008-10-04 11:54:48'),(429,3,23,'Many of the rocky parts have been smoothed out, especially at the [[track:2]] end. Some recent track work is still a bit soft.','2008-10-04 11:59:29','2008-10-04 11:59:29'),(430,4,23,'Firm and dry, apart from a few insignificant puddles.','2008-10-04 11:58:50','2008-10-04 11:58:50'),(431,12,23,'All good.','2008-10-04 12:01:25','2008-10-04 12:01:25'),(432,11,23,'The top section is a bit wet, but the switchbacks are solid.','2008-10-04 12:02:53','2008-10-04 12:02:53'),(433,35,23,'The fallen tree bypass has been turned into a ridable chicane.','2008-10-04 12:07:58','2008-10-04 12:07:58'),(434,117,23,'Recently trimmed, so now wide and clear.','2008-10-04 13:02:25','2008-10-04 13:02:25'),(435,29,23,'A bit squishy in places, but generally OK.','2008-10-05 16:34:49','2008-10-05 16:34:49'),(436,25,23,'Concrete channeling is being built from the green house off Waiapu Road to where the track first meets the fence.  Strictly speaking it seems to still be closed.','2008-10-05 16:44:21','2008-10-05 16:44:21'),(437,24,23,'Slightly soft in places, but mostly OK. Good work clearing the gorse.','2008-10-05 16:49:29','2008-10-05 16:49:29'),(438,28,23,'Several new drainage channels have been freshly cut.  A couple of them are in awkward places, so might claim the unwary.','2008-10-05 16:56:46','2008-10-05 16:56:46'),(439,3,17,'Wow totally flattened! This used to be a great track. If the second half becomes like the first then this track should drop down a grade. Same thing has been happening at Mt Vic - completely flattened, derooted and graveled on lots of sections.  Good for new riders, but bad for the regulars.','2008-10-08 16:35:26','2008-10-08 16:35:26'),(440,35,17,'Dry and fast. Cool track.','2008-10-11 15:50:42','2008-10-11 15:50:42'),(441,4,17,'Dry and a little dusty.','2008-10-11 15:52:32','2008-10-11 15:52:32'),(442,35,23,'Indeed it has dried out a lot. Now good for climbing.','2008-10-11 19:33:09','2008-10-11 19:33:09'),(443,11,23,'Top section is drying out well.  All good.','2008-10-11 19:34:35','2008-10-11 19:34:35'),(444,5,23,'Lots of dry, loose gravel marbles to spice up some of the corners.','2008-10-11 19:41:01','2008-10-11 19:41:01'),(445,12,23,'So dry that it was actually dusty.','2008-10-11 19:42:18','2008-10-11 19:42:18'),(446,50,23,'A bit rough around the edges.  Due for some maintenance tomorrow.','2008-10-11 19:45:15','2008-10-11 19:45:15'),(447,73,23,'Surface is still a bit soft in places. Watch out for the trees next to the track, they are close and might leap out to grab passing handle bars.','2008-10-11 19:47:47','2008-10-11 19:47:47'),(448,68,23,'A little wet and soft in places, but generally in good condition.','2008-10-11 19:51:30','2008-10-11 19:51:30'),(449,6,23,'Due for some attention tomorrow, though doesn\'t need much to make it all good.','2008-10-11 19:54:33','2008-10-11 19:54:33'),(450,7,23,'Dry and firm.  Recent work has made it flow better than ever.','2008-10-11 19:57:40','2008-10-11 19:57:40'),(451,22,23,'Recent upgrades have taken the flow factor up a notch.  Smooth and fast.','2008-10-11 20:02:09','2008-10-11 20:02:09'),(452,99,17,'One bit washed out near the start of Baked Beans. ','2008-10-12 13:39:04','2008-10-12 13:39:04'),(453,105,17,'Very soft. Some big ruts appearing on many of the switchbacks.','2008-10-12 13:41:22','2008-10-12 13:41:22'),(454,27,17,'There is a large tree right across the track. Its just past the house.','2008-10-13 18:42:26','2008-10-13 18:42:26'),(455,28,17,'Those drainage ditches are a bitch. Especially the one near the bottom. Ran over my buddy and ended up in the gorse when he pulled on the anchors.','2008-10-13 18:44:46','2008-10-13 18:44:46'),(456,29,17,'Was firm and dry except for one boggy spot that may not dry out all summer (bit of #8 solution has been applied to that patch tho). Raining quite heavily now...sigh.','2008-10-16 18:47:33','2008-10-16 18:47:33'),(457,3,23,'Recent maintenance has settled nicely, though has taken the edge off the track.  I liked that edge.','2008-10-18 12:43:20','2008-10-18 12:43:20'),(458,51,23,'Recently graded and gravelled, at least on the southern side, so in good condition.','2008-10-18 12:44:51','2008-10-18 12:44:51'),(459,9,23,'Lower section, just before the paddock, is really quite technical now - being steep with a rocky and rutted surface.','2008-10-18 12:48:06','2008-10-18 12:48:06'),(460,65,23,'Track is barely discernable in the long grass at the [[track:9]] end - clearly not much traffic.  Remainder is in good condition.','2008-10-18 12:50:23','2008-10-18 12:50:23'),(461,10,23,'Seriously deep rut just after [[track:65]] joins.  Lots of loose rocks and other debris on the track, but generally OK.','2008-10-18 12:56:23','2008-10-18 12:56:23'),(462,46,23,'Very close foliage, including gorse and holly. The planks only vaguely resemble a bridge - wouldn\'t trust them.','2008-10-19 21:05:14','2008-10-19 21:05:14'),(463,25,23,'Significant rut forming just below the top of the [[track:28]]. Off to the side though, so not a big issue.','2008-10-19 21:07:08','2008-10-19 21:07:08'),(464,28,23,'On the second attempt the drainage ditches aren\'t as dodgy as they look, provided you keep to the left.','2008-10-19 21:10:12','2008-10-19 21:10:12'),(465,41,23,'Top half, down to [[track:62]], is fine.','2008-10-19 21:11:44','2008-10-19 21:11:44'),(466,62,23,'Three logs on the track to negotiate, along with a low hanging tree at head height.','2008-10-19 21:13:38','2008-10-19 21:13:38'),(467,55,23,'Lots of roots and a few rocks exposed by bikes skidding down the drops and slides.','2008-10-19 21:17:06','2008-10-19 21:17:06'),(468,24,23,'A few roots and rocks getting exposed by wear and tear.','2008-10-19 21:21:56','2008-10-19 21:21:56'),(469,118,23,'Rather muddy across the top, especially around a saddle point that has been deeply cut up by a sizable herd of cattle.  Best to go around that bit.','2008-10-26 09:44:35','2008-10-26 09:44:35'),(470,107,23,'A few minor drainage ruts across the road, but nothing to worry about.','2008-10-26 09:45:40','2008-10-26 09:45:40'),(471,74,23,'Firm and in good condition, despite the rain.','2008-10-26 18:13:15','2008-10-26 18:13:15'),(472,75,23,'Good condition throughout.','2008-10-26 18:14:22','2008-10-26 18:14:22'),(473,77,23,'Getting a bit rugged. Several of the drops have tree roots sticking out in awkward places.','2008-10-26 18:16:10','2008-10-26 18:16:10'),(474,79,23,'Generally good condition.  Liking the new structure - looks intimidating, but rides really well.','2008-10-26 18:20:43','2008-10-26 18:20:43'),(475,78,23,'Bit of mud, a few ruts and lots of exposed tree roots make for an interesting ride.  Tricky in the wet - like today.','2008-10-26 18:22:55','2008-10-26 18:22:55'),(476,109,23,'The middle section, north of the intersection with [[track:136]], is rather messed up by cattle.','2008-10-28 11:10:46','2008-10-28 11:10:46'),(477,134,23,'Bit of a rut infestation halfway between the [[track:135]] turnoff and the track\'s northern end.','2008-10-28 11:12:46','2008-10-28 11:12:46'),(478,135,23,'A few chewed up pieces of track, where the cattle have been active. On the summit of Boulder Hill encountered a crew filming a short film about a mad scientist.  Weird props.','2008-10-30 16:36:38','2008-10-30 16:36:38'),(479,136,23,'Rough and occasionally difficult surface, due to a combination of cattle, recent rain, and steep terrain.','2008-10-28 11:21:07','2008-10-28 11:21:07'),(480,88,23,'Work is underway to clear this track of fallen trees etc, so it should be ridable soon.','2008-10-30 16:34:15','2008-10-30 16:34:15'),(481,67,5,'At 325m at the south end and 825m at the north end ie about 500m to go (still excludes the bit around back of knob).  Thanks to the track pixie I bumped into during the week - our progress has slowed cos of better weather - more riding less building.','2008-11-07 09:08:27','2008-11-07 09:08:27'),(482,1,23,'First section has been groomed - now nice and smooth.','2008-11-08 19:36:57','2008-11-08 19:36:57'),(483,4,23,'Good condition.','2008-11-08 19:39:05','2008-11-08 19:39:05'),(484,12,23,'A few sections of recent digging are a bit soft, but nothing major.','2008-11-08 19:40:26','2008-11-08 19:40:26'),(485,11,23,'Looking good.','2008-11-08 19:41:07','2008-11-08 19:41:07'),(486,88,23,'Cleared and tidied except for several large trees that are marked for cutting by the Council.','2008-11-08 19:43:52','2008-11-08 19:43:52'),(487,105,23,'Bottom section, up to the green hut, is solid.  The rest is mushy, rutted and generally cut up from last week\'s PNP race. There is a new, more sustainable, track section under development just above the green hut.','2008-11-09 20:22:40','2008-11-09 20:22:40'),(488,142,23,'New track with a challenging surface consisting of smooth clay slides and soft sections.','2008-11-09 21:01:55','2008-11-09 21:01:55'),(489,111,23,'Dry and firm, so no worries.','2008-11-09 21:14:02','2008-11-09 21:14:02'),(490,112,23,'In good condition, apart from lots of sheep leaving their mark.','2008-11-09 21:18:17','2008-11-09 21:18:17'),(491,143,23,'Deep ruts and lots of loose rocks in places, especially on the final descent to the gate just before [[track:102]].','2008-11-09 21:49:02','2008-11-09 21:49:02'),(492,145,23,'Dry and smooth, apart from a slightly rutted hairpin near the Charles Plimmer Park end.','2008-11-17 19:43:00','2008-11-17 19:43:00'),(493,147,23,'Recently groomed surface, so all good.','2008-11-17 19:44:11','2008-11-17 19:44:11'),(494,144,23,'Some moderately technical rooty sections, especially the last 200m at the northern end.','2008-11-17 19:46:32','2008-11-17 19:46:32'),(495,146,23,'A couple of deep drains across the track heading down to the velodrome, but only an issue if hit at speed.','2008-11-17 19:48:09','2008-11-17 19:48:09'),(496,148,23,'Much of the western half has been bulldozed recently, leaving a clear but soft surface.  Most of the eastern half is overgrown with long grass.','2008-11-17 20:13:14','2008-11-17 20:13:14'),(497,149,23,'[[track:148]] end has been cleared by bulldozer.  The rest is a bit overgrown.','2008-11-17 20:20:14','2008-11-17 20:20:14'),(498,150,23,'Watch out for the patches of stinging plants, some of which protrude into the track.','2008-11-17 20:41:30','2008-11-17 20:41:30'),(499,151,23,'Upper sections in good condition.  Deeply rutted on the lower sections down towards [[track:150]].','2008-11-17 20:46:18','2008-11-17 20:46:18'),(500,152,23,'Generally good condition, though the grass is getting a bit long in places.','2008-11-17 20:57:35','2008-11-17 20:57:35'),(501,99,23,'Enthusiastic spring growth encroaching on the track, especially at the Cornish Street end.','2008-11-17 21:00:41','2008-11-17 21:00:41'),(502,67,5,'The track pixie has been on steroids and punched the track well south of the 800m marker.  The girls are very excited and have threatened to leave some baking in the gloves container!  Just about to hit a rock outcrop.  Will do a revised measure up at both ends at some stage.','2008-11-18 09:04:44','2008-11-18 09:04:44'),(503,67,23,'Looking good.  I wandered around with the GPS and noted that the north-south gap is 470m, with another 360m around the knob. Updated the map accordingly. ','2008-11-19 20:14:58','2008-11-19 20:14:58'),(504,153,23,'Dry and smooth, with a nice flow.  Some of the berms are a bit soft, even if only slightly off the beaten track.','2008-11-22 21:17:04','2008-11-22 21:17:04'),(505,154,23,'Mud patch at the creek culvert, otherwise all good.','2008-11-22 21:28:06','2008-11-22 21:28:06'),(506,105,23,'Dry and firm throughout.  Some of the switchbacks still have deep ruts, but manageable when dry.','2008-11-22 21:55:19','2008-11-22 21:55:19'),(507,113,23,'Plenty of new grass growth, especially on the lower half.  Could be tricky, as the grass hides the rocks and ruts underneath.','2008-11-22 21:57:21','2008-11-22 21:57:21'),(508,155,23,'Much of the track is barely discernable, especially in the middle section, with markers being few and far between.','2008-11-22 22:14:05','2008-11-22 22:14:05'),(509,116,23,'Dry and hence surprisingly ridable, albeit slowly and carefully.','2008-11-22 22:29:31','2008-11-22 22:29:31'),(510,103,23,'Upper section is getting a bit overgrown. Middle section, near [[track:156]], is lined with hundreds of plants in protective plastic bags - quite surreal.','2008-11-23 20:42:03','2008-11-23 20:42:03'),(511,156,23,'The northern half has grass disguising a bumpy surface that has been deeply cut up by cattle during some particularly wet era.','2008-11-23 20:48:45','2008-11-23 20:48:45'),(512,157,23,'Generally in good condition.  Watch out for the thistle-lined section of sheep track just above the twin power transmission towers.','2008-11-23 21:12:38','2008-11-23 21:12:38'),(513,158,23,'Takapu section has lots of loose stone chip on a firm base - great for drifty cornering, intentionally or otherwise.','2008-11-24 18:32:57','2008-11-24 18:32:57'),(514,31,23,'Dry and firm.  Generally good throughout.','2008-11-29 20:35:18','2008-11-29 20:35:18'),(515,71,23,'Quite overgrown, especially at the top.  Easy to not realise that the track is there, even if you\'re looking for it.','2008-11-29 20:38:13','2008-11-29 20:38:13'),(516,25,23,'Steep sections just to the west of [[track:34]] are quite cut up, with a rough rocky surface.','2008-11-29 20:42:55','2008-11-29 20:42:55'),(517,174,23,'Very narrow, with lots of encroaching vegetation - some with prickles.','2008-11-29 21:59:17','2008-11-29 21:59:17'),(518,52,23,'Top half is dry with lots of loose marbles. The bottom half exchanges stones for tree roots and low hanging branches.','2008-11-30 20:33:05','2008-11-30 20:33:05'),(519,69,23,'The final drop looks near vertical when viewed from the top. No apparent traffic on the last section, which is completely camouflaged from the [[track:52]] side by undisturbed foliage.','2008-11-30 20:51:15','2008-11-30 20:51:15'),(520,70,23,'Getting overgrown, with a lining of knee high gorse on both sides for most of the way.','2008-11-30 21:01:44','2008-11-30 21:01:44'),(521,74,23,'Dry and firm.  All good.','2008-12-06 22:17:33','2008-12-06 22:17:33'),(522,75,23,'A couple of trees hanging over the track - one on the original section and another on the extension.  Both are high enough to be not much of a problem.','2008-12-06 22:19:25','2008-12-06 22:19:25'),(523,81,23,'Good condition between [[track:75]] and [[track:162]].','2008-12-06 22:21:14','2008-12-06 22:21:14'),(524,162,23,'Dry and largely free from loose gravel, hence mostly ridable.','2008-12-06 22:25:11','2008-12-06 22:25:11'),(526,80,23,'New track segment is brilliant - heaps better than the old one.','2008-12-07 11:17:36','2008-12-07 11:17:36'),(527,29,52,'Grass is starting to get pretty long up the top, but otherwise all good. That little boggy patch is still there and shows no signs of drying out. ','2008-12-12 13:13:35','2008-12-12 13:13:35'),(528,176,23,'Looking good so far.  Wide and easy track up to the head of the valley.','2008-12-12 14:04:31','2008-12-12 14:04:31'),(530,67,5,'The track pixies (at least 4 different guys) have been main lining the good stuff and added heaps on benched track in the last couple of weeks eg 35m in the last 2 days!  At about 675m at the north end and 350 at the south so 325 to go!!!','2008-12-14 21:49:06','2008-12-14 21:49:06'),(531,32,23,'From the Makara Road end through to [[track:177]] is generally in good condition. A few rough rocky patches emerging in places. There is an occasional cattle landmine, but not enough to be of concern.','2008-12-15 21:16:07','2008-12-15 21:16:07'),(532,177,23,'Freshly mown grass in the upper sections made for a fast descent and a smooth climb. The latch on the top-most gate was jammed shut.','2008-12-15 21:21:36','2008-12-15 21:21:36'),(533,178,23,'A few soft patches where there has been recent digging, but otherwise a firm hard-packed dirt surface.','2008-12-15 21:26:21','2008-12-15 21:26:21'),(534,29,23,'Lots of enthusiastic vegetation, including gorse and blackberry, encroaching on the track.','2008-12-20 22:19:25','2008-12-20 22:19:25'),(535,30,23,'Some dodgy sections following heavy rain this morning.  Also a bit overgrown in places. That is, business as usual.','2008-12-20 22:22:43','2008-12-20 22:22:43'),(536,35,23,'Some encroaching vegetation, including gorse, near the top. The chicane is easily ridable in both directions.','2008-12-20 22:26:06','2008-12-20 22:26:06'),(537,88,23,'All clear!  The fallen trees have been cut away, so the whole track is ridable.','2008-12-20 22:27:31','2008-12-20 22:27:31'),(538,190,23,'This is a new track that has been freshly excavated.  The surface is still settling, currently consisting of soft soil and loose rock throughout.','2008-12-21 22:15:34','2008-12-21 22:15:34'),(539,148,23,'Most of the upper part of the eastern half has been replaced by the new [[track:190]] track. The western half has been substantially realigned, currently giving it a soft surface.','2008-12-21 22:24:55','2008-12-21 22:24:55'),(540,149,23,'Excavated throughout, so much of the surface is raw with soft soil, loose rocks, and protruding sticks. A couple of the creek crossings are a bit abrupt, making them difficult to ride.','2008-12-21 22:28:15','2008-12-21 22:28:15'),(541,100,23,'There\'s been recent digging on the 50m section from the top of [[track:148]], just below the summit, down to the gate at the end of [[track:152]].','2008-12-21 22:31:58','2008-12-21 22:31:58'),(542,166,23,'Noted in passing that the top section, off Horokiwi Road, has been recently mown.  I didn\'t venture any further to see how far the work went.','2008-12-21 22:34:14','2008-12-21 22:34:14'),(543,11,17,'Getting overgrown.','2008-12-22 11:22:23','2008-12-22 11:22:23'),(544,189,23,'Clearly had a bit of maintenance recently, so all good.','2008-12-22 21:20:58','2008-12-22 21:20:58'),(545,182,23,'Some fresh digging in places, so quite soft. There are also a few close trees to watch out for.','2008-12-22 21:42:10','2008-12-22 21:42:10'),(546,183,23,'There was a bunch of ferns and vines across the track, which I moved out of the way.','2008-12-22 21:43:28','2008-12-22 21:43:28'),(547,188,23,'Top section is almost completely overgrown.','2008-12-22 21:44:48','2008-12-22 21:44:48'),(548,187,23,'The zig-zag section is slippery bare dirt, so difficult to walk up when wet.','2008-12-22 21:46:33','2008-12-22 21:46:33'),(549,43,23,'Lots of bird song in the early evening - very pleasant. The track is a bit soft in places, with a bit of rain recently.  Watch out for the long hanging vines, which can be difficult to see.','2008-12-22 21:49:29','2008-12-22 21:49:29'),(550,186,23,'A bit of erosion where the track drops down from the upper car park, otherwise all good.','2008-12-22 21:51:45','2008-12-22 21:51:45'),(551,184,23,'Had a bit of smoothing work on the track surface recently, so looking good.','2008-12-22 21:52:44','2008-12-22 21:52:44'),(552,181,23,'All good.','2008-12-22 21:53:59','2008-12-22 21:53:59'),(553,180,23,'A few rocks starting to emerge in places, but generally in good condition.','2008-12-22 21:55:01','2008-12-22 21:55:01'),(554,185,23,'Fresh digging on the new entry/exit off Wrights Hill Road is still a little soft. A few new shallow drains have been dug across the track, but no worries.','2008-12-22 21:57:43','2008-12-22 21:57:43'),(555,105,17,'Still slippery on clay corners even after a few days of sun. More a problem going up than down.','2008-12-24 08:33:58','2008-12-24 08:33:58'),(556,1,23,'Lots of fern fronds encroaching on the track.','2008-12-25 21:17:15','2008-12-25 21:17:15'),(557,2,23,'A little overgrown, but otherwise all good.','2008-12-25 21:17:53','2008-12-25 21:17:53'),(558,3,23,'Eastern half is smooth and fast with a nice flow, but you\'ll get a lashing from the long grass. Western half also has some long grass, plus a bit of gorse.','2008-12-25 21:19:50','2008-12-25 21:19:50'),(559,4,23,'A few puddles, but firm underneath so no problems.','2008-12-25 21:20:44','2008-12-25 21:20:44'),(560,5,23,'Seems to be getting more rocky and difficult. Easier lines are emerging around some of the trickier parts.','2008-12-25 21:22:08','2008-12-25 21:22:08'),(561,50,23,'All good. Much easier than [[track:5]] at the moment.','2008-12-25 21:25:19','2008-12-25 21:25:19'),(562,6,23,'Looking good. Flows well, with just a hint of encroaching vegetation.','2008-12-25 21:25:35','2008-12-25 21:25:35'),(563,7,23,'Sweet, sensuous, smooth singletrack.','2008-12-25 21:27:20','2008-12-25 21:27:20'),(564,22,23,'Developing a few too many bumps to flow well, though nothing major.','2008-12-25 21:30:30','2008-12-25 21:30:30'),(565,8,23,'Difficult alternative is deeply rutted towards the bottom, but that\'s the idea. The rest seems to be going for that rough, weathered look - apart from the top, which is nicely smooth.','2008-12-25 21:34:01','2008-12-25 21:34:01'),(566,193,23,'Firm and smooth throughout. The 2.5km section ending at Totara Park Road has a new tarseal surface that is extremely sticky on a hot summer\'s afternoon.','2008-12-28 15:26:09','2008-12-28 15:26:09'),(567,198,23,'Singletrack section up from Tulsa Park is in good condition.','2008-12-28 15:27:56','2008-12-28 15:27:56'),(568,197,23,'Lots of low hanging trees and ferns - easy to avoid when ascending, but might be a hazard when descending. The surface is in good condition, with only a few small ruts and bumps along the way.','2008-12-28 15:46:19','2008-12-28 15:46:19'),(569,199,23,'Section between the top of [[track:197]] and the western end, including Cannon Trig, is smooth and well groomed.','2008-12-28 15:33:30','2008-12-28 15:33:30'),(570,195,23,'Recently reconstructed to facilitate logging and replanting in the Lindsay Block. Some of the surface has a very coarse angular rock base that it is best to avoid riding on.[[br]]\nCurrently ends in an area that is badly chewed up by recent logging operations.[[br]]Instead of being a dead-end, there might be a track to the east towards Birchville...','2008-12-28 15:43:47','2008-12-28 15:43:47'),(571,200,23,'Shallow to moderate ruts, though too steep to retain many loose stones on the mostly hard clay and rock surface.','2008-12-29 13:22:12','2008-12-29 13:22:12'),(572,201,23,'Many of the steep bits are deeply rutted. Some of the troughs have  semi-permanent mud puddles. About 0.3km after passing a fire fighting pond, the track becomes increasingly overgrown - mostly with gorse. Bare arms and legs will not fare well.','2008-12-29 13:07:12','2008-12-29 13:07:12'),(573,81,23,'A few ruts and lots of exposed rock embedded in the road, along the section between [[track:200]] and the [[track:201]] intersection.','2008-12-29 13:19:58','2008-12-29 13:19:58'),(574,205,23,'Smooth and easy through the reserve. The singletrack section is a little boggy in a couple of places, and there is a small step down in the middle.','2008-12-30 14:24:01','2008-12-30 14:24:01'),(575,202,23,'Firm surface, with plenty of grip for climbing. The whole track is on the side of a steep hill, so it seems to drain well.','2008-12-30 14:42:02','2008-12-30 14:42:02'),(576,203,23,'Recent rain has washed much of the loose gravel down the steep eastern slopes, forming deep piles on the not-so-steep bits. The short singletrack section at the western end has some encroaching vegetation, including large gorse bushes.','2008-12-30 15:25:44','2008-12-30 15:25:44'),(577,204,23,'Leafy track surface with a few exposed tree roots and some small drops (if descending).','2008-12-30 16:12:30','2008-12-30 16:12:30'),(578,126,23,'A little overgrown in a couple of places with long grass and thistle, though much of the stopbank section has been recently mown.','2009-01-04 10:14:42','2009-01-04 10:14:42'),(579,214,23,'From the top it looks rather overgrown, though probably still rideable.','2009-01-04 12:12:28','2009-01-04 12:12:28'),(580,210,23,'Good condition.  A fair amount of loose gravel in some places, which makes for fun downhill cornering at speed.','2009-01-04 12:14:38','2009-01-04 12:14:38'),(581,207,23,'A bit rough and rutted on some of the steeper sections, but generally OK.','2009-01-04 12:15:26','2009-01-04 12:15:26'),(582,206,23,'Soft and muddy in a few places. Near the State Highway 2 end there are several fallen trees hanging precariously over the track - they are held by trees on the other side of the track.','2009-01-04 12:19:39','2009-01-04 12:19:39'),(583,208,23,'Clear and in good condition, though probably won\'t stay like that if the logging trucks have their way.','2009-01-04 12:21:39','2009-01-04 12:21:39'),(584,209,23,'Surface is good.  Getting a little overgrown along the edges, though the road is wide enough to not be a problem.','2009-01-04 12:23:27','2009-01-04 12:23:27'),(585,215,23,'There\'s a large and deep puddle near the [[track:206]] end, though easy enough to go around.','2009-01-04 12:39:37','2009-01-04 12:39:37'),(586,61,63,'Dry, steep and a fair bit of gorse, sheep track to the bottom is a bit hard to find, starts in the dip before the bunkers.','2009-01-04 12:55:19','2009-01-04 12:55:19'),(587,60,63,'Top section before the gate is quite grassy. Ended up on private land at the end of Bata Pl with diggers and a 2m fence with a locked gate (~6pm Saturday), got bike over fence by standing on a rock and lowering it down the other side, then jumped the fence.','2009-01-04 13:12:27','2009-01-04 13:12:27'),(588,23,63,'Dry, some sections with loose stuff.','2009-01-04 13:07:09','2009-01-04 13:07:09'),(589,217,23,'The gravel surface is remarkably smooth, consisting of small stone chip on a firm base.','2009-01-05 11:14:34','2009-01-05 11:14:34'),(590,218,23,'Typical back country gravel road. Deeply scoured drains along the roadside reflect the high rainfall and steep catchment of the area, though the road itself is mostly rut-free.','2009-01-05 11:17:45','2009-01-05 11:17:45'),(591,221,23,'Somewhat rough and getting a little overgrown, especially towards the northeastern end.','2009-01-05 11:18:50','2009-01-05 11:18:50'),(592,219,23,'Starting to get overgrown, but looks like it gets a regular trim.','2009-01-05 11:23:25','2009-01-05 11:23:25'),(593,220,23,'Very overgrown - more so the further you go, eventually becoming impassable.','2009-01-05 11:21:45','2009-01-05 11:21:45'),(594,212,23,'[[link:http://www.doc.govt.nz/parks-and-recreation/plan-and-prepare/alerts/wellington/#incline DOC]] said on 15 October 2008: \"A large piece of the old railway embankment has been washed out ~50 metres on the South end of the Prices Tunnel. Warning signs and flagging tape have been placed around the affected area. Please take extreme caution in this area, especially if riding bikes.\"','2009-01-05 21:04:47','2009-01-05 21:04:47'),(595,41,17,'Bottom section is quite overgrown. Makes a tough climb brutal.','2009-01-07 15:15:21','2009-01-07 15:15:21'),(596,27,17,'Throat grabbing blackberry and leg ripping gorse. You will be blooded riding this track.','2009-01-07 15:17:35','2009-01-07 15:17:35'),(597,67,23,'There\'s a bit more ridable track at the northern end, so the gap has reduced to 300m. More significantly, the gap is starting to be cleared, in a step towards it becoming track. Although not recommended, it is possible to push/carry a bike along the gap.','2009-01-07 21:14:16','2009-01-07 21:14:16'),(598,36,23,'Top section is clear, but the rest is constrained by long grass on both sides - making the track quite narrow in the middle.','2009-01-07 21:24:26','2009-01-07 21:24:26'),(599,25,23,'Surface is quite dry and crumbly. There\'s a deep rut on one of the steep sections halfway between the turbine and the bottom end of [[track:24]].','2009-01-07 21:34:54','2009-01-07 21:34:54'),(600,24,23,'Recent digging has smoothed some parts of the track, though a few exposed rocks and roots remain - especially along the bottom section. Just over 100m from the top there is a new track being cut straight down the hill. Not clear where it is going...','2009-01-07 21:42:21','2009-01-07 21:42:21'),(601,41,63,'Top is pretty good under fairly mature regenerated bush, quite a lot of mahoe roots. Bottom is gorse and weeds, track is well rutted, some deep grooves, corners pretty tight. ','2009-01-11 17:22:36','2009-01-11 17:22:36'),(602,47,63,'Tried to go up through Waimapihi Reserve, a few people were doing a working bee clearing weeds, one lady says \"No Bikes! it says on the sign\". Turned tail ...','2009-01-11 17:35:20','2009-01-11 17:35:20'),(603,10,17,'Swarms of sandflies. You\'ll get a gob full almost every corner...dirty stuff.','2009-01-13 08:19:31','2009-01-13 08:19:31'),(604,28,69,'Right at the top, where it splits from the walking trail is mega tight with overgrowth at the moment.  It was narrower than my bars last night.  Meant not being able to really let go at the top.','2009-01-16 12:19:32','2009-01-16 12:19:32'),(605,222,23,'The grass is of moderate length, which adds a surprising amount of drag on the wheels. Otherwise, all good.','2009-01-16 17:23:25','2009-01-16 17:23:25'),(606,223,23,'The area around the confluence of Black Creek and the Wainuiomata River is quite overgrown. There\'s also a couple of deep channel drains along the northern section.','2009-01-16 19:15:28','2009-01-16 19:15:28'),(607,224,23,'Top 400m is quite overgrown and has progressively deeper ruts the higher you go. One rut is almost wheel deep, so beware. Clambering up the bypass at the top is tricky, even with the rope to provide assistance.','2009-01-16 21:27:42','2009-01-16 21:27:42'),(608,228,23,'Dusty and loose surface in many places thoughout Mt Victoria. Some parts that were overgrown have been trimmed, presumably in preparation for the race on 18 Jan 2009.','2009-01-18 09:43:31','2009-01-18 09:43:31'),(609,144,23,'Dry and dusty. Appears to have been getting a fair bit of use, but still in good condition.','2009-01-17 21:39:57','2009-01-17 21:39:57'),(610,147,23,'Quite dry and loose so traction is less than optimal on some of the climbs, but generally OK.','2009-01-17 21:41:52','2009-01-17 21:41:52'),(611,145,23,'A bit of encroaching long grass, but otherwise all good.','2009-01-17 21:44:27','2009-01-17 21:44:27'),(612,146,23,'Very dusty and a few exposed rocks on the last climb up just before the velodrome.','2009-01-17 21:47:35','2009-01-17 21:47:35'),(613,229,23,'A jump has been built across the track just below the car park entry. It might be temporary, since this section of track is part of the [[track:228]].','2009-01-18 09:07:56','2009-01-18 09:07:56'),(614,230,23,'The grass and scrub has been trimmed and a low tree has been removed, probably in preparation for running the [[track:228]].','2009-01-18 09:12:02','2009-01-18 09:12:02'),(615,231,23,'There\'s a small tree fallen across the track just below Alexandra Road. A bypass is emerging, though it is tricky to negotiate on a bike.','2009-01-18 09:18:50','2009-01-18 09:18:50'),(616,232,23,'Soft on the surface, but firm underneath. The middle straight section has some moderate ruts, but nothing major.','2009-01-19 08:23:32','2009-01-19 08:23:32'),(617,225,23,'Deeply rutted and muddy in many places. Getting overgrown with mature gorse and broom intruding on the track.','2009-01-19 08:26:28','2009-01-19 08:26:28'),(618,226,23,'Northern third is deeply rutted and muddy, while the rest is firm and smooth.','2009-01-19 08:29:14','2009-01-19 08:29:14'),(619,228,63,'Did it the day after the event which was reasonably muddy due to overnight rain. The track is mostly dried out and not too cut up considering the traffic. The steep climb at the end of Stage 3 was un-rideable for me and I chickened out for the ski slope chute in stage 4 and the drop from the grove at the start of stage 6. Other than that rooty sections provide some challenges. Alex park to the dipper is lots of fun.','2009-01-19 15:15:50','2009-01-19 15:15:50'),(620,67,23,'Another 40m of track added from the north. Gap is now 260m.','2009-01-19 21:33:18','2009-01-19 21:33:18'),(621,233,23,'A few moderate ruts and lots of loose rocks for sliding down the steep bits and making the first part of the climb out to [[track:234]] very difficult. Also some long grass and gorse, though nothing major.','2009-01-19 22:19:14','2009-01-19 22:19:14'),(622,234,23,'Medium length dry grass with narrow track of loose rocks in between.','2009-01-19 22:09:43','2009-01-19 22:09:43'),(623,236,23,'Dry and rocky, making for a difficult climb and tricky descent.','2009-01-19 22:11:23','2009-01-19 22:11:23'),(624,235,23,'A fair bit of loose gravel, and a few rocks embedded in the base to watch out for.','2009-01-19 22:12:22','2009-01-19 22:12:22'),(625,39,23,'From [[track:234]] up (yes, up) to the top is in generally good condition. There\'s plenty of loose gravel and just a few shallow to moderate ruts.','2009-01-19 22:14:38','2009-01-19 22:14:38'),(626,228,17,'Worth a trip! Easy to see why the elites rated this course as one of the best on the national circuit. Challenging up and down.  Grade 4-5. Honest climbs and sharp downhill sections with limit testing drops.  Once you drop in it\'s ride it or crash. Could be a few Mt Vic(tims) on this course. Give it a crack, but ride to your skills. ','2009-01-20 18:35:32','2009-01-20 18:35:32'),(627,142,71,'This is NOT for the Faint Hearted in the WET! This Track however is great fun in the DRY. \r\nNice Switchbacks with gradients and Yep some slippery Clay Slides in the bottom half - YEEEE-HAAAAA','2009-01-20 20:43:43','2009-01-20 20:43:43'),(628,104,71,'Nice & quick to the bottom - apart from the gate half way down! Mostly clay all the way.  Makes a nice change instead of riding down stratton street to Danzig! However the track at present needs some gorse cutting work on the lower half- prepare to be needled in the bare arms and legs! (Hoz - U gotta get that cutter out eh!)','2009-01-21 22:16:44','2009-01-21 22:16:44'),(629,153,71,'Difficult in the Wet! Watch the Tree Roots!\r\n100% better in the Dry!','2009-01-20 20:53:24','2009-01-20 20:53:24'),(630,116,71,'Yes as Ian states -Not really a track for the wet. Watch your lines when tackling those chutes too.','2009-01-20 20:57:55','2009-01-20 20:57:55'),(631,139,23,'Did just the singletrack section around the summit - currently very dry with a crumbly rock surface.','2009-01-25 12:15:26','2009-01-25 12:15:26'),(632,30,17,'In good condition.  Some of the semi-permanent bogs are almost dry. \nGetting narrow in lower section due to erosion of track edges.','2009-01-25 09:45:58','2009-01-25 09:45:58'),(633,29,17,'Overgrown with blackberry.\n\nThe big bog in the middle, that people have laid logs in, has dried right out.','2009-01-25 09:48:34','2009-01-25 09:48:34'),(634,238,23,'Well groomed and generally smooth. A fair bit of loose gravel towards the eastern end, including a few sharp-edged fist-sized rocks to watch out for.','2009-01-25 11:23:04','2009-01-25 11:23:04'),(635,237,23,'Lots of loose gravel on the hill climb section, though on a firm base. Parts of the lower section are roughly sealed.','2009-01-25 11:26:11','2009-01-25 11:26:11'),(636,239,23,'A bit overgrown with long grass and some scrub. Not quite singletrack yet, but working on it.','2009-01-25 11:44:17','2009-01-25 11:44:17'),(637,24,63,'The track is dry and in good condition at the moment.','2009-01-25 16:52:38','2009-01-25 16:52:38'),(638,67,63,'Nice flowing single track, its going to be good when its done.','2009-01-25 16:55:29','2009-01-25 16:55:29'),(639,82,73,'Very dry and tree rooty. Good technical climb.','2009-01-26 12:35:13','2009-01-26 12:35:13'),(640,83,73,'Super dry, steep, rooty and technical - great fun, enjoy it while the dry spell lasts.','2009-01-26 12:36:32','2009-01-26 12:36:32'),(641,87,73,'Dry, dusty and fast - a few gorse bushes hanging into the track and attacking unprotected arms/legs but otherwise all good.','2009-01-26 12:38:26','2009-01-26 12:38:26'),(642,60,74,'Top section now very grassy. Bottom 700m section from hard left is freshly metalled. OK if leg out on corners but loose. Bata Pl gate locked at 6pm Monday.','2009-01-26 18:51:31','2009-01-26 18:51:31'),(643,67,5,'A bit more rideable track has been added but most recent work has been on opening up the blazed track between the track ends.  Have removed a bunch of trees and filled in holes etc to make it easier for the bike carry.  It takes 4mins to walk so its now prob worthwhile doing that.  I\'ll continue to improve the \'carry\' to make it easier.','2009-01-28 14:01:39','2009-01-28 14:01:39'),(644,228,63,'They are busy building a footpath near the toilets on Stage 2. This is a great track to upskill on.','2009-01-28 23:09:35','2009-01-28 23:09:35'),(645,62,63,'Four big Gum tree logs to negotiate at the start. The rest of the track is under fairly mature mahoe. Some patches of mahoe roots to negotiate. Leaf litter covers most of the track.','2009-01-29 22:25:20','2009-01-29 22:25:20'),(646,39,63,'Gorse encroaching especially on the bottom half. ','2009-01-29 22:29:01','2009-01-29 22:29:01'),(647,67,63,'Its now possible to walk with your bike on your shoulder the whole way through the unfinished section.','2009-01-29 22:41:09','2009-01-29 22:41:09'),(648,191,63,'Still a bit of mud about even in dry conditions. They have dumped fresh rock on the track in quite a few places, will probably be well packed down for the race. Watch out for the dirt bikes and quads.','2009-02-01 16:14:01','2009-02-01 16:14:01'),(649,194,63,'Fun downhill. Pretty dry at the moment, didn\'t notice the permanent mud puddle. A bit rutted in places but generally a smooth downhill ride.','2009-02-01 16:20:42','2009-02-01 16:20:42'),(650,193,63,'The end section between [[track:192]] and [[track:195]] is a decent climb, this section of the track is dry and in good condition. ','2009-02-01 16:27:35','2009-02-01 16:27:35'),(651,192,63,'Dry, gravel, not much shade on a hot day. They have started logging at the top.','2009-02-01 16:39:48','2009-02-01 16:39:48'),(652,74,63,'Excellent uphill single track, in good condition. I would classify it Intermediate due to narrowness, steep dropoffs and close trees in places. Well worth a visit.','2009-02-01 16:34:50','2009-02-01 16:34:50'),(653,75,63,'Excellent single track, in good condition currently.','2009-02-01 16:36:32','2009-02-01 16:36:32'),(654,78,63,'Dry, super downhill, lots of fun (inc 491). Rocks, then roots then fast clay.','2009-02-01 16:38:52','2009-02-01 16:38:52'),(655,240,23,'All good. Firm gravel and rock surface throughout.','2009-02-01 20:57:17','2009-02-01 20:57:17'),(656,241,23,'Tidy gravel track with several tight switchbacks. Looks to have had a bit of recent work, smoothing a few sections.','2009-02-01 20:59:02','2009-02-01 20:59:02'),(657,243,23,'Jumps are all in good condition - clearly had a lot of work put into forming the jumps. Good stuff.','2009-02-01 21:01:20','2009-02-01 21:01:20'),(658,242,23,'Sealed driveway. No potholes. That is all.','2009-02-01 21:02:25','2009-02-01 21:02:25'),(659,244,23,'Tricky start at the Kotinga Street end, especially if cars are parked in the way.  Also a little boggy in the middle.','2009-02-01 21:04:20','2009-02-01 21:04:20'),(660,67,5,'Gap down to about 200m with more benching done at both ends.  More trees out in the gap so the bike push is easier and quicker.','2009-02-03 15:37:06','2009-02-03 15:37:06'),(661,67,5,'Track pixies have knocked off more track at the north end (good quality track!).  A crude track has been cut through most of the gap from the south end - its a bit like T3.  Bike push is down to about 1min. No more trees in the way!','2009-02-05 14:08:04','2009-02-05 14:08:04'),(662,67,5,'Its all rideable!!!!  Sparrow and I finished the rough track to connect it all up.  Theres about 150m thats fairly \'raw\' in places but give it a nudge.  Prob take a month or so to bench the last bit to a good standard.','2009-02-11 18:18:36','2009-02-11 18:18:36'),(663,67,74,'Yep all connected up for after work ride yesterday. Cheers lads. Its got good flowy bits like sally alley and carparts. Recommended to get to Hawkins','2009-02-12 10:22:43','2009-02-12 10:22:43'),(664,166,83,'Section from last pylon to top is mainly overgrown gorse. So steep and overgrown that at times track is hard to see. Definitely not rideable up or down.','2009-02-12 12:45:48','2009-02-12 12:45:48'),(665,79,73,'Not as dry as it has been but still very firm lower down once you get out of the trees. Watch the roots in the top half they are really slippy after the recent rain. A couple of ruts forming in the usual places but nothing too major.','2009-02-12 15:40:59','2009-02-12 15:40:59'),(666,77,73,'Track has been tidied up really nicely by the trail pixies, nice and flowy with the concrete pipe across the track at the top now buried. Fairly grippy with a couple of minor puddles in places but that may have changed with all the rain today!','2009-02-12 15:41:18','2009-02-12 15:41:18'),(667,74,73,'Undergrowth has been trimmed back and some of the corners tidied up. Riding well.','2009-02-12 15:41:41','2009-02-12 15:41:41'),(668,75,73,'Riding nicely. Recent rain has drained off and the track is in great nick.','2009-02-12 15:42:01','2009-02-12 15:42:01'),(669,80,73,'Some gravel has been laid in places which is still bedding in so a bit soft. Otherwise all good.','2009-02-12 15:42:21','2009-02-12 15:42:21'),(670,67,88,'Well done guys, stunning piece of track you have built. I rode the track for the first time on Sunday (South to North) and it almost made riding up the Tip Track worth while, almost.','2009-02-24 09:47:42','2009-02-24 09:47:42'),(671,62,63,'Slippery roots going up.','2009-02-26 20:49:37','2009-02-26 20:49:37'),(672,41,63,'Slippery roots going up top half.','2009-02-26 20:49:57','2009-02-26 20:49:57'),(673,34,63,'Cover is dense so if you do it at twilight its going to be dark, some very tight switchbacks.','2009-02-26 20:53:29','2009-02-26 20:53:29'),(674,31,63,'Good condition, not much mud.','2009-02-26 20:54:54','2009-02-26 20:54:54'),(675,1,23,'Koru Wet Feet is currently closed, presumably for construction of the bridge over Karori Stream.','2009-02-28 14:24:13','2009-02-28 14:24:13'),(676,2,23,'Trimmed well back, so all good.','2009-02-28 14:25:54','2009-02-28 14:25:54'),(677,3,23,'In good condition - clear and smooth.','2009-02-28 14:26:48','2009-02-28 14:26:48'),(678,4,23,'Near the lower end of the track a couple of the wooden drainage channels are becoming exposed, each of which is now a small step up.  Otherwise all good.','2009-02-28 14:29:29','2009-02-28 14:29:29'),(679,12,23,'The track is riding well, despite the heavy rain today.  Also saw a family of goats off the track, near the step down.','2009-02-28 15:08:32','2009-02-28 15:08:32'),(680,35,23,'The track is in good condition, though the mud on the down hill side of the chicane is quite slippery.  There is a new sign at the top about branches being placed across the track - see \'Other notes\'.','2009-02-28 15:50:07','2009-02-28 15:50:07'),(681,11,23,'Generally clear, though the trimmed gorse scattered on the track might be a puncture hazard when it dries out.','2009-02-28 15:49:42','2009-02-28 15:49:42'),(682,249,23,'A little soft, with bare dirt and rock surface. Plenty of tyre marks indicating recent use.','2009-03-01 20:25:25','2009-03-01 20:25:25'),(683,251,23,'Generally firm surface throughout, with loose rocks most of the way and just a couple of slightly boggy bits.','2009-03-01 20:26:01','2009-03-01 20:26:01'),(684,250,23,'Mostly firm underneath, though a little soft on top following heavy rain over the last couple of days.','2009-03-01 20:27:22','2009-03-01 20:27:22'),(685,27,63,'The gorse is taking over, your arms will bleed.','2009-03-03 10:25:15','2009-03-03 10:25:15'),(686,24,63,'Muddy (unsurprisingly).','2009-03-03 10:26:38','2009-03-03 10:26:38'),(687,81,23,'There\'s a new culvert 50m north of the southern end of [[track:162]]. A couple of culverts near [[track:253]] have broken concrete and steel reinforcing poking through the road surface. Otherwise all good between [[track:162]] and [[track:253]].','2009-03-07 21:42:18','2009-03-07 21:42:18'),(688,162,23,'Deep, deep rut at the northern end - partly filled with loose rocks, but very soft so beware.','2009-03-07 21:45:27','2009-03-07 21:45:27'),(689,253,23,'Deep ruts on all of the steeper sections. Some loose gravel in a few places. Otherwise mostly a smooth, hard-packed clay surface.','2009-03-07 21:53:47','2009-03-07 21:53:47'),(690,254,23,'Deeply gouged surface that makes for a fun and challenging descent. The good news is that it is too steep for much loose material to persist.','2009-03-07 21:50:43','2009-03-07 21:50:43'),(691,257,23,'Hard-packed gravel surface, except for a few very soft sandy patches where the dunes have drifted over the track.','2009-03-13 13:06:53','2009-03-13 13:06:53'),(692,258,23,'Generally firm gravel surface, though some sand sections to watch out for.','2009-03-13 13:39:19','2009-03-13 13:39:19'),(693,259,23,'Mostly firm gravel surface, with a few sections of mown grass.  Watch out for the occasional sand trap.','2009-03-13 14:21:04','2009-03-13 14:21:04'),(694,260,23,'Less than 0.2km from the northern end is a 30cm drop into a sand pit, so watch out for that. Otherwise all good.','2009-03-13 14:47:20','2009-03-13 14:47:20'),(696,264,23,'Mostly short grass surface, with some soft sand and lots of \"horse apples\" - it is a horse trekking track after all.','2009-03-13 16:08:54','2009-03-13 16:08:54'),(697,263,23,'Short grass along the southern segment and alongside the Wainui Stream. Note the detour inland at the southern end of the bridge, as shown on the map, to avoid riding on the beach.','2009-03-13 16:36:42','2009-03-13 16:36:42'),(698,265,23,'Nice to have some shade under the trees alongside the Wainui Stream - shade is rare in [[area:21]] but sought after on a sunny day.','2009-03-13 16:55:47','2009-03-13 16:55:47'),(699,261,23,'The grass was getting a bit long, but otherwise all good.','2009-03-13 17:50:36','2009-03-13 17:50:36'),(700,262,23,'Encountered a large herd of young bulls, who weren\'t keen on letting me through. I wasn\'t sure if they were aggressive or merely curious, but didn\'t wait around to find out.','2009-03-13 18:27:51','2009-03-13 18:27:51'),(702,266,23,'Just on the [[track:257]] side of the summit bench seat there are a few steps. They have become eroded and so the track has collapsed into a sand trap for a few metres.','2009-03-13 20:01:35','2009-03-13 20:01:35'),(703,267,23,'Clumpy grass surface, probably cut up by horse trekkers, but still easily ridable.','2009-03-13 20:23:28','2009-03-13 20:23:28'),(704,65,92,'DH entry from South K Road is just nasty. Track is totally over grown.  \n\nEdge of PBL is very loose in some places.\n\n\n','2009-03-14 08:48:23','2009-03-14 08:48:23'),(705,27,92,'Track closed for \'tree maintenance\'. Probably fixing the big pit at the bottom where tree was uprooted last year.','2009-03-14 08:49:21','2009-03-14 08:49:21'),(706,62,92,'Four logs still blocking track.  Not enough chain-ring clearance to hop first or 4th.','2009-03-14 08:51:29','2009-03-14 08:51:29'),(707,41,92,'Lower part has been trimmed. Makes climb a little easier, but those ever present ruts on the switchback always looking to give you the beat down.','2009-03-14 08:54:47','2009-03-14 08:54:47'),(708,8,92,'Difficult section is getting gnarlier due to water run off.  First shoot slightly obscured by a well placed fern. Rest of the track is doing pretty well considering it takes ages to dry out after rain.','2009-03-14 09:06:49','2009-03-14 09:06:49'),(709,9,92,'Trimmed back the SK Road exit from PBL out.','2009-03-15 10:26:47','2009-03-15 10:26:47'),(710,273,23,'Smooth gravel path in fine condition.','2009-03-15 19:44:14','2009-03-15 19:44:14'),(711,275,23,'Mostly firm forestry track, with an occasional muddy patch between the coating of pine needles.','2009-03-15 19:49:43','2009-03-15 19:49:43'),(712,276,23,'Eastern section has a firm gravel surface. The western section is a smooth forestry track.','2009-03-15 19:50:49','2009-03-15 19:50:49'),(713,274,23,'Several small pine trees across the track at about the halfway point are easy to step over. But a massive fallen pine near the northern-most point takes some effort to climb over.[[br]]Steep section at the northern end is deeply rutted with lots of loose rocks.','2009-03-15 19:58:38','2009-03-15 19:58:38'),(714,277,23,'Rough and rocky surface makes for an interesting v