 a blast. Well done guys - good build. Thanks','2009-05-01 18:53:16','2009-05-01 18:53:16'),(794,32,73,'Makara Rd to KauKau - mostly dry /damp and all rideable. No mud. Loving the new cattle stops!','2009-05-03 15:46:47','2009-05-03 15:46:47'),(795,10,92,'Watch out for the still born goat and dead mother. On bridge as the DH starts to climb up to the link.','2009-05-03 18:43:59','2009-05-03 18:43:59'),(796,294,23,'Updated the map with a GPS log from both ends. So far, blazing from the northern end is 0.21km long and from the southern end is another 0.92km.\n','2009-05-03 19:56:12','2009-05-03 19:56:12'),(797,25,23,'Beware of the rut halfway between the turbine and the bottom end of [[track:24]] â€“ it is nearing canyon proportions.','2009-05-03 19:54:57','2009-05-03 19:54:57'),(798,67,59,'In good nick considering a week solid week of rain. One section has become a stream but all good other than that.','2009-05-09 19:58:50','2009-05-09 19:58:50'),(799,39,59,'WCC track \"improvement\" seems to involve widening and flattening of track :( ','2009-05-09 20:34:58','2009-05-09 20:34:58'),(800,302,23,'Grassy bits are firm and reasonably smooth, so all good.','2009-05-10 11:53:32','2009-05-10 11:53:32'),(801,307,23,'Trimmed well back, making the track quite wide. The edges have mown gorse, so might be a puncture hazard.','2009-05-10 11:55:39','2009-05-10 11:55:39'),(802,304,23,'Some parts on the western side are quite indistinct, so watch out for the yellow marker discs attached to trees along the way.','2009-05-10 11:59:35','2009-05-10 11:59:35'),(803,310,23,'Lots of rooty and rocky goodness heading down to the hairpin bend. The baboons were especially vocal around feeding time.','2009-05-10 12:01:32','2009-05-10 12:01:32'),(804,305,23,'The bottom (northern) end is quite soggy following heavy rain over the last few days.','2009-05-10 12:02:58','2009-05-10 12:02:58'),(805,311,23,'The grass is short and well trimmed, but still provides a fair bit of rolling resistance when cl