d.','2009-08-16 10:37:51','2009-08-16 10:37:51'),(983,35,92,'A bit chewed up particularly muddy near the tree stump by pass.','2009-08-16 13:51:25','2009-08-16 13:51:25'),(984,560,23,'Horrible! Much of the track has been chewed up by a bulldozer, leaving a very soft surface. The trail of destruction includes a track surface littered with mangled gorse bushes sticking out of the ground at all angles, ready to snag anything passing by. The dozer hasn\'t made it to the eastern end (yet), so that section of track is overgrown with blackberry and gorse.','2009-08-16 19:51:25','2009-08-16 19:51:59'),(985,101,23,'The bottom 400m of road has an almost continuous rut running down one side â€“ ranging in depth from mild to yawning abyss.','2009-08-16 19:58:04','2009-08-16 19:58:04'),(986,106,23,'[[track:101]] end is well trimmed. Climbing up from the creek there are some deep ruts and the track has been a bit chewed up by a roaming bulldozer.','2009-08-16 20:05:54','2009-08-16 20:05:54'),(987,346,92,'In great condition given rainfall.','2009-08-18 20:42:22','2009-08-18 20:42:22'),(988,337,92,'Very boggy. It\' unlikely you\'ll be able to climb it at the moment even if you are running tractor tires.','2009-08-18 20:43:46','2009-08-19 21:29:02'),(989,508,139,'Update: As of today, the track is now 100% rideable, though it is still slippery and pig-rooted in places.  Welcome back one of the local greats!','2009-08-22 18:03:43','2009-08-22 18:03:43'),(990,105,92,'As dry as I\'ve seen it in ages. Clay corners are still as slick as ever.','2009-08-23 14:23:15','2009-08-23 14:23:15'),(991,150,92,'Stream is low and most of the track is firm and dry. Gotta love Baked Beans (on toast)!','2009-08-23 14:25:54','2009-08-23 19:51:23'),(992,110,92,'As Ian notes erosion has made the drainage boxes far more prominent. There are some you can ride over, some you can ride around and others...','2009-08-23 14:29:53','2009-08-23 14:29:53'),(993,27,144,'Easy? By whose standards?  Very narrow in parts, slick when wet, a few decent ruts.  This would be Intermediate if it were in Makara Peak.','2009-08-24 15:58:59','2009-08-24 15:58:59'),(994,567,23,'There\'s a dead sheep on the track, just as the track climbs out of the valley. Eew.','2009-08-24 21:24:06','2009-08-24 21:24:06'),(995,566,23,'Fine condition â€“ smooth and firm.','2009-08-24 21:24:41','2009-08-24 21:24:41'),(996,143,23,'Some shallow to moderate ruts towards the bottom end, along with a few slippery bare clay patches to watch out for.','2009-08-24 21:26:03','2009-08-24 21:26:20'),(997,102,23,'Valley floor section is in good condition, though if walking then you\'re likely to get wet feet negotiating a couple of the unbridged stream crossings.','2009-08-24 21:28:49','2009-08-24 21:28:49'),(998,565,23,'There are a couple of washouts to negotiate.  The first, at the start of the track, has taken the bank up to the edge of the track. The other is further up the valley and has taken all of the track and then some â€“ it is tricky to bypass, requiring a precarious scramble over exposed tree roots.','2009-08-24 21:32:52','2009-08-24 21:32:52'),(999,27,92,'Easy because its not open for bicycles. It\'s a foot track only. WCC have permitted construction of two new bike tracks on Polhill and the build begins soon. Stay tuned.','2009-08-25 16:53:07','2009-08-25 16:53:07'),(1001,294,121,'For the record the name Barking Emu refers to the ostrichs at the Nth end and the dogs at the Castle closer to the Sth end. We found out they were ostrichs later because they only have 2 toes not 3.','2009-08-26 16:11:13','2009-08-26 16:11:13'),(1002,144,92,'There is a nice little ride around developing on the connector between the  Southern Walkway and the lower NI XC Cup track (on the quite rooty west-east track just south of the velodrome). There has been a try blocking this track for most of the winter.','2009-08-30 18:30:45','2009-08-30 18:30:45'),(1003,339,23,'Nice entry to the tracks behind [[area:6]] â€“ firm, smooth, and