umps were clean. But a tree has fallen between the 2nd and 3rd jumps.','2010-01-19 15:03:04','2010-01-19 15:03:04'),(1237,305,210,'The grass has grown over the edges of the track. It needs a \'cleaning\'. ','2010-01-19 15:04:29','2010-01-19 15:04:29'),(1238,839,92,'Great little number. Fast, firm and fun.','2010-01-21 21:58:00','2010-01-21 21:58:00'),(1239,839,23,'Looks like this will become an excellent track, with nice flow and plenty of bumps and dips to keep things interesting. Length as at 22-01-2010 is 1.13km.','2010-01-23 16:13:04','2010-01-23 16:13:04'),(1240,27,23,'Short section above [[track:851]] is  a bit overgrown, and there\'s a tree across the track at head height just below [[track:36]].','2010-01-23 16:14:30','2010-01-23 16:14:30'),(1241,851,23,'Quite narrow and with soft edges from recent digging. Some parts are very slick after a bit of rain.','2010-01-23 16:16:02','2010-01-23 16:16:02'),(1242,840,23,'Lower (northern) section is a bit overgrown and very slippery after some rain.','2010-01-23 16:16:44','2010-01-23 16:16:44'),(1243,851,92,'Good ride home if you live in Brooklyn. Sure beats being stuck in traffic!','2010-01-24 16:56:51','2010-01-24 16:56:51'),(1245,857,23,'All good â€“ firm, smooth, and well-trimmed.','2010-01-25 14:11:51','2010-01-25 14:11:51'),(1246,167,23,'Firm surface in good condition throughout.','2010-01-25 14:12:41','2010-01-25 14:12:41'),(1247,856,23,'The grass bits are well-trimmed. Expect to get wet feet if crossing the weir after recent rain (though there\'s no reason to cross it, as it doesn\'t go anywhere).','2010-01-25 14:15:06','2010-01-25 14:15:06'),(1248,858,23,'The southern section is dark and dank, under a heavy tree canopy and clearly gets little sunlight. The rest is fine, though the steep descent down the western section is quite slick in the wet.','2010-01-25 14:17:12','2010-01-25 14:17:12'),(1249,851,144,'Awesome new track but not all ride-able yet because of a few narrow parts with branches on the uphill side and a very soft shoulder on the downhill side.','2010-01-26 10:58:06','2010-01-26 10:58:06'),(1250,337,212,'top half still boggy while bottom half is quite dry.  While the track is still boggy its probably a better down hill ride than uphill','2010-01-27 16:33:57','2010-01-27 16:33:57'),(1251,613,23,'Great progress being made on the construction. Currently about 70% done, in terms of being cleared and benched to a rideable standard. Lots of refinement to follow, of course.  The remaining gap, in the middle section close to [[track:5]], is about 510m.','2010-01-30 08:23:58','2010-01-30 08:25:53'),(1252,19,23,'Allington Road end has been thoroughly mown â€“ short back and sides.','2010-01-30 08:27:26','2010-01-30 08:27:26'),(1253,177,23,'Surprisingly devoid of animals around the farm buildings â€“ no ducks, geese, chickens, or anything. Though there were four horses on the track up to [[track:32]]. The track itself is in fine condition.','2010-01-31 12:57:32','2010-01-31 12:57:32'),(1254,40,23,'In good condition, though there\'s a bit of loose gravel to watch out for if descending.','2010-01-31 12:58:48','2010-01-31 12:58:48'),(1255,32,23,'Updated the map to include some newish (ie. circa 2009) sections of single track between [[track:177]] and [[track:40]] that bypass steep sections of farm road. Overall the track is in great condition.','2010-01-31 13:02:16','2010-01-31 13:02:16'),(1256,39,178,'Getting quite overgrown on the last section past the chain gate. Definitely don\'t bother with that single track shortcut near the bottom unless you want to wade through chest high gorse!','2010-01-31 22:36:20','2010-01-31 22:36:20'),(1257,515,216,'Its \'Peaking Ridge\' Steve .. Nice work mapping it though.','2010-01-31 23:31:24','2010-01-31 23:31:24'),(1258,839,59,'Bumped into a local glue sniffer. Track name \'Transient\' makes more sense now :p','2010-02-02 19:45:01','2010-02-02 19:45:01'),(1259,178,92,'Few bogs on the lower part. There are at least two trees on the outs