ots. ','2010-03-20 11:30:14','2010-03-20 11:30:14'),(1370,1,23,'Very dry and firm track surface, in fine condition.','2010-03-21 09:30:43','2010-03-21 09:30:43'),(1371,2,23,'Starting to get a bit rocky and bumpy, adding a bit of spice to a generally great track.','2010-03-21 09:31:30','2010-03-21 09:31:30'),(1372,3,23,'The exit from the rock cutting is becoming quite a step down, so watch out for that.','2010-03-21 09:33:09','2010-03-21 09:33:09'),(1373,4,23,'Business as usual grind up the hill, over a rocky and occasionally loose surface.','2010-03-21 09:34:16','2010-03-21 09:34:16'),(1374,12,23,'Top section has had a bit of trimming.  A bunch of drains have been added, consisting of notches in the outside edge of the track, so watch out for them.','2010-03-21 09:36:06','2010-03-21 09:36:06'),(1375,613,23,'The refinement continues.  The top two switchbacks, in particular, have tremendously improved flow.  Great work.','2010-03-21 09:39:00','2010-03-21 09:39:56'),(1376,50,23,'The protruding rocks are becoming more prominent, so choosing an appropriate line is key to maintaining the flow.','2010-03-21 09:42:10','2010-03-21 09:42:10'),(1377,6,23,'There\'s a small step down developing near the [[track:50]] end.','2010-03-21 09:44:15','2010-03-21 09:44:15'),(1378,7,23,'A couple of the corners have lots of loose gravel on top of a hard dirt surface, which might result in some unintentional drifting.','2010-03-21 09:46:31','2010-03-21 09:46:31'),(1379,22,23,'The step down is becoming more of a jump, as the footing has been eroded by people rolling/skidding down it.','2010-03-21 09:49:40','2010-03-21 09:49:40'),(1380,881,23,'As of last Tuesday evening (16 March 2010) almost half of the track has been roughly benched.  The rest has been piloted and can be walked with care â€“ though watch out for the tree stumps and stinging nettle (both of which will be removed).','2010-03-21 11:11:29','2010-03-21 11:11:29'),(1381,851,23,'The extension through to Aston Fitchett Drive is op