.','2010-03-21 21:18:12','2010-03-21 21:18:12'),(1394,883,23,'Moved this track from [[area:3]] to [[area:2]] to better reflect the geography and relationship with adjacent tracks.','2010-03-24 14:26:49','2010-03-24 14:26:49'),(1395,26,23,'Moved this track from [[area:3]] to [[area:2]] to better reflect the geography and relationship with adjacent tracks.','2010-03-24 14:27:00','2010-03-24 14:27:00'),(1396,24,23,'Moved this track from [[area:3]] to [[area:2]] to better reflect the geography and relationship with adjacent tracks.','2010-03-24 14:27:12','2010-03-24 14:27:12'),(1397,839,5,'Have got to the last, yet to be built, hairpin before heading to Karepa.  I didn\'t pace it out but maybe 40m to go.','2010-03-25 11:29:27','2010-03-25 11:29:27'),(1398,80,23,'There\'s a short new section at the eastern end to separate this track from [[track:859]].','2010-03-27 20:45:14','2010-03-27 20:45:14'),(1399,859,23,'Now benched throughout.  The western end has taken over a short section of [[track:80]], which now follows a new parallel path.','2010-03-27 20:47:11','2010-03-27 20:47:11'),(1400,74,23,'The gas pipeline that runs down the hill is having a series of retaining walls built to protect it from the elements and motorbikes. Where this track crosses the pipeline there are some signs warning about the building work.  ','2010-03-27 20:52:13','2010-03-27 20:52:13'),(1401,75,23,'Occasional tree root and exposed rock, but otherwise in fine condition.','2010-03-27 20:53:31','2010-03-27 20:53:31'),(1402,79,23,'A bit of track pixie work has tidied up a few sections. Meanwhile, some of the drops seem to be getting bigger â€“ especially off the end of the hair-pin bend\'s wooden ramp.','2010-03-27 20:56:09','2010-03-27 20:56:09'),(1403,78,23,'Seemed more worn that usual, with many of the exposed tree roots accompanied by ruts.','2010-03-27 20:58:02','2010-03-27 20:58:02'),(1404,176,23,'The rut mentioned below is getting deeper. Meanwhile, some large pine trees have been recently removed from within the area circumscribed by the loop.','2010-03-27 21:00:00','2010-03-27 21:00:00'),(1405,77,23,'Some large pine trees have been felled at the bottom of this track, shedding additional light on the jumps.','2010-03-27 21:01:28','2010-03-27 21:01:28'),(1406,738,23,'Track surface is all good.  There looks to be an alternative line under development around a couple of the more difficult features.','2010-03-27 21:02:41','2010-03-27 21:02:41'),(1407,739,23,'In great condition, though the bottom half\'s track surface isn\'t quite as polished as the top half.','2010-03-27 21:11:38','2010-03-27 21:11:38'),(1408,887,23,'Rideable throughout, though the track surface isn\'t yet fully completed.','2010-03-27 21:24:23','2010-03-27 21:24:23'),(1409,839,23,'Updated the map. The track is benched up to the last switchback, which is 75m from meeting [[track:861]].','2010-03-27 21:28:59','2010-03-27 21:28:59'),(1410,27,92,'Wear longs when \'walking\'. This track is pretty overgrown with angry plants.','2010-03-28 10:29:36','2010-03-28 10:29:36'),(1411,50,92,'EDI Downer sign at trailhead says \"Closed\"\n\nNot very obvious if you\'ve come off ridgeline. \n\nNot sure what the reason for closure is?','2010-03-28 10:36:13','2010-03-28 10:36:13'),(1412,49,232,'A bit of debris on the track from some recent weed-eating. Still rideable though.','2010-03-28 13:47:00','2010-03-28 13:47:00'),(1413,861,92,'Not sure this is an \'easy\' track. Ok it\'s a sealed path, but it is fairly steep - Intermediate?','2010-03-30 07:08:02','2010-03-30 07:08:02'),(1414,882,92,'Large tree has fallen across path just before the s-bend. Eye popping tentacles are hard to spot on a dark morning.','2010-03-30 21:03:43','2010-03-30 21:03:43'),(1415,861,23,'Fair point â€“ a 20% slope isn\'t easy.  Therefore, the Grade has been changed to \"Intermediate\".','2010-03-30 21:22:25','2010-03-30 21:22:25'),(1416,28,5,'Warning - from today painters are working on the pylon at top of coaster.  Vehicles go up and down fenceline to Highbury.','2010-03-31 21:17:11','2010-03-31 21:17:11'),(1417,839,5,'Good progress today with about half the remaining distance done ie 30m to go, and that has been cleared more so you can walk bikes thru\'.','2010-03-31 21:19:01','2010-03-31 21:19:01'),(1418,881,23,'The last evening session for the season was held on Tuesday.  The top 270m of the track is rideable (though needing further refinement), the next 50m is mostly cleared but not benched, and the last 50m is still jungle. In a couple of weeks from now a corporate group is scheduled to do further work on the track.','2010-04-01 07:35:59','2010-04-01 07:35:59'),(1419,67,92,'Quite a big break down of the outside edge of the track. At least half the bench has broken down. Confined to one patch. Closer to the CP end. \n\nIt isn\'t an issue riding out towards Red Rocks direction. You will certainly notice it if you are riding back towards CP. \n\nRest of the track is a bit loose and dusty. Little bit of moisture wouldn\'t hurt.','2010-04-02 12:21:59','2010-04-02 12:21:59'),(1420,7,11,'Overall pretty dry, those corners with the gravel are really bad now, I dont think there is much substance under them. Maybe whoever laid the gravel was hoping for rain to help it bed down?','2010-04-02 18:53:04','2010-04-02 18:53:04'),(1421,784,165,'Took my bike for a walk around the 629 today.  Extreme might be a bit of an understatement.  Would suggest 1st timers maybe only go with someone that knows the track and the riders ability.  Hats off to the madmen that actually ride it!','2010-04-03 13:19:41','2010-04-03 13:19:41'),(1422,890,23,'Very pleasant under the trees, though a few in the middle section have been felled. Grassy section at the eastern end is well trimmed.','2010-04-03 13:55:03','2010-04-03 13:55:03'),(1423,892,23,'Heaps of steps, many in less than optimal condition. Some of the steeper gravel sections are quite loose.','2010-04-03 13:56:26','2010-04-03 13:56:26'),(1424,893,23,'Some moderate ruts just above the intersection with [[track:892]].  The area around the top 0.1km has been logged, though the track is clear.','2010-04-03 13:58:17','2010-04-03 13:58:17'),(1425,891,23,'Looks to be ongoing construction of jumps and drops adjacent to the ridgeline road, so expect continuing changes.','2010-04-03 14:16:15','2010-04-03 14:16:15'),(1426,894,23,'Construction is progressing well. The entire track is rideable, though some sections are a bit soft and loose.','2010-04-03 14:19:45','2010-04-03 14:19:45'),(1427,178,92,'Signs of digging and rebenching. Hope work includes reshaping of a couple of ugly switchbacks!','2010-04-03 21:01:23','2010-04-03 21:01:23'),(1428,30,199,'Track in good very condition. Stream crossings at lowish levels.','2010-04-04 10:07:50','2010-04-04 10:07:50'),(1429,52,199,'Drop in at start is moist but not greasy, usual mild ruts. Slight over growth at beginning. ','2010-04-04 10:10:03','2010-04-04 10:10:31'),(1430,12,92,'Flax at the end of Zac\'s is trying to conceal the track exit.','2010-04-04 18:52:38','2010-04-04 18:52:38'),(1431,35,92,'Yup. That bridge is very, very slick in the wet.','2010-04-04 18:55:35','2010-04-04 18:55:35'),(1432,673,122,'The loop track round the upper lake is a little overgrown with one or two fallen trees, but is still easily navigable.','2010-04-04 19:18:07','2010-04-04 19:18:07'),(1433,27,92,'Bumped into a very weird dude on this track today. Both buddy and I swore we could smell smoke at various points along the track after running into him. No other obvious signs of fire (we looked around). Just noting in case there are any issues reported.','2010-04-05 18:00:22','2010-04-05 18:00:22'),(1434,792,122,'The track is closed for renovations between Kau Kau summit and Woodmancote St.  When it re-opens it will be wider and have new steps.','2010-04-05 19:11:47','2010-04-05 19:11:47'),(1435,1,23,'Generally good, though there are a few spots that could do with a touch up.','2010-04-05 20:38:27','2010-04-05 20:38:27'),(1436,2,23,'Some bits are getting a bit worn.','2010-04-05 20:39:22','2010-04-05 20:39:22'),(1437,3,23,'A few stray ferns along the eastern side, while in places the western side seems to be going for that desiccated, cracked mud look.','2010-04-05 20:45:44','2010-04-05 20:46:16'),(1438,4,23,'Really dry and dusty, with quite a lot of loose rock along the way.','2010-04-05 20:47:11','2010-04-05 20:47:11'),(1439,12,23,'Top end is very dry and loose.','2010-04-05 20:47:54','2010-04-05 20:47:54'),(1440,613,23,'This track gets better every week. The refinement work is now around half way down, with lots of nice berms and other adjustments adding polish to an already great track.','2010-04-05 20:49:59','2010-04-05 20:49:59'),(1441,881,23,'Much refinement work was done today, adding more berms and other busy features to the top two-thirds of this track. The rest will be rideable soon â€“ in the meantime, there\'s a short walk and then jump up to [[track:50]].','2010-04-05 20:53:02','2010-04-05 20:54:23'),(1442,50,23,'A few rocks and exposed roots to watch out for on the last quarter of the track.','2010-04-05 20:55:45','2010-04-05 20:55:45'),(1443,6,23,'Very dry and hard surface, as usual.','2010-04-05 20:58:12','2010-04-05 20:58:12'),(1444,7,23,'The good news is that much of the stray gravel has been swept off the corners, so becoming less of a concern.','2010-04-05 20:59:40','2010-04-05 20:59:40'),(1445,22,23,'This track has quite a different character when ridden down in the near-dark with an inadequate light. Some of the trees seemed closer than during daylight.','2010-04-05 21:03:30','2010-04-05 21:03:30'),(1446,585,59,'This area has been logged, Pondy downhill is not rideable.','2010-04-06 11:36:12','2010-04-06 11:38:38'),(1447,882,92,'Tree has been removed by WCC contractors.','2010-04-11 10:20:59','2010-04-11 10:20:59'),(1448,895,23,'In fine condition, with firm gravel surface throughout.','2010-04-11 14:57:20','2010-04-11 14:57:20'),(1449,896,23,'This track has been upgraded recently, with some realignments and resurfacing.  Currently dry and in excellent condition.','2010-04-11 15:01:53','2010-04-11 15:01:53'),(1450,897,23,'Looks to have had some maintenance work recently, especially on the lower sections, so in fine condition.','2010-04-11 15:03:05','2010-04-11 15:03:05'),(1451,342,232,'There are a couple of short but excellent tracks that head off the downhill side of this.','2010-04-12 09:59:24','2010-04-12 09:59:24'),(1453,839,5,'Now rideable to Karepa!  Some hairpins require more work and future workparties will remove scrub and improve flow.  Enjoy!','2010-04-15 10:44:19','2010-04-15 10:44:19'),(1454,881,23,'Awesome progress today â€“ now rideable throughout!  The last 100m at the [[track:73]] end is freshly dug, so very soft. Not quite fully benched yet, with more refinement to follow, but rideable nonetheless.','2010-04-17 19:29:23','2010-04-17 19:29:23'),(1455,1,23,'A few prominent tree roots in awkward places, which look to be ideal candidates for the [[link:http://www.makarapeak.org/Default.aspx?pageId=593368 Adopt A Track]] initiative.','2010-04-18 08:33:39','2010-04-18 08:33:39'),(1456,2,23,'Some ferns draped across the track, so remember to duck.','2010-04-18 08:34:55','2010-04-18 08:34:55'),(1457,3,23,'Fun \'n games: encountered riders coming the other way (yes, this is a two-way track) and a rider who fell a long way down the bank on the western side â€“ bike and rider both OK.','2010-04-18 08:37:11','2010-04-18 08:37:11'),(1458,4,23,'A bit of rain recently has dampened the dust, which is helpful.','2010-04-18 08:43:42','2010-04-18 08:43:42'),(1459,12,23,'Quite treacherous along the upper section, with tiny rock beads on a hard surface.','2010-04-18 08:45:56','2010-04-18 08:45:56'),(1460,613,23,'A bit of rain and lots of traffic have nicely compacted the surface. Still advisable to not stray much from the riding line, as the edges are very soft.','2010-04-18 08:47:44','2010-04-18 08:47:44'),(1461,50,23,'Definitely getting a bit rough along the last part. I wonder if this track is getting more use as a flow on effect of traffic going down [[track:613]]?','2010-04-18 08:50:27','2010-04-18 08:50:27'),(1462,7,23,'Big patch of gravel is back on one of the corners â€“ a bit awkward.','2010-04-18 08:51:39','2010-04-18 08:51:39'),(1463,22,23,'Definitely easier now to treat the step as a jump rather than rolling down it. ','2010-04-18 08:52:38','2010-04-18 08:52:38'),(1464,840,40,'The last bit is rideable but gorsey and very steep. Tiny bit of single track at the end is very overgrown.','2010-04-18 09:56:52','2010-04-18 09:56:52'),(1465,870,88,'First corner and entry line opened up substantially. The berm is very soft, as is the huge new berm around the pine tree (4th corner) and the rocky switchback below that (6th corner). \n\nUntil we get some rain to pack these new sections down please ride with caution or at least not leaning over your front wheel ;-)\n\n','2010-04-18 19:45:14','2010-04-18 19:52:50'),(1466,839,92,'Well I guess it had to happen...the ditch at the start of the second path is flattened. I really liked riding up there tho... this is an awesome track. Well done CS and pixies.','2010-04-19 19:39:07','2010-04-19 19:39:07'),(1467,905,122,'Logging is currently underway at the Nikau Valley entrance to the forest.  Avoid this area.','2010-04-24 19:45:06','2010-04-24 19:45:06'),(1468,316,23,'Cleared a couple of fallen branches, otherwise all good.','2010-04-25 20:18:23','2010-04-25 20:18:23'),(1469,35,23,'Remember to duck under the tree near the bottom. The rest of the track is its usual pine needle covered goodness.','2010-04-25 20:20:03','2010-04-25 20:20:03'),(1470,11,23,'Trimmed way back, which is excellent â€“ though it does highlight how narrow the riding line is in places.','2010-04-25 20:21:53','2010-04-25 20:21:53'),(1472,12,23,'The flax around the lower end has been trimmed, so all clear.','2010-04-25 20:23:46','2010-04-25 20:23:46'),(1473,613,23,'Some more refinement today, tidying up the last 70m. The last corner is also being redesigned, adding a little detour â€“ just because we can.','2010-04-25 20:26:53','2010-04-25 20:26:53'),(1474,881,23,'The [[track:73]] end was finished today.  The track surface is still very soft, but great fun nonetheless.','2010-04-25 20:29:18','2010-04-25 20:29:18'),(1475,73,23,'A few handlebar-grabbing trees to watch out for, otherwise fine.','2010-04-25 20:30:59','2010-04-25 20:30:59'),(1476,68,23,'Firm and smooth track surface in good condition, though a few bits of encroaching foliage to brush past along the way.','2010-04-25 20:33:37','2010-04-25 20:33:37'),(1477,851,5,'Theres a big work party on Fling on Wed 28th April to deal to the trees and widen the track at the southern end.  Be best to avoid the track tomorrow.','2010-04-27 08:27:26','2010-04-27 08:27:26'),(1478,851,92,'Feel free to lend a hand tomorrow.  No work party on Transient as we\'ve nicked all the tools!\n\nTime?','2010-04-27 08:27:44','2010-04-27 19:10:53'),(1479,851,5,'Theres a big work party on Fling on Wed 28th April to deal to the trees and widen the track at the southern end.  Be best to avoid the track tomorrow.','2010-04-27 08:28:04','2010-04-27 08:28:04'),(1480,739,252,'Council workers are out adding gravel to the lower end, watch out during weekdays for the power barrow!','2010-04-28 15:09:34','2010-04-28 15:09:34'),(1482,851,5,'Very successful workparty yesterday.  Most of the tree stumps removed and the track widened.  All good.','2010-04-29 11:22:40','2010-04-29 11:22:40'),(1483,910,113,'Please scope the structures before you hit them.   Most take a bit of knowlegde to hit so best you have a wee look first.  A couple riders have already come off second best [it was dark mind you]','2010-05-06 09:19:07','2010-05-06 09:19:07'),(1484,613,1,'Checked it out today, riding sweet. Great work gang.','2010-05-06 22:15:43','2010-05-06 22:15:43'),(1485,80,23,'In fine condition â€“ firm and dry.','2010-05-08 13:57:43','2010-05-08 13:57:43'),(1487,859,23,'Rideable throughout, though most of the track surface is still fairly raw with only a short section having gravel.','2010-05-08 13:59:09','2010-05-08 13:59:09'),(1488,74,23,'The gas pipeline work appears to be complete. Meanwhile, the track is in great condition.','2010-05-08 14:00:15','2010-05-08 14:00:15'),(1489,739,23,'The recently added gravel is like a concrete path, being firm and fast.  But watch out for the edges, which are not as solid as they look. The gravel ends at the bottom of the zig-zag section.','2010-05-08 14:02:43','2010-05-08 14:02:43'),(1490,176,23,'Eastern side is in fine condition, though the anti-skid mesh on the boardwalk doesn\'t seem very robust as a small section has has broken again.','2010-05-08 14:05:12','2010-05-08 14:05:12'),(1491,738,23,'Updated the map with a bypass around the drops in the middle section. Watch the step where the bypass rejoins the main line.','2010-05-08 14:09:37','2010-05-08 14:09:52'),(1492,911,23,'Very busy little piece of track, with lots of twists and turns along minimal gradient. More sections of track to be added later.','2010-05-08 14:13:18','2010-05-08 14:13:18'),(1493,294,5,'Further work on this track has been shelved for the time being - we are putting our energy into finishing Transient and then Windmill.  These are the feeder tracks from town to Carparts Extension.  When they are done we\'ll refocus on the mighty Barking Emu.  WCC consent is still pending.','2010-05-10 15:32:35','2010-05-10 15:32:35');
