t the top of [[track:289]] and Whakatikei Road (otherwise known as [[track:285]]), to a T-intersection where [[track:288]] heads off to the right.','Eastern end is at the top of [[track:283]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nWestern end is at an intersection with [[track:288]].','This track forms part of the [[track:255]] course.','5.786',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2009-04-05 11:52:32',23,'-40.994152','175.028086',13,3,1,4,23,'2009-04-05 11:52:32','calc',5),(285,'Big Ring Boulevard',15,'','Fast and almost continuously down hill forestry road.','This is a fast and almost continuously down hill run to Doper\'s Creek.  Watch out for some tight corners which can be tricky at speed.\r\n[[para]]\r\nAs you approach the valley floor, you\'ll pass the eastern end of [[track:301]] (on your right).  About 0.35km later you\'ll meet the point where Rimu Road crosses the Whakatikei River, which is the end of this track and the start of [[track:286]].','Starts near the western end of [[track:284]] â€“ turn left into Whakatikei Road.\r\n[[para]]\r\nEnds at an intersection with Rimu Road, next to Whakatikei River and near Doper\'s Creek.','This track forms part of the [[track:255]] course.','4.893',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2009-04-03 20:43:49',23,'-41.014102','175.019846',13,3,1,1,23,'2009-06-29 12:27:18','calc',5),(286,'Doper\'s',15,'','Steep and almost continuous climb up from Doper\'s Creek.','This is the third, and final, big climb of the [[track:255]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe climb starts from just west of the confluence of Doper\'s Creek and the Whakatikei River.  Head up the hill for a 320m climb that is not as steep as the first two big climbs of the [[track:255]], but it is more consistently up.','Starts at the bottom of [[track:285]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nEnds at the start of the [[track:287]].','This track forms part of the [[track:255]] course.','2.728',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2009-04-03 20:51:36',23,'-41.026503','175.039415',15,3,1,3,23,'2009-04-03 20:51:36','calc',5),(287,'Pram Track',15,'',