'','Coastal track from Mukamuka Stream to Onoke Spit past the small Ocean Beach settlement','Start the track either from Onoke Spit, or from Ocean Beach.  Ocean Beach is a small fishing settlement - there are houses and fishing boats but no stores (nearest gas station and food is Featherston).\r\n[[para]]\r\nThere is a 4WD track to Mukamuka stream, and on round the coast.  Walking is fine, but there are locked gates to prevent vehicles from going down the track.  Check out the historic Mukamuka Covenant memorial on the eastern side of Mukamuka stream.\r\n[[para]]\r\nIt is a wild and desolate coastline, so make sure you are adequately prepared for the trip.  Cellphones may be out of range.\r\n[[para]]\r\nMukamuka Covenant\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2460/3776799345_278622a3ca.jpg:Mukamuka Covenant:490:326]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nCoastline\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2429/3776799365_4980cd4467.jpg:Coastline:490:326]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nOcean Beach\r\n[[image:http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3522/3776799387_f0fa672b1a.jpg:Ocean Beach:490:326]]','By car, down Western Lake Road about 40 km south of Featherston.  The last 5 - 10 km of road is unsealed.','Cycling possible on the 4WD track between Ocean Beach and Mukamuka','8.672',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2009-08-01 21:03:41',122,'-41.378097','175.052719',12,2,2,3,122,'2009-08-01 21:07:09','calc',5),(397,'Palmer Head',22,'','Spectacular views over Wellington airport and Southern coast','Track description given starting from Rangitatau reserve on the southern coast road just round from Moa Point.  There is a carpark at the entrance to the reserve and [[track:400]].  There is also a larger carpark across the road.  From the carpark the track goes either right to Ataturk Memorial, left to Kekeranga St, or straight up.  The route here is the wide sealed road going straight up the hill for about 500 metres.  This is a \"Woof woof ruff\" area and popular with owners following their dogs and cleaning up the things that dogs do!\r\n[[para]]\r\nAt the top of the rise about 500 metres from the carpark the Eastern walkway veers to the right.  Follow the track to the left and on to Bowes Crescent (there is another large carpark here).  Go up Bowes Crescent for a short distance, then left onto Birhall Grove and onto the Airport corporation walking track at the end of the grove.  You then join a reasonable wide sealed track leading past Palmer Head airport navigation station and radio beacon, with good views over Cook Strait and the airport area.  On the left just past the radio antenna are some old gun bunkers, covered with graffiti but interesting to walk round and watch the planes come in.  The track continues to exit point on Ahuriri St/Kekerenga St corner.  There is a locked gate here, but a large opening in the fence allows walkers, cyclists and dogs to pass through.\r\n[[para]]\r\nGun bunkers\r\n[[image:http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3538/3779203205_00b73e3432.jpg:Gun bunkers Palmer Head:490:326]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nView of Wellington airport\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2437/3779203225_4a8f7d290f.jpg:Wellington airport:490:326]]','Good carparks at Rangitatau reserve, Bowes Crescent, and on Ahuriri St.  Buses may run up Ahuriri St.','Bicycles are allowed on the section round Palmer Head from Ahuriri St, but not in Rangitatau reserve.','2.143',108,0,2,110,'','','2009-08-02 15:35:25',122,'-41.337219','174.813981',15,2,2,5,122,'2009-08-03 20:52:45','calc',5),(398,'Kekerenga Reserve',22,'','Pleasant walk across sandy hillsides with good views over Wellington airport','Beginning from the park on Kekerenga Street the sandy track meanders along the hillside overlooking the airport and golf links.  After about 250 metres there is the [[track:401]] leading down past the golf links and sewerage treatment plant to the south coast.  The track continues north along the hillside for about 1 km to Tukanae reserve.  From here there are exits to Tukanae St and Ahuriri St.\r\n','There are several entry and exit points, but parking is not possible around the sewerage treatment works.  Plenty of parking on Ahuriri St and Kekerenga St.  There may be a bus service to this area.','Bicycle access okay on track, but a few steps at each access point.','0.942',0,14,77,63,'','','2009-08-02 15:53:20',122,'-41.337380','174.814689',16,2,1,1,122,'2009-08-02 19:51:16','calc',5),(399,'Rangitatau Reserve',22,'','Sheltered walk from Rangitatau carpark to Kekerenga crescent','This is the small track from Rangitatau carpark winding up to the left through the scrub and bush to join the sealed road on Palmer Head near the navigation array.  If you want to start the track from Palmer Head, the start of the track is a little tricky to find - there is a peg with a white top, and a small mound of stones.  Once you start the track it will be found well formed.','Park at Rangitatau carpark, or at the Palmer Head entrance on Kekerenga Crescent.','Bicycles are not permitted in Rangitatau reserve.','0.774',115,0,5,120,'','','2009-08-02 16:02:07',122,'-41.335898','174.822135',15,3,2,1,122,'2009-08-03 20:53:21','calc',5),(400,'Ataturk Memorial',22,'','Short walk to historic Ataturk memorial with views over East harbour','From Rangitatau carpark the track heads up a few steps to the right and about 250 metres to the large white Ataturk memorial.  The track then continues up for another 600 metres to rejoin the Eastern walkway track.  If you are doing the Eastern walkway I recommend doing this diversion instead of following the main route up Woof Woof Ruff.\r\n[[para]]\r\nAtaturk memorial\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2450/3780012258_82bf719fee.jpg:Ataturk memorial:326:490]]','Park at Rangitatau carpark, which is a short way along the southern coast past Moa Point.','Bicycles not allowed in Rangitatau reserve.','0.914',77,NULL,3,80,'','','2009-08-02 16:11:19',122,'-41.335544','174.819946',15,1,2,1,122,'2009-10-17 21:06:54','calc',5),(401,'Moa Pt steps',22,'','Exit fr