ough a felled section to the road, or you can turn left at the saddle and exit via \"Gliding Glovers\" track','Access is via Sharlands Road.\r\nFrom the forest enterance about 4km up the Maitai Valley Road, ride up until you see a road to the left called Sharland Road.\r\nRide 8.5km up this road, making sure you DO NOT turn off at either of the Bob Fern Road signs. you will ride on up until you come to a huge skidder site at the 7km mark and follow the road around to the left. from here head up past a water lake avoiding any turn offs until you come to Thomas road at the top. Turn left into Thomas road, and ride along for about 200m to where Savage road goes off to the right.\r\nIf you look to the left at this intersection, you shouls find the entrance to this track.','[[image:http://www.tasman.net/~newport2/PROFILES/RUSH.jpg:Rush Profile:500:400]]\r\n','2.216',25,207,535,326,'Pretty well all downhill, just a couple of minor short pinches',' - Great track to advance your skills on','2009-08-12 11:06:51',135,'-41.246286','173.359945',15,4,3,1,135,'2010-01-12 11:53:56','calc',5),(474,'Rush Early Exit',101,' - Weekend Only - Permit Required','An alternative exit to R and R Rush','This was originaly made as a temporary exit, but is still ridden by those who do not like the small climb through the rest of the trail','See the R and R Rush description for details','','0.318',0,64,392,328,'Has small uphill section in the middle',' - Tricky Rocky Exit','2009-08-12 11:38:14',135,'-41.241597','173.358800',15,4,3,1,135,'2009-08-13 19:46:08','calc',5),(475,'Gliding Glovers',101,' - Weekend Only - Permit Required','An alternative exit to the R and R Rush extention.\r\nSee R and R descriptions for further information','From the saddle of the R and R Extention, this is an alternative exit to the easier option to the right. It undulates across the Douglas firs, and then drops into a small valley with a couple of berms and then down through a rooty section before dropping out onto th