ngton motorway, to a car parking area near Everton Terrace.  Cross over the motorway at Everton Terrace and walk left along the top of Boulcott St and then take the signposted walkway left into the trees, which heads uphill for about 250 metres to the playing fields and memorial fountain.  This track through the trees has steps in places, but can also be muddy after rain.  The walkway skirts around the outside of the playing fields and emerges near the sharp corner of Salamanca Road and Kelburn Parade.  About 100 metres up Kelburn Parade on the right-hand side is an accessway (lots of steps) up to Rawhiti Terrace.  Turn right along Rawhiti Terrace and about 150 metres along there is a walkway leading uphill to join up with the station at the top of the Cable Car at the botanic gardens.\r\n\r\n','Either take the cable car to the top stop at Kelburn, or walk up Willis Street to Ghuznee St.','Many variations are possible to the route shown.  Some parts of this route are on the longer City-to-Sea Walkway. You may also like to do  the Terrace Gardens walkway nearby.','2.293',78,NULL,50,128,'','','2009-08-13 20:07:48',122,'-41.285321','174.777203',15,1,2,1,122,'2009-08-29 22:46:08','calc',5),(515,'Peaking Ridge',105,' - Long Ride','Peaking Ridge is a Grade 4-5 advanced cross country track.','Peaking Ridge is a Grade 4-5 advanced cross country track.\r\nIt is approximatly 2.3km long and drops from 665m down to 177m.\r\nAccess is via [[track:517]] and [[track:516]] from the top of [[track:512]].\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe track itself starts with a daunting drop down from the ridge and then settles into a technical rootfest with a few good ramps and drops in there for good measure.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis track is part of an epic 4-6 hour ride combining a climb up [[track:512]], [[track:517]], [[track:516]], [[track:nelson:PeakingRidge]] and the ride home down the Maitai Valley.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThis combined ride is very open to the weather so suitable clothing and emergency equipment s