rest and scrub, until you get to \"Four Corners\" an intersection between the Dun Tack and \"The Classic\".\r\nFrom here its a further 5km through some beautiful native forest alongside the Brook Bird Sanctuary up to Third House.\r\nIf you are venturing further, the track remains easy riding another 4km up to the site of the original forth house (some ruins). its then becomes a singletrack through to Windy point, and then a technical singletrack the last 2.5km to Coppermine Saddle.\r\nSome inspiring views to be had on a fine clear Nelson day.\r\nPack a picnic and take your time. The huge fun downhill all the way back always seems longer than the ride up.. an added bonus!','From Central Nelson find Brook Street and travel up brook Street past the shop on the right. The road carries on straight and becomes one way, carry on untill you find Blick Terrace on the right. Park here.\r\nOn brook street on the left hand side heading up the valley just before the blick terrace turn off, you will find a monument. This is the start of the easy track, Codgers Connection. Ride up here past the water works, and then keep to the right on the corner, traveliing around to a gate. the track heads off to the left here and is signposted.\r\nA steeper alternative, is to carry on up Brook street to where there is a big paddock on the left, and take the first left here and park at the official Dun Mountain Carpark and ride up the steep track. ','','17.516',826,22,49,875,'',' - long ride that although easy requires fitness','2009-08-13 20:53:46',135,'-41.309447','173.337660',12,2,1,2,135,'2010-01-11 16:36:42','calc',5),(519,'Bullock Spur',105,' Try and stop at the bottom!','Not Strictly a track, this firebreak is sometimes ridden by madmen with a death wish.\r\n','Access is from \"The Classic\" on cummings spur road. Ride up to the carpark on fringed hill, then start your way down the cummings spur until you see this track off to the right as you head down.\r\nWhile technicaly \"possible\" 