ke and walk, or continue on a rougher track to the coast.','When travelling north from Christchurch, turn left of SH1 immediately after crossing the Ashley river bridge.  There is a carpark beside the river, with anglers access roads leading both east and west.','','2.259',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2009-11-18 19:55:35',122,'-43.278955','172.704391',14,2,1,4,122,'2009-11-18 19:59:12','calc',5),(667,'Travis Wetland',118,'','Loop walk around a nature reserve.','[[link:http://traviswetland.org.nz/ Travis wetland]] is a nature and bird reserve in northern Christchurch Burwood area.  It is popular with nature lovers, and also with the locals for a morning stroll.  The track shown is a loop walk from the main carpark off Frosts Road but there are a number of other entry/exit points for shorter walks.','In northern Christchurch, take Queen Elizabeth II Drive (route 74, which becomes Travis Road) towards the sea, turn left on to Frosts Road and the main carpark is mid-way up the road on the left.  There are also access points on the northern end from Mairehau Road and from Travis Country Drive on the southern side.  ','Cyclists and dogs not allowed, except on the track along the southern end beside Travis Road, which is outside of the reserve but bordering the wetland.','3.612',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2009-11-18 20:54:01',122,'-43.483909','172.692933',15,1,2,2,122,'2009-11-18 20:54:50','calc',5),(668,'Bridal Veil',119,'','A reasonably gentle walk through forest north of Arthurs Pass.','From the carpark at the northern end of Arthurs Pass the track is marked at the same place at the more popular (shorter) route to Devils Punchbowl Falls.  The Bridal Veil track is through Beech forest and has a reasonable gradient except for a short \"down and up\" in the middle.  It exits to SH73, but there is no footpath so return is along the same route.  Allow 1.5 hours for the return walk.\r\n[[para]]\r\nThe walks are documented in a small booklet available at the Arthurs Pass informa