ou pick up the signs again for Karori Sanctuary across the road which takes a shortcut to old Karori Road.  From here you walk along the pavement up to Chaytor Street besdie the park, cross Birdwood Terrace, and then walk down Waiapu Road to Karori Sanctuary.\r\n[[para]]\r\nGun magazines Trelissick Park\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2719/4198815747_6b5bcd962e.jpg:Historic gun magazines:320:480]]\r\n[[para]]\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2743/4198815751_0b3c4e950c.jpg:Sanctuary to Sea sign:320:480]]\r\n[[para]]\r\nKarori Sanctuary visitor centre\r\n[[image:http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2694/4198815753_927517350a.jpg:Karori Sanctuary:480:320]]','At the Ngaio gorge end you can park off Ngaio gorge at the second entrance to Trelissick Park (there is no off-street parking at the bottom entrance).  Alternatively the Kaiwharawhara train station isn\'t far away, and there is a bus stop at the bottom of Ngaio Gorge.\r\n[[para]]\r\nYou can park near Karori Sanctuary at the other end, though parking can be scarce on a sunny weekend.  The Karori bus stops on Chaytor Street near Karori tunnel.\r\n[[para]]\r\nFor a mid-way park, there is a large carpark at the Wilton house entrance to Otari-Wilton bush off Churchill Drive.','Cycling not permitted in Trelissick Park or Otari-Wilton bush.','7.453',116,NULL,17,133,'','','2009-12-20 20:12:56',122,'-41.265550','174.774284',13,2,2,2,122,'2009-12-20 20:18:48','calc',5),(723,'Thorby Street',41,'','Joins Raroa Crescent to Northland Road going \"over\" the Northland tunnel','Shortcut for pedestrians who wish to bypass Northland tunnel.  The walking track zig-zags up to Thorby Street from Raroa Crescent about 200 metres south of the Northland tunnel.  After cross Thorby St there is another pedestrian way zig-zagging down to Northland Road about 100 metres from the small roundabout by Upland Rd/Kelburn viaduct.\r\n[[para]]\r\nExit from Thorby St walkway to Northland Road\r\n[[image:http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4006