e top, head 0.3km to the east (turn left), along [[track:83]], to find the top of [[track:87]].  Alternatively, 1.5km to the west (turn right) is the top of [[track:742]] which ends only 0.2km around the road from the bottom of this track â€“ making for a nice circuit.  ','Bottom end is on Gardiner Grove, between numbers 19A and 19B.\r\n[[para]]\r\nTop meets [[track:83]] via a stile at a well sign-posted T-intersection.','Like most tracks in this area, bikes are not permitted.','0.944',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2010-01-02 13:49:15',23,'-41.267558','174.937588',16,3,2,2,23,'2010-01-02 14:34:16','calc',5),(742,'Lees Grove',9,'','Very steep walking track between [[track:83]] and Lees Grove.','The top section of this track is extremely steep, with roughhewn steps cut into the clay providing some assistance for negotiating the 60%+ gradient. As the track descends down a ridge and then into a valley, the gradient mellows to eventually become a gentle stroll through a pleasant bush-filled setting.\r\n[[para]]\r\nMuch of the track surface is moderately rough, being a mixture of bare dirt and exposed tree roots.\r\n[[para]]\r\nTowards the bottom of the track, there are a couple of small bridges across a creek.  The bottom 0.2km follows a fence before emerging suddenly onto the footpath at the very top end of Lees Grove.\r\n[[para]]\r\nFrom the top head 1.5km to the east to find the top of [[track:741]], which ends only 0.2km around the road from the bottom of this track â€“ making for a nice circuit. ','Bottom is at the top end of Lees Grove, next to a bunch of letter boxes.\r\n[[para]]\r\nTop meets [[track:83]] via a stile at a well sign-posted T-intersection.','Like most tracks in this area, bikes are not permitted.','1.080',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','2010-01-02 13:53:38',23,'-41.265945','174.929692',16,3,2,1,23,'2010-01-02 14:52:35','calc',5),(743,'Puriri',9,'','Short and steep walking track connecting Wainuiomata Road with [[track:82]].','Starting from no-man\'s-land ju